ost thaw impact physical, biological, chemical, and hydrological processes of peatlands, and how this has cascading impacts on downstream ecosystems. From this we will develop a better understanding of the overall impact of disturbances at the catchments scale. The main objectives of this research program are: 1) To project future greenhouse gas exchange and carbon storage in northern peatlands; and 2) To understand the role of peatlands as biogeochemical hot spots from a catchment perspective. Northern peatlands are of importance both at the global scale through their influence on the climate through land-atmosphere greenhouse gas emission, and at the local to regional scales through their implications for water quality, biodiversity, human health, and resource/infrastructure development. Improving our understanding of peatland functions is at the core of this research program.","principal_investigator":"David Olefeldt","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":2959,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2015-11-26 22:57:01 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-26 22:57:01 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--106","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Margot Bishop","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2960,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2015-11-27 02:49:44 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-27 02:49:44 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--374","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sharon Farnel","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2961,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2015-11-27 02:51:39 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-27 02:51:39 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--107","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sharon Farnel","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2962,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2015-11-27 14:37:30 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-27 14:37:30 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--108","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Alyssa Rahemtulla","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2972,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2015-11-27 20:29:07 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-27 20:29:07 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--127","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Douglas Race","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2973,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2015-11-27 20:41:04 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-27 20:41:04 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--117","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2975,"title":"Local Culture Research Archive Digital Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2015-11-29 22:46:16 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-29 22:48:34 UTC","slug":"local-culture-research-archive-digital-management-plan","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The Local Culture and Diversity on the Prairies project documented everyday life of Prairie Canadians of Ukrainian, French, German and English heritage up to 1939. Hundreds of hours of audio interviews, video and photographs together constitute a rich resource for researchers of ethnic identity, regional variation, locality and community. To make it more accessible for the research community and the general public, the collected data needs to be carefully described using established metadata standards and made available online. Themes specific to Canadian Prairies need to be identified and incorporated into the subject vocabulary. Technical and preservation metadata must be captured to ensure accessibility and long-term sustainability. This project aims to release a segment of the Local Culture corpus into the public domain. Once the infrastructure is in place, it can be expanded to include other resources.","principal_investigator":"Andriy Nahachewsky","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Maryna Chernyavska, 780-299-6043, chernyav@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":2976,"title":"South Asian Music in Canada - South Asian Roots","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2015-11-30 15:39:19 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-30 16:04:14 UTC","slug":"south-asian-music-in-canada-south-asian-roots","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This project supplements the online exhibit, South Asian Music in Canada, by digitizing and making available online a selection of materials (sound recordings, field notes, and related documents) collected by Regula Burckhardt Qureshi in India and Pakistan beginning in the 1960s. The goals are a) to deepen understanding of South Asian musical activities in Canada by presenting related materials from South Asia - where the practices originated, and with which there is continual interaction by Canadian South Asian musicians; and b) to develop and test a process for digitizing and presenting a larger collection of materials collected during Professor Qureshi's career.","principal_investigator":"David Gramit","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"dgramit@ualberta.ca; 780-492-4009","funder_name":null},{"id":2977,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2015-11-30 22:29:05 UTC","updated_at":"2015-11-30 22:29:05 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--118","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Robin Smith","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2978,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2015-12-01 20:02:22 UTC","updated_at":"2015-12-01 20:02:22 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--128","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Kristin Bogdan","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":2979,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2015-12-01 21:21:06 UTC","updated_at":"2015-12-01 21:22:47 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--19","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"SB1","description":"Architecture publique contemporaine","principal_investigator":"Silvie Bernier","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":2980,"title":"Academic Social Networking at the University of Alberta [working thesis title]","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2015-12-02 06:11:26 UTC","updated_at":"2015-12-20 20:57:43 UTC","slug":"academic-social-networking-at-the-university-of-alberta-working-thesis-title","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Today, a variety of platforms exist for storing and making academic scholarship openly accessible (OA). Among these is the institutional repository (IR) – institutionally hosted platforms – which have proliferated over the last decade, despite struggling to gain traction among researchers. In contrast, academic social networking sites (SNSs) have successfully marketed their services to a large and diverse global community of scholars in a short period of time (Thelwall & Kousha, 2014; Ortega 2015). Academic SNSs have received negative criticism largely for their proprietary business model, which is said to exploit the open access model and subvert the principles of openness and transparency on which it is premised (Adema, 2015; Aventurier, 2015; Fitzpatrick, 2015; Hall, 2015; Parry, 2015). Little research, however, has examined content on academic SNSs and the metadata underlying that content, nor have studies compared SNSs to the more established not-for-profit IR. \r\nThe proposed research compares object-level metadata from a sample of deposits made by various University of Alberta researchers on Academia.Edu, Research Gate (RG), and the university IR. The aim is to compare metadata attributes such as formats, types, and standards. The IR represents a curated database of metadata, and should act as a mirror against which to reflect the type and quality of metadata found on the academic SNSs. Identifying the differences in metadata across repositories contributes to improved efforts toward interoperability, and better informed, objective criticism regarding the value of academic SNSs as dissemination platforms.","principal_investigator":"Zachary Schoenberger","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":2981,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2015-12-02 16:46:09 UTC","updated_at":"2015-12-02 16:47:02 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--129","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"SSHRC HART 2.0","principal_investigator":"Sheila Woody","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":2983,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2015-12-02 22:27:10 UTC","updated_at":"2015-12-02 22:27:10 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--119","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal