:"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-12 19:01:32 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-12 19:01:32 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--522","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Natalia Ivanova","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3769,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-13 16:11:47 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-13 16:59:05 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--523","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Cody Fullerton","principal_investigator_identifier":"http://orcid.org/0000-0002-4018-4137","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3770,"title":"Thinking Historically for Canada's Future","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-09-14 18:23:22 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-14 18:27:43 UTC","slug":"thinking-historically-for-canada-s-future","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"SSHRC Partnership Grant: Thinking Historically for Canada's Future\r\n\r\nThe overall goals and objectives of the proposed partnership: In keeping with the goals and objectives of both Insight and Connection Programs, the proposed partnership will build on and extend the successes of THEN/HiER and the HTP in order to provide opportunities for interdisciplinary interaction among various constituencies involved in history education (e.g., historians, Indigenous scholars, history educators working in faculties of education, museum educators, and teachers), with the goals of stimulating, supporting, and enlarging the Canadian history education research base, publishing digital and print teaching resources, and generating research-based policy recommendations, which will have long term implications for, and impacts on, history education across Canada. This will require extensive, long-term collaboration among partners. The partnership will use a range of strategies to:\r\n•\tNurture a community of inquiry among academic historians; researchers based in faculties of education; Indigenous scholars; graduate students; educators in museums, archives and historic sites; practicing teachers; policy makers and other stakeholders;\r\n•\tProvide opportunities for engagement with, and critique of, existing Canadian and international research in the field of history education, with the aim of bridging research and practice. Establish and nurture fertile research connections in Canada and with international colleagues;\r\n•\tDevelop and test innovations that provide more powerful and engaging learning experiences for students;\r\n•\tEngage in the development of authentic, multi-faceted approaches to assess students’ historical thinking. Well-conceived assessments, in conjunction with curriculum, materials and professional development, are a powerful driver of the reform of history education itself; \r\n•\tTransform classroom practice through pro-active connections with ministries of education, faculties of education, Indigenous organizations and stakeholders, textbook publishers, other curriculum developers, and practicing teachers;\r\n•\tConduct professional development in conjunction with partners to promote engaged and critical historical thinking; and\r\n•\tCollaboratively develop, in both official languages, teacher resource materials and on-line museum-based activities and other digital resources, for K-16 history education.\t\r\n","principal_investigator":"Carla Peck","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3771,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2016-09-14 21:16:30 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-14 21:23:17 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--206","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"John Ries","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3772,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-15 16:33:03 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-15 16:33:03 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--524","organisation_id":9,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3773,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-15 17:37:51 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-15 17:37:51 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--525","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Debbie Chaves","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3774,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-15 17:37:51 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-15 17:37:51 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--526","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Debbie Chaves","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3776,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-09-18 22:34:26 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-18 22:34:26 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--513","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Shawn Douglas","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3777,"title":"My plan (MICYRN Data Management Plan Template)","dmptemplate_id":3,"created_at":"2016-09-19 13:30:52 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-19 13:30:52 UTC","slug":"my-plan-micyrn-data-management-plan-template--20","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jessica McEwan","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3778,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-19 14:51:57 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-19 14:51:57 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--528","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jessica McEwan","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3779,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-19 18:58:10 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-19 18:58:10 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--529","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Pamela Jacobs","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3780,"title":"Compromised Conscience: Towards Managing Moral Injuries in Public Safety Personnel","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-09-19 19:10:00 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 18:09:01 UTC","slug":"compromised-conscience-towards-managing-moral-injuries-in-public-safety-personnel","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"PPS 162528","identifier":"","description":"The proposed study will develop and pilot test a course on the concept of MI and moral decision-making for PSP that may be used as an intervention effort to mitigate MI. The main objective is to provide PSP with the tools necessary to deal with the diverse, sometimes morally challenging scenarios that they may face in their professional practice that may lead to moral injury.  The aim of the course is to provide PSP with the skills needed to guard against MI and to manage their cognitions and emotions in the wake of morally challenging events.  Additionally, the course will describe and provide examples of MI or moral distress, and how these psychological constructs can manifest. The study results will focus on producing an evidence-informed curriculum that can be delivered to PSP, either as part of an intervention to ameliorate MI, or as a preventative measure during training, to provide them with vital skills to help support and protect their mental health. Such wide-scale delivery and assessment would be the focus of a future larger, multi-year project; this pilot study is the first step toward developing an intervention that is not only evidence-informed, but evidence-based.\r\nResearch Questions \r\nThe primary research question driving this study is:\r\n\r\nRQ1. \tDo paramedics, firefighters, and police officers taking a pilot course on moral injury feel that the content and delivery are clear and relevant? (e.g., What do participants from the three public service professions feel is important to include in this course? What aspects did individuals who took the course find most effective? What are their suggested improvements?)\r\nSecondary research questions include:\r\nRQ2. \tDoes a course on moral injury—tailored for the needs and types of scenarios likely to be encountered by PSP—lead to improvements in symptoms of moral injury and PTSD among police, firefighters, and paramedics in the short-term (baseline vs. post-course)?\r\nRQ3. \tWhat variables are most strongly correlated with severity of moral injury and with PTSD symptoms?\r\nRQ4.\tIs there a correlation between measures of hardiness and moral injury?\r\nRQ5.  Do men and women report differences in terms of: (a) degree of improvement in moral injury and/or PTSD symptoms following completion of the pilot course; (b) hardiness; and/or (c) baseline and post-course scores along any of the other domains being assessed?\r\n","principal_investigator":"David Malloy","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-6481-6488","data_contact":"Liana Lentz, llentz@ualberta.ca, llentz2@uwo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":3781,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-09-20 12:42:43 UTC","updated_at":"2016-09-20 12:42:43 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--530","organisat