:null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Amy Samson","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3958,"title":"Data Management Plan for HUCO617","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-09 21:56:11 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-17 22:32:40 UTC","slug":"data-management-plan-for-huco617","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Mengchi Sun","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3959,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-09 21:56:43 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-09 21:56:43 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--661","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Mengchi Sun","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3960,"title":"HUCO 617 Final Project (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-09 22:03:14 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 21:32:54 UTC","slug":"huco-617-final-project-university-of-alberta-template","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This project will involve harvesting content from web pages relating to news coverage of the Muskrat Falls hydroelectric development project in Labrador and the protests against the project. The project will address questions about news media's representation of the project and the protestors, and will situate these representations within the wider national and international context of contemporary indigenous environmental action.\r\n\r\nIn order to address these questions, I will harvest WARC files of online news articles  from various news sources. I will extract the text and metadata from these WARC files, and will perform textual analysis on the texts using Voyant tools. I will compare texts from different news sources, and will compare texts from different periods in time.","principal_investigator":"Nailisa Tanner","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3962,"title":"Stone Tools, Diet, & Sociality at the Dawn of Humanity","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-10 02:15:25 UTC","updated_at":"2017-01-05 19:05:49 UTC","slug":"stone-tools-diet-sociality-at-the-dawn-of-humanity","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"SSHRC","identifier":"895-2016-1017","description":"Nature of our research:\r\n\r\n•\tExplore the correlation between growing aridity on the one hand and shifting technologies, functionalities, food-processing abilities, diets, and human dimensions’ contexts on the other;\r\n•\tImplement cutting-edge protocols with respect to analysis of organic remains;\r\n•\tAchieve a holistic characterization of an ancient technology that integrates surface features such as color, texture, or shape with stone provenance, function, and residue analysis;\r\n•\tDevelop sustainable links with the traditional land owners for long term involvement in the Partnership’s endeavors, for dissemination and exchange of information, and for the protection of local heritage;\r\n•\tCreate research and training opportunities for students to acquire laboratory and field training, Masters and PhD degrees, and for involvement in knowledge mobilization;\r\n•\tReposition the role of Olduvai Gorge in the public imagination so that it achieves self-sustainability as a national and international resource.\r\n\r\nOur research questions:\r\n\r\n•\tDid hominins settle wooded areas for their proximity to water and abundance of tubers, seeds, and nuts? Did these affluent places (with their increased safety from large Savannah carnivores supporting large human group sizes) encourage modern sociality?\r\n•\tWhat was the effect of climate change on the occupation of lake shores, the development of new technologies as a function of effective responses to ecological stability and change, and the exploitation of the landscape for stone procurement and food consumption?\r\n•\tSince many resources were no longer in close proximity to human occupation sites, what impact did this multiplicity of food procurement locations have on communication networks across a landscape characterized by scattered fresh water sources and mosaic ecologies?\r\n\r\nPurpose of our research data collection:\r\n\r\nAs a clearly defined archaeological landscape representing the fossil record of a much broader region, Olduvai Gorge provides an exceptional opportunity to examine the validity of central questions for the discipline such as when, why, and how early humans shifted diets to rely on meat and other food sources. By incorporating sites spanning long periods of time excavated by several partners, a model for large scale network among teams and a depth of insight and accuracy will emerge that would not be possible without a partnership approach. Forging this type of network will generate mutually beneficial research opportunities, professional training for Canadian and international colleagues, and offer significant advantages for African scholars to design, conduct, and disseminate information and understanding about human evolution. There is a critical need to utilize the underappreciated information contained in residues from ancient stone tools and their context to illuminate various aspects of early environmental and socioeconomic history, and an urgent need to assess the impact of new field and laboratory techniques while they are emerging.\r\n\r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Dr. Julio Mercader Florin","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID Id 0000-0002-5637-7937","data_contact":"Sara Hormozinejad, 4032206008, sara.hormozinejad@ucalgary.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":3963,"title":"St. Mary's Data Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-10 14:52:54 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-10 14:54:08 UTC","slug":"st-mary-s-data-management-plan","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Kailey  Brennan","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3966,"title":"Friends & Family Study Data Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-10 19:22:08 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-13 19:44:15 UTC","slug":"friends-family-study-data-management-plan","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"2576-8943-0028","identifier":"UWO-557-194","description":"This study addresses the question: How is friendship quality affected by family relationships?  Previous research has shown that negative family relationships translate into a decreased quality of life, but this study seeks to be original by focusing specifically on the nexus between high school students, their friends and their family.  This study aims to determine what type of correlation exists in the hope that it will aid high school teachers and faculty in recognizing problematic social behaviours and identifying situations when school intervention may be needed.","principal_investigator":"Sarah Lawrence","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID http://orcid.org/","data_contact":"Sarah Lawrence","funder_name":null},{"id":3979,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-11 18:27:57 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-11 18:27:57 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--532","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Lynne Motkoski","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3980,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-12 17:33:47 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-12 17:33:47 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--668","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Devina Dandar","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3981,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-12 22:42:48 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-12 22:42:48 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--533","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jennifer Leask","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3982,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-13 03:21:58 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-13 03:21:58 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--534","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Trish Fontaine","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3983,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-13 17:19:39 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-24 00:28:00 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--669","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The Huxley State University Library is developing its next four-year strategic plan for the period of January 2017 to December 2020. The research group at Huxley State University Library has been given the task of surveying the library’s users in order to evaluate whether changes in what the library offers would be advisable to better serve and meet the needs of the users. The survey examines three dimensions of Huxley State University Library’s usage, which are the use of the library’s collections, the use of the library’s physical and virtual spaces, and the use of the library’s services by the library’s users. All three dimensions will be examined by asking a variety of questions regarding the frequency of their usage, barriers that may currently be limiting the usage and affecting their frequency of use, and to what extent aspects of the library are valued. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Kaitlin Hill","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Kaitlin Hill","funder_name":null},{"id":3984,"title":"Coming Together: Understanding the narrative of nurse who care for women and families experiencing ealry miscarriage.","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-13 21:15:54 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-17 00:38:48 UTC","slug":"coming-together-understanding-the-narrative-of-nurse-who-care-for-women-and-families-experiencing-ealry-miscarriage","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Margaret Patrice Drake","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"902-218-3457 mdrake@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":3985,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-13 23:44:43 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-13 23:44:43 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--670","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3986,"title":"The State of Blackness Database Project","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-14 03:21:54 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-14 03:46:09 UTC","slug":"the-state-of-blackness-database-project","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Andrea Fatona","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3988,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-14 16:27:26 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-14 16:27:26 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--59","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Arina Soare","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3989,"title":"Doyle-Lauren-Data-Management-Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-15 01:18:36 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-15 01:21:37 UTC","slug":"doyle-lauren-data-management-plan","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Lauren Doyle","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":3990,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-15 20:04:41 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-15 20:04:41 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--536","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Connie Winther","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3992,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-16 14:38:46 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-16 14:38:46 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--674","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Matthew Garsia","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3994,"title":"Plan Partenariat de recherche Séparation parentale, recomposition familiale","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-16 15:49:02 UTC","updated_at":"2016-12-19 16:44:04 UTC","slug":"plan-partenariat-de-recherche-separation-parentale-recomposition-familiale","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"895-2016-1022","identifier":"Partenariat Séparation","description":"Ce projet s'inscrit dans le programme Subvention de partenariat du CRSH et rassemble 27 chercheurs provenant de 12 universités différentes et 18 organismes partenaires. Il s'intéresse à l'expérience de la séparation parentale et de la recomposition familiale dans la société québécoise. Cinq grands objectifs sont poursuivis: \r\n1) Comprendre, dans une perspective longitudinale, les trajectoires et l’expérience des adultes et des enfants qui vivent une séparation parentale ou une recomposition familiale sur le plan des dynamiques familiales et des impacts sur les membres de la famille, de même que sur le plan de l'utilisation des services sociaux et juridiques;\r\n2) Cerner les enjeux particuliers concernant les familles séparées ou recomposées sur le plan du droit de la famille et des politiques publiques;\r\n3) Analyser la variation et l’évolution de ces phénomènes selon le genre et les caractéristiques sociodémographiques; \r\n4) Accroître l’accessibilité à des données de qualité sur la thématique des familles séparées et recomposées pour la communauté scientifique, les milieux d’éducation, de pratique, de planification ainsi que le grand public; \r\n5) Renforcer l’appropriation des connaissances par les organismes partenaires, afin d’améliorer les politiques, les programmes et les services.\r\nPour atteindre ces objectifs, une enquête quantitative longitudinale à trois temps de mesure et cinq enquêtes qualitatives seront réalisées. ","principal_investigator":"Marie-Christine Saint-Jacques","principal_investigator_identifier":"MCSJ","data_contact":"418-656-2131 poste 4721, caroline.robitaille@jefar.ulaval.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":3995,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2016-11-16 18:22:33 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-16 18:22:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--216","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Eugene Barsky","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3996,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2016-11-16 18:28:15 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-16 18:28:15 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--217","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Water Partners","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3997,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-16 19:03:52 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-16 19:03:52 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--677","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Susan Powelson","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3998,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2016-11-16 20:52:21 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-16 20:52:21 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--218","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sean Shang","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":3999,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-16 21:25:48 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-16 21:25:48 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--678","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Deinera Exner-Cortens","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4001,"title":"Words in the World Partnered Research Training Initiative Data Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-17 14:55:40 UTC","updated_at":"2017-01-09 17:23:14 UTC","slug":"words-in-the-world-partnered-research-training-initiative-data-management-plan","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"895-2016-1008","identifier":"","description":"The overall goal of the Words in the World Partnered Research Training Initiative is to advance the development of the next generation of research leaders through partnered training and collaborative knowledge creation and mobilization. The research in this project is  in the field of psycholinguistics. This is a transdisciplinary field that combines insights from linguistics, psychology, and neuroscience.  The data obtained in the project will  be based primarily on experiments that investigate how people process words during language comprehension and production.","principal_investigator":"Gary Libben","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"1-905-688-5550, ext. 6240; email: glibben@brocku.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4002,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2016-11-17 22:06:43 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-17 22:06:51 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--220","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4003,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-18 13:40:07 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-18 13:40:07 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--680","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"yeni liang","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4008,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-18 19:28:33 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-18 19:28:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--682","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"E W","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4009,"title":"MLIS Census Review ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-18 22:56:15 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-22 20:26:47 UTC","slug":"mlis-census-review","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"250380164","description":"The University of Western Ontario, boasts that the MLIS program is known to be “one of the best programs of its kind” (2016). Known as a professional academic program, my team was interested in deepening our understanding of MLIS gradate students professional and educational background. Specifically, we had focused our questionnaire on MLIS students past education level, area of study, library experience and geographical location. My research team wanted to explore the correlation between particular fields of undergraduate studies, previous professional experience and the MLIS program.  ","principal_investigator":"Brittney Smith","principal_investigator_identifier":"250380164","data_contact":"bsmith86@uwo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4010,"title":"Study on the audiovisual content viewing habits of Canadians in 2014","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-18 23:24:01 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-19 19:11:30 UTC","slug":"study-on-the-audiovisual-content-viewing-habits-of-canadians-in-2014","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This study surveyed 3078 Canadians over the age of 15 in order to gain information on their audiovisual content viewing habits. The study aimed to address the viewing habits of Canadians in regards to feature films and television series as well as the trends that are emerging in this industry; what Canadians like and prefer when it comes to feature films; and finally, what Canadians know about the movie business and how they perceive the Canadian film industry.\r\n\r\nThe data were collected in order to analyze film viewing trends in Canada and to ultimately publish an analysis of these findings. This publication will help inform those in the film industry about the preferences and perspectives of Canadian film viewers.","principal_investigator":"Telefilm Canada","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4011,"title":"Amateur Movie Database","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-18 23:43:10 UTC","updated_at":"2016-12-21 04:42:08 UTC","slug":"amateur-movie-database","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"10010353","identifier":"435-2015-0970","description":"This project produces a research tool in the form of a database over twelve hundred award-winning amateur films and filmmakers (titles/names and metadata) between 1928 and 1971. The project will facilitate scholarship and film preservation efforts and generate new scholarship and critical analysis about this robust world of non-commercial film production and circulation. The database will be posted on a publicly accessible website. ","principal_investigator":"Charles Tepperman","principal_investigator_identifier":"10008275","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4012,"title":"Blogging through breast cancer: Sentiment Analysis.","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-19 23:00:53 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-21 02:44:28 UTC","slug":"blogging-through-breast-cancer-sentiment-analysis","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Blogging through breast cancer: Sentiment Analysis. Is focus in answer the main question of this paper \"How young women have turned to illness blogs to describe their lived experience with cancer and how can sentiment change in a cancer survivor?\"\r\n\r\nObjective:\r\nTo gain a unique perspective of the experiences of young women with cancer (age 20–39 years at diagnosis) through  sentiment analysis of their online illness blogs.\r\n","principal_investigator":"Olga Gonzalez","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4013,"title":"Hillary Clinton's emails released August 31, 2016 (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-20 00:30:23 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-21 05:09:17 UTC","slug":"hillary-clinton-s-emails-released-august-31-2016-university-of-alberta-template","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This research project analyzes the relationship that Hillary Clinton has had with her correspondences through email. It aims to understand the solidity of network relationships that were maintained between Hillary and the contact individuals appearing in her leaked emails. In addition, the project aims to render explicit the nature of the topics of the held conversations. The ultimate goal is to study the idea of information sharing and that of the online behaviour of a high profile politician, and this in the 21st century.","principal_investigator":"Maryse Kiese","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4014,"title":"Project Plan. Big Data final paper","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-20 00:46:16 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 20:10:42 UTC","slug":"project-plan-big-data-final-paper","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Data management plan for final project for HUCO 617 Big Data, Fall 2016.","principal_investigator":"Sergii Gorbachov","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4015,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2016-11-20 03:01:38 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 03:01:38 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--222","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Juan Chen","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4016,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-20 06:52:16 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 06:52:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--540","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Juan Chen","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4017,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-20 06:54:26 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 06:54:26 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--686","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Juan Chen","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4018,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-20 16:57:09 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 16:57:09 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--687","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Joseph Deveau","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4019,"title":"HuCo 617: Big Data Project","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-20 19:27:10 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 19:29:40 UTC","slug":"huco-617-big-data-project","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"1239824","description":"An examination of SID Today, the internal newsletter of the NSA, to understand how spies discuss the growth of data. ","principal_investigator":"Kaitlyn Grant","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4020,"title":"Using Free Web Resources as Music History Teaching Materials","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-20 20:36:19 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-25 15:45:58 UTC","slug":"using-free-web-resources-as-music-history-teaching-materials","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"99999","description":"This study involves surveying and interviewing music history professionals as to how they use--or might use--existing, freely-available, music history recordings, videos, images, and readings. It is Part 1 of a two-part Guided Research Project at Western University, undertaken by MLIS student Durrell Bowman (PhD in Musicology) and supervised by Dr. Lynne McKechnie.\r\n\r\nThe study's main research question is:\r\n“How do—and how might—music history instructors use freely-available, web-based recordings, videos, images, readings, and scores as their students’ study materials?”\r\n\r\nMore specific ways of addressing certain issues in the research question involve the following, clarifying questions:\r\n     •\"Do representative music history instructors use free, internet resources in courses or are they considering using such resources in the near future?\"\r\n     •\"What combination of recordings, videos, images, readings, and scores do they use?\"\r\n     •\"What are the real or perceived copyright implications concerning fair dealing / fair use?\"\r\n     •\"Would a portal of consolidated music history resources be of use to different types of instructors and their students?\"\r\n\r\nThe data collected will derive from an anonymous, 12-question, quantitative, online (SurveyMonkey) survey made available to at least forty music history faculty members, instructors, and related librarians in music programs at five universities in south-central Ontario: Western, Waterloo, Wilfrid Laurier, Toronto, and York. The survey data about demographics and rating certain relevant web resources (from at least twenty respondents) will be analyzed for frequencies (teaching areas, use of YouTube, etc.) and summarized visually and in other ways. Certain survey materials may need to be anonymized and/or de-individualized in the publicly-available version of the data.\r\n\r\nSurvey respondents may also choose to participate in a qualitative interview (over Skype or telephone, or possibly in-person) in order to discuss relevant issues further, based on a schedule of nine interview questions related to the ratings portion of the anonymous survey. The interview data (from at least five of the survey participants) will be transcribed and coded for emergent themes. The survey data is anonymous, and certain interview data will be anonymized and/or de-individualized before being made publicly available.\r\n\r\nThe point of the study is to understand how professionals use existing web resources as music history teaching materials, as well as how they might wish to do so in the future. I will be building a website to explore the possibilities for the latter by consolidating useful materials as Part 2 of this Guided Research Project in Summer 2017. The website for that aspect of the project is provisionally called Music History Resources Library (MHRL).","principal_investigator":"Durrell Bowman","principal_investigator_identifier":"88888","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4021,"title":"Canadians’ Attitudes Towards the Truth and Reconciliation Commission","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-20 21:37:02 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-24 01:23:08 UTC","slug":"canadians-attitudes-towards-the-truth-and-reconciliation-commission","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Description","principal_investigator":"Caroline Taylor","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"519-671-8417, ctaylo94@uwo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4022,"title":"LIS9374-CFL","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-20 23:56:58 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-20 23:58:37 UTC","slug":"lis9374-cfl","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"E W","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4023,"title":"HUCO 617 Project Plan","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-21 04:33:02 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-21 05:47:37 UTC","slug":"huco-617-project-plan","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"A comparison between the Malaysian and Chinese mainstream online news portals coverage on the MH370 disappearance.\r\n\r\nResearch Questions :\r\n1. How the news portals differed and were similar in their reporting in terms of language?\r\n2. Were the news portals trying to portray a positive, negative or balanced/fair side of the incident?\r\n3. How people reacted to it: positively or negatively?\r\n\r\nPurpose: To establish how the news portals in both countries have compared in their respective coverage of the crisis issue.\r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Lovania Goorimoorthee","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4024,"title":"Research Data Management Needs & Practices of Researchers in the Faculties of Engineering & Science at the University of Waterloo","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-21 05:10:56 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-25 06:13:11 UTC","slug":"research-data-management-needs-practices-of-researchers-in-the-faculties-of-engineering-science-at-the-university-of-waterloo","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Research data management (RDM) is becoming an increasingly important aspect of the academic research and publication cycle in Canada, in light of directives outlined by national research funding agencies. This project aims to query University of Waterloo faculty members about their current RDM views and practices, so that librarians can ascertain what the RDM needs are of the university's research community. With this information, it will be possible to determine what RDM services the library could offer, so as to more effectively serve patrons.","principal_investigator":"Dave Gall","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"dgall3@uwo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4026,"title":"Type Series of Roman Pottery from Corbridge Roman History Museum","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-21 13:57:34 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-24 17:49:29 UTC","slug":"type-series-of-roman-pottery-from-corbridge-roman-history-museum","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"333","identifier":"llawlis","description":"Type series of ancient Roman Pottery found at Corbridge, England. This data is collected to help researchers understand life in antiquity. The project was completed to understand life at Corbridge and provide insight into how this military town helped support the Roman Empire. ","principal_investigator":"Lisa Lawlis","principal_investigator_identifier":"Lisa Lawlis","data_contact":"lisalawlis3@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":4030,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2016-11-21 16:15:11 UTC","updated_at":"2016-12-13 20:04:53 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--543","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"1473676","description":"My research will be focused on the Madison high school shootings where a 14 year old male student shot and injured four other students. Questions I will attempt to answer include, what sentiments do politicians of both the democratic and republican parties say about incidents like this, what are some concerned celebrities saying, and finalize, what sentiments and thoughts are being expressed by survived victims. \r\n\r\nMajority of this work will be based on comparisons of thoughts, and sentiments.\r\n\r\nTo answer these questions, Big Data will be used and it will be obtained solely from the internet with tools like python program language. subsequent analysis will be done using python programming language and Voyant - a web-based text reading and analysis environment. Specially, I will resort to internet archives like Factiva for my data. ","principal_investigator":"Elliot Damasah","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"+1 647 876 7255 and damasah@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4031,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-21 16:39:29 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-25 20:30:41 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--695","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"250810501","description":"","principal_investigator":"Jennifer Roy","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"jroy63@uwo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4032,"title":"Jessica Mole DMP (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-21 17:40:53 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-24 22:30:08 UTC","slug":"jessica-mole-dmp-portage-template","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"Personal project; no number available","identifier":"Personal project; no ID available","description":"The purpose of this project was to compare two healthcare databases - the Nursing & Allied Health Source (NAHS) and the Cumulative Index to Nursing and Allied Health Literature (CINAHL). Due to the similarities between the two databases, the focus of this study was to investigate and compare their respective coverage. \r\nThe research questions addressed were the following: If only one database could (hypothetically) be purchased, which one should it be and why? Could/should we keep both?\r\nComparisons of similar subject databases help a library to make decisions on where to allocate funds based on how appropriate a database is for a specific library, which is what this project sought to accomplish.","principal_investigator":"Jessica Mole","principal_investigator_identifier":"Personal project; no ID available","data_contact":"cell number: 289-308-7247; email: jmole@uwo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4033,"title":"Outcome Based Measurement at Stratford Public Library","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-21 19:08:46 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-21 19:17:23 UTC","slug":"outcome-based-measurement-at-stratford-public-library","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"11-2016","identifier":"11-2016","description":"Stratford Public Library is researching the outcomes of its library services and programmes to help measure its impact and value in the community.  The research involved collecting the comments and stories of library service users, library programme participants and community members in response to the short term, medium term and long term impact of library services or programmes.  This data will be used to assist with library planning, strategic directions and advocacy.","principal_investigator":"Merley Wheaton","principal_investigator_identifier":"www.stratford.library.on.ca","data_contact":"Merley Wheaton","funder_name":null},{"id":4034,"title":"Female Let's Player YouTube","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2016-11-21 19:52:32 UTC","updated_at":"2016-11-21 19:54:24 UTC","slug":"female-let-s-player-youtube","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier"