"2017-02-17 15:53:07 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-17 15:53:07 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--246","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Logan Donaldson","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4293,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-02-17 15:54:03 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-17 15:55:03 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--854","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Judy Senecal","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4294,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-02-17 19:11:49 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-17 19:11:49 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--855","organisation_id":27,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jessica Leslie","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4295,"title":"DIssertation: B4P","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-02-20 18:02:50 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-20 18:16:31 UTC","slug":"dissertation-b4p","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"My research has two goals. The first is methodological: to determine whether using a different methodological approach rooted in complex systems theory can provide a “theoretically progressive” alternative  to the conventional social science methodological paradigm, to the extent that it can overcome the three challenges identified above. To do so, my research seeks to apply complex systems methods to examine in-depth the governance systems and social interactions surrounding two mine sites in Guatemala as plausibility probes of “most likely” cases: the Marlin I mine (owned by Goldcorp) and the Cerro Blanco mine (owned by Bluestone Resouces). The second is substantive: to determine whether this alternative methodological approach can uncover novel and “policy relevant” insights --both theoretical, empirical--that could help advance debates regarding “Business for Peace.” \r\n\r\nMy research asks the following questions: \r\n\r\nDoes applying complex systems theory and method in an examination of the two cases in Guatemala: \r\nA.\tIdentify novel policy-relevant factors or considerations that conventional research methods have not identified? \r\nB.\tIdentify policy-relevant connections and linkages among factors (novel or previously identified in the literature) that conventional research methods have not identified?\r\nC.\tCapture policy-relevant dynamics that conventional research methods have not identified?\r\nD.\tOffer a significantly different, yet policy-relevant, conclusion or explanation about how mining activities impact and are impacted by peacebuilding?  ","principal_investigator":"aviva silburt","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4296,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-02-20 19:32:26 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-20 19:32:26 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--90","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4297,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-02-20 19:35:44 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-20 19:35:44 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--91","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4298,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-02-20 19:35:45 UTC","updated_at":"2017-02-20 19:35:45 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--92","organisation_id":null,"grant_numbe