ier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4512,"title":"Genre Characterization of the Oxford English Dictionary 2nd edition","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-05-09 17:01:49 UTC","updated_at":"2017-05-10 14:51:12 UTC","slug":"genre-characterization-of-the-oxford-english-dictionary-2nd-edition","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"20563145","description":"This research project is an analysis of a data set of the Oxford English Dictionary 2nd edition as coded at the University of Waterloo with permission from Oxford University Press. The purpose of the research is to use a bottom up approach to genre classification, in order to gain clarity about genre theory in practice of citation evidence in OED2. Using the mark-up file of OED2, the process involves assigning presence/absence of a fixed number of \"genre attributes\" that any given text can feature. After characterizing the works cited in OED2 in a variety of ways using relevant research in genre auto-classification and genre theory, data visualization methods are explored in order to further analysis of textual genre in OED2. ","principal_investigator":"Danielle Griffin","principal_investigator_identifier":"Danielle Griffin","data_contact":"dbgriffi@edu.uwaterloo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":4513,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-05-10 19:29:53 UTC","updated_at":"2017-05-10 19:29:53 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1000","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4514,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-05-11 18:28:08 UTC","updated_at":"2017-05-11 18:28:08 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1001","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Lindsay O'Donnell","principal_investigator_