 Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-07-31 14:02:10 UTC","updated_at":"2017-07-31 14:02:10 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1201","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Peter Webster","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4848,"title":"IMPACTS: Collaborations to Address Sexual Violence on Campus","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-01 13:37:58 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-01 20:10:19 UTC","slug":"impacts-collaborations-to-address-sexual-violence-on-campus","organisation_id":13,"grant_number":"895-2016-1026","identifier":"","description":"Our multidisciplinary Partnership comprises 14 multi-sector Partners, 23 Co- Applicants, 13 Collaborators, 9 Partner universities and faculties (Partners) and McGill as host institution, bringing diverse academic, professional and community-based expertise together to tackle rape culture in universities. Our overarching goal is to unearth, dismantle and prevent rape culture within universities, and ultimately in society, through evidence-based research that will inform sustainable curriculum and policy change. Our team is well positioned to shift the focus from commonly applied reactive solutions to identify proactive ways to inform the current policy vacuum, through preventive and legally defensible policy responses. These will, in turn, support educational practices that engage students in safe dialogues about this complex social phenomenon. Our research over the 7-year term of the Partnership will result in informed and equitable university policies, as well as innovative, student-relevant curricula. Our strategic methodologies will have lasting impacts within and beyond universities as Partners disseminate research from the project into their respective fields and students mobilize knowledge to create a cultural shift in how rape culture is understood and addressed in society. Unlike current efforts that occur in isolation, this Partnership is the first of its kind to address, dismantle and prevent rape culture by means of a systemic partnered solution between the fields of law, education, arts and popular culture (Arts) and news and social media (Media).","principal_investigator":"Shaheen Shariff","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4849,"title":"Effect of Training Load on Performance","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2017-08-01 18:39:19 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-01 18:40:32 UTC","slug":"effect-of-training-load-on-performance","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Robert Poehling","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"bpoehling@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":4850,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-02 15:11:37 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-02 15:11:37 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1204","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4852,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-02 17:11:44 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-02 17:11:44 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1206","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Wendy Merkley","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4857,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-03 17:19:18 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-03 17:19:18 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1207","organisation_id":28,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jake Cameron","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4858,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","