My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-12 21:59:43 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-12 22:01:00 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1210","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":"","identifier":"REB17-1415","description":"Acute coalescent mastoiditis rates","principal_investigator":"Justin Chau","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4869,"title":"Edwards Lab Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-13 13:39:01 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-13 13:40:09 UTC","slug":"edwards-lab-plan","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Trial to see how this works","principal_investigator":"Elizabeth Edwards","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4870,"title":"Voices of energy democracy","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-14 20:50:57 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-06 21:50:06 UTC","slug":"voices-of-energy-democracy","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"1.0 Overview of research\r\n\r\nExtensive support for a transition from fossil fuels to renewable energy systems conceals a wide range of perspectives on the transformative potential of the energy transition. For many, the challenge of energy transition centers on the substitution of fuel types, while others find this conventional framing inadequate, seeing rather an opportunity for more fundamental social transformation through energy transition. As a leading example of this transformational perspective, the movement for energy democracy has emerged in North America over the past decade to advance a vision of a renewable energy future rooted in social and ecological values. The energy democracy agenda seeks an energy future based on collectively-owned and predominantly decentralized renewable energy technologies and guided by principles of democracy, social and environmental justice, and ecological integrity (Weinrub & Giancatarino, 2015). Realizing this transformative energy vision will largely depend upon the capacity for groups working towards energy democracy to influence the direction of transition “from the bottom” through specific innovations and practices.\r\n\r\n2.0 Energy democracy initiatives in northeastern North America \r\n\r\nTransition theory suggests that so-called niche innovations are needed to help shift the trajectory of energy regimes. A likely proposition is that a democratic energy transition will require sufficient experimentation at the niche level in combination with regime-level policy support. This stage of research identifies and learns from the experiences of energy democracy initiatives and the actors who implement them within the region of northeastern North America using a multiple-case study design (Yin, 2012, 2014). The objectives of this research are to 1) describe examples of energy democracy across the selected region 2) refine, clarify or calibrate an ideal-type model of democratic energy transition, and 3) draw out or explain situationally specific reasons why observed outcomes have failed to achieve the ideal (Jackson, 2016). This document is organized along two steps of the research. Step 1 investigates a set of organizations advancing renewable energy transition and their associated transition narratives using qualitative (text) document analysis. Step 2 investigates the perspective and beliefs of representatives from a selection of these organizations using analysis of interviews.\r\n\r\n2.2 Voices of energy democracy in northeastern North America\r\n\r\nSummary TBD\r\n\r\nRQ1: How do practitioners believe that this model of transition can be better enabled (i.e., what factors contribute to or constrain the realization of an energy democracy transition across this region)?\r\n\r\nKeywords: TBD","principal_investigator":"Matthew Burke","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4872,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2017-08-15 18:36:38 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-15 19:48:26 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--604","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Swedenborg Dissertation Project.\r\n\r\nA historical analysis of the religion vs. science debate surrounding the work of the 18th ct. enlightenment thinker Emanuel Swedenborg.\r\n\r\nWhat mechanisms were at play when his scientific and political achievements fell into oblivion?","principal_investigator":"Rita Never","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4873,"title":"ULeth Library Research","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-15 20:16:23 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-15 20:22:33 UTC","slug":"uleth-library-research","organisation_id":28,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Test project to use the DMP Assistant.","principal_investigator":"Sandra Cowan","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":4875,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-15 20:35:48 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-15 20:35:48 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1215","organisation_id":28,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jake Cameron","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4876,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-08-16 18:27:13 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-16 18:27:13 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1216","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Moira Connor","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":4877,"title":"National TAVI Wait-Times Project ","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2017-08-17 20:58:04 UTC","updated_at":"2017-08-17 20:58:43 UTC","slug":"national-tavi-wait-times-project","organisation_id":