hile at the Dana Porter humanities  library on campus and their precautionary behaviour to minimize that perceived risk. \r\n\r\nThe purpose of this research is to understand the general perceptions about the risk of theft and how these beliefs impact the prevalence and type of cautionary measures used. It hopes to contribute to the efforts encouraging such precautionary behaviour by exploring what motivates students to implement these measures. In doing so, the researcher will strive to identify and understand the feelings associated with student perception of this particular risk. The research objective is thus to produce findings to inform and improve the effectiveness of current theft awareness prevention programs.\r\n\r\nThe following central question serves as a guide for the direction of the research: “What is the relationship between the risk of theft at the University of Waterloo (UW) Dana Porter (DP) library and the precautionary measures students take?” This overarching question is broken into the following research questions to help provide a more in-depth understanding of the primary relationship being explored. \r\n(1) How do students at UW perceive the safety of their valuables from theft when they are at the DP library?\r\n(2) What factors influence how students at UW perceive this risk? \r\n(3) What types of behavioural measures are most commonly used by students?\r\n(4) How do these measures affect the students’ perception of the risk of theft?\r\n","principal_investigator":"Nicole Schoenberger","principal_investigator_identifier":"I do not have a researcher ID","data_contact":"nschoenb@uwo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":5156,"title":"Mon plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2017-11-02 13:23:15 UTC","updated_at":"2017-11-02 13:23:15 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--3","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_inves