which IL competencies are already covered through other course work, and any gaps that may exist. This holistic approach ensures that instruction is timely, minimizes duplication, and is integrated across the curriculum.\r\n\r\nWe wish to investigate how this approach could be used not only to design and place IL sessions throughout a degree program, but how this process is perceived by faculty, and if it could be used as a tool to build collaborative library-faculty relationships. We believe this work will provide a foundation to explore faculty perceptions of the library, librarians, and library-led IL instruction, and can inform future research into building productive, collaborative relationships where librarians and faculty view each other as equal partners in IL instruction.","principal_investigator":"Sajni Lacey","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5293,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2017-12-08 23:01:12 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-08 23:01:12 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--636","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Margaret Law","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5294,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2017-12-09 05:37:05 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-09 05:37:05 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--637","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sajad Soleymani Yazdi","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5295,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2017-12-09 05:39:14 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-09 05:39:14 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--638","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifie