work differently and to provide a springboard for their many varied research questions.","principal_investigator":"Marie Carriere","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"780-492-9505, carriere@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":5301,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-11 20:24:37 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-11 20:24:37 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1484","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Shawn Fraser","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5303,"title":"Digital Humanities Pilot","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-12 20:51:22 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-12 20:54:49 UTC","slug":"digital-humanities-pilot","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":"","identifier":"Queens-2017-12-12","description":"The Diniacopoulos Collection Virtual Exhibit is a collaborative project to create an interactive and informative online exhibit of archaeological artefacts. The purpose of the project is to showcase 3D models of the artefacts as digital assets.","principal_investigator":"Meghan Goodchild","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5304,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-13 02:31:49 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-13 02:31:49 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1487","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Adriana Lopez","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5305,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-13 21:11:51 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-13 21:11:51 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1488","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jeremy Geelen","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5306,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-14 23:40:34 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-14 23:40:34 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1489","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Berenica Vejvoda","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5307,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-15 20:46:36 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-15 20:46:36 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1490","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jenaya Webb","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5308,"title":"My plan (C-EBLIP Basic Template: Prototype)","dmptemplate_id":21,"created_at":"2017-12-15 20:58:28 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-15 20:58:28 UTC","slug":"my-plan-c-eblip-basic-template-prototype--5","organisation_id":17,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Li Zhang","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5309,"title":"\"Beasts to Bed, Wed & Dread: Imagining Men in Folk and Popular Media\"","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2017-12-17 19:56:16 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-17 20:07:29 UTC","slug":"beasts-to-bed-wed-dread-imagining-men-in-folk-and-popular-media","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Examination of contemporary variations and remediations of animal spouse tales (in television, as seen in series such as the Korean drama (K-drama) \"Boys over Flowers\" and History Channel’s \"Vikings,\" and in print in the form of the much-maligned genre of popular romance) and the fan communities which take up these works and create their own products in turn.","principal_investigator":"L Gulcev","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5310,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-19 22:51:38 UTC","updated_at":"2017-12-19 22:51:38 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1491","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Matt Huculak","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":5311,"title":"Plan de gestion des données projet pilote d'archivage d'affiches scientifiques (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-20 15:59:00 UTC","updated_at":"2018-01-05 00:06:41 UTC","slug":"plan-de-gestion-des-donnees-projet-pilote-d-archivage-d-affiches-scientifiques-modele-portage","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"ARC, CDC","description":"Projet pilote initié par l'ARC et le CDC afin d'effectuer l'archivage des affiches scientifiques diffusées dans les colloques de l'ARC, dans le cadre de l'ACFAS, de 2014 à 2017.","principal_investigator":"Isabelle Laplante","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0003-0138-7983","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5312,"title":"SSHRC Insight Development Grant","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-21 13:47:04 UTC","updated_at":"2018-01-04 18:03:13 UTC","slug":"sshrc-insight-development-grant","organisation_id":13,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This research program seeks to shed light on the invisible topic of racism from one’s intimate partner and close others (family and friends) within intercultural couples. Furthermore, this research will investigate the relationship between this intimate racism and each partner’s identity and relationship outcomes. Specifically, this research first intends to identify how racism manifests itself from close others against partners in intercultural couples. Our team will achieve this through qualitative in-person discussion groups that give voice and shape to these overlooked experiences. Second, this research intends to develop a measure of intimate racism for partners in intercultural couples. Third, this research intends to examine the critical role of intimate racism in predicting intercultural couples’ identity conflicts and relationship quality. We will achieve this through a large-scale, quantitative and dyadic study, which will unpack the mutual influence of each partner’s racism experiences to their own and to their partner’s outcomes. Our findings will be disseminated to the psychology research community, therapists, community centres, and the public, where they will contribute to greater sensitivity towards intercultural couples, as well as greater competence in the care they receive.","principal_investigator":"Maya Yampolsky","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5323,"title":"Thesis Data Management Plan (Christopher Bell)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2017-12-30 21:59:10 UTC","updated_at":"2020-01-10 23:04:37 UTC","slug":"thesis-data-management-plan-christopher-bell","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This study will identify stakeholders' views on the causes of, and potential solutions for addressing, municipal infrastructure deficits in Canada, through comparative case studies of the City of Calgary and the City of Edmonton. \r\n\r\nCore research questions are: Why have Calgary and Edmonton large accumulated large infrastructure deficits?\r\nHow are Calgary and Edmonton responding to their infrastructure deficits? What tools are available to Calgary and Edmonton, and by extension to other large Canadian cities, to address their infrastructure deficits?\r\n\r\nKey informant interviews will be conducted to assist with answering the above questions.","principal_investigator":"Mark Seasons","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Christopher Bell, 403-616-1360, cgbell@uwaterloo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":5324,"title":"My plan (University of British Col