ptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-04-23 15:32:21 UTC","updated_at":"2018-04-23 15:41:52 UTC","slug":"impact-of-precieved-social-support-for-bereaved-and-non-bereaved-university-students","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This study is correlational in design and will examine the relationship between bereavement, perceived social support and identity formation. Specifically, is there a difference in perceived social support between those that have experienced the death of a family member or friend and those that have not, and what impact does the normativity of the experience of bereavement have on perceived social support? Are there differences in identity formation between these two groups? Are potential differences in identity formation between these groups mediated by perceived social support? In order to answer these questions participants will be recruited from the Psychology Research Experience Pool (PREP) and will be asked to fill out a number of surveys as well as to answer open ended questions about their experiences with bereavement as well as with coming to university. The quantitative measures include measures of the number of life transitions or events they have experienced, the impact of the transition or event that they felt was most significant, measures of the degree to which they feel supported by friends and family, and the degree to which they feel challenged by these relationships. They will also complete a measure of identity consolidation and confusion, measures looking at resiliency, depression, and psychological well-being. ","principal_investigator":"Katherine Ottley","principal_investigator_identifier":"175806260","data_contact":"Katherine Ottley, ottl6260@mylaurier.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":5731,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-04-23 22:37:10 UTC","updated_at":"2018-04-23 22:37:10 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1770","organisation_id":8,"grant_n