-assist-device","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"JBI14534","description":"The aim of this review is to synthesize the best available evidence related to the impact of care giving from the perspective of caregivers/support persons for individuals living with a left ventricular assist device (LVAD). Specifically, the review question is “What are the experiences of adult caregivers/support persons for individuals living with a LVAD in the community?\r\nThis review will consider studies that include caregivers/support persons who are over the age of 18 years who are caring for persons living with a LVAD in the community irrespective of the relationship and include any type of LVAD and indication for the LVAD implant.\r\nThe phenomenon of interest for this review is the experiences, insights, feelings and perceptions of caregivers/support persons about their role as caregivers for an individual living with a LVAD in the community.\r\nThis review will consider studies that investigate the personal impact of caring for an individual with a LVAD in the community from the caregivers’ perspectives including studies that investigate the perceptions, experiences, or beliefs of caregivers/support persons related to their role as caregivers, the perspectives of the consequences for caring for an individual with an LVAD and perceived coping strategies in caring for individuals living with a LVAD. This review will consider studies that focus on qualitative data, surveys that have a qualitative component as well as the grey literature.","principal_investigator":"Lorraine Avery; Andrea Szwajcer; Bev Temple; Jo-Ann Sawatzky","principal_investigator_identifier":"Scopus Author ID: 23466203400","data_contact":"lavery@sbgh.mb.ca; 204-258-1286","funder_name":null},{"id":5760,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2018-05-02 17:47:13 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-02 17:47:13 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-br