nadian Urban Environmental Health Research Consortium (studying how where you live affects your health)","principal_investigator":"Eleanor Setton","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5815,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-05-16 17:39:39 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-16 17:41:32 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1809","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"CIMP 191","identifier":"","description":"Project Title: Watching the Land: Knowing the Impacts of Change\r\n\r\nProject Abstract:  To establish a community-based monitoring program with the main focus being the collection and analysis of TK environmental information that can inform regulatory and environmental management decisions being made by KFN and other agencies.  The overall goal of the project is to track the health of the environment and changes to the environment over time based on a set of pre-determined TK parameters through field-based monitoring. The project will also build capacity within the community by developing the technical skills required of community members to document TK information in a reliable and credible manner for decision making purposes and mentoring youth to monitor the environment from a TK perspective.    \r\n","principal_investigator":"Peter Redvers","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Patrick Riley (4039684980)","funder_name":null},{"id":5816,"title":"Boreal caribou habitat selection analysis and mapping to support range planning in the Dehcho,  South Slave and North Slave regions","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-05-16 22:24:05 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-16 22:32:57 UTC","slug":"boreal-caribou-habitat-selection-analysis-and-mapping-to-support-range-planning-in-the-dehcho-south-slave-and-north-slave-regions","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"CIMP202","identifier":"CIMP202","description":"This project will evaluate boreal caribou habitat selection as a function of time since fire, pre-fire and post-fire land cover type, unburned residuals within fire perimeters, and burn severity.  Resource selection functions (RSF) will be used to compare landscape attributes at observed and random caribou collar locations within and outside fire perimeters to evaluate seasonal habitat selection.  RSF models will in turn be used map the relative probability that caribou will select areas of the landscape according to fire attributes and other landscape covariates, including extrapolation to areas where no collar data is available.  This will provide maps of relative habitat importance for boreal caribou across the southern half of the NT1 range that can be used by NWT decision makers to help delineate areas in range plans where careful management of caribou habitat should be prioritized. ","principal_investigator":"James  Hodson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"james_hodson@gov.nt.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":5817,"title":"DHatGuelph 2018 test","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-05-17 13:11:16 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-17 13:14:33 UTC","slug":"dhatguelph-2018-test","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"test_plan","principal_investigator":"Nicholas Field","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5818,"title":"DH@Guelph","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-05-17 13:12:59 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-17 13:14:36 UTC","slug":"dh-guelph","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Test","principal_investigator":"Sarah Whitwell","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":5820,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-05-17 13:13:24 UTC","updated_at":"2018-05-17 13:14:44 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1814","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Test.","principal_investigator":"Samantha Rife","principal_inv