y","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6049,"title":"Open Badges for demonstrating Open Access compliance: A pilot project","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-07-31 19:17:09 UTC","updated_at":"2018-07-31 21:15:50 UTC","slug":"open-badges-for-demonstrating-open-access-compliance-a-pilot-project--2","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"A planned pilot project to develop and test Open Badges.  Open Badges will recognize researchers’ compliance with the Tri-Agency Open Access Policy on Publications in a streamlined, visually-appealing manner. An open badge will be developed and then integrated with DSpace 5.5.  The project will allow relevant authors to demonstrate their compliance with the Policy in a portable, open, and attractive fashion, and may increase the perceived value of PRISM, our institutional repository.\r\n\r\nThe volume of research outputs deposited into PRISM will be compared to deposits in similar institutional repositories during the same time period to assess whether the badges were effective as an incentive.","principal_investigator":"Christie Hurell","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6052,"title":"Mon plan (Université de Montréal (FR))","dmptemplate_id":42,"created_at":"2018-07-31 21:05:40 UTC","updated_at":"2018-07-31 21:05:40 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-universite-de-montreal-fr","organisation_id":32,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Marie-Hélène Vézina","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6053,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-08-01 03:04:25 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-01 03:04:25 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1967","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sina Keshvadi","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6054,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2018-08-01 14:42:45 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-01 14:42:45 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--678","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Tamara  arnold","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6055,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-08-01 15:15:30 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-01 15:15:30 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1968","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Angela Di Nello","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6056,"title":"vAFC Phase 3","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2018-08-01 17:02:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-21 22:45:50 UTC","slug":"vafc-phase-3","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"PG 62R74285","identifier":"","description":"Atrial fibrillation (AF) is a serious, unpredictable, chronic condition with incidence rates that rapidly increase with advancing age. Older adults living in rural communities are at a disadvantage compared to their urban counterparts, since they often have to travel to access specialists and targeted support services. A virtually enhanced AF clinic may offer a viable approach to care for rural populations, but currently no virtual AF models exist. This study will compare virtually delivered specialty AF clinic care with usual onsite AF clinic care.\r\nThe study will use a randomized controlled trial in a nested group design. The study will compare virtually delivered AF clinic care with usual AF clinic care. The control group will receive usual follow up care onsite at the AF clinic, the intervention group will receive the Virtually Enhanced AF Clinic (vAFC). The vAFC will include follow-up  appointments with the AF clinic delivered using telehealth and access to an educational AF website. A total of 40-60 patients, 20-30 allocated to each group, will be recruited from an urban-based AF Clinic. Participants will include first time AF clinic patients who live in rural communities. Data will be collected at baseline, 3 months, and 6 months. Primary outcomes include: AF quality of life and AF knowledge; secondary outcomes include: healthcare utilization, stroke risk, bleeding risk, perceived stress, BMI, physical activity, and lifestyle behaviors. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Kathy Rush","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Lindsay Burton, 250-807-8652, l.burton@ubc.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":6057,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-08-01 19:06:48 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-01 19:06:48 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1969","organisation_id":14,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Minglu Wang","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6058,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-08-01 20:32:31 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-01 20:32:31 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1970","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Crystal Yin","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6059,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-08-01 20:33:55 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-01 20:33:55 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--1971","organisation_id":14,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Crystal Yin","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6060,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-08-02 12:31:01 UTC","updated_at":"2018-08-02 1