:"portage-dmp-exemplar-mixed-methods","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"12345","identifier":"8675309","description":"This is a fictional exemplar data management plan focusing on mixed methods research (survey & interviews/focus groups). This exemplar DMP was developed in February 2020 by James Doiron (Co-chair, Portage DMP Expert Group) for educational and guidance purposes. For these purposes, the premise of the project being described is that the study topic of interest is not sensitive in nature, and that participants are consenting for their de-identified information (data) to be deposited for long-term preservation, discoverability, and open access.","principal_investigator":"James Doiron","principal_investigator_identifier":"9997","data_contact":"James Doiron (jdoiron@ualberta.ca)","funder_name":null},{"id":6308,"title":"Identifying Journals and Topics Instrumental to Librarian Practitioner Professional Practice and Development","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-09-13 18:25:57 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-21 16:38:51 UTC","slug":"identifying-journals-and-topics-instrumental-to-librarian-practitioner-professional-practice-and-development","organisation_id":38,"grant_number":"PSSHRC_UofS","identifier":"","description":"The overall project examines which library and information science (LIS) journals/sources practitioners rely on and who publishes in them in order to answer the question: Do practitioners rely more on research produced by practitioners or research produced by academics? Phase 1—conducted in autumn 2016— involved designing and administering a pilot survey of Saskatchewan librarian practitioners to identify the top journals that these practitioners rely on to support their professional practice and development, to compile a top 20 list, and to do a pilot of the survey questions and data analysis methods before expanding the survey to a wider population.\r\n\r\nPhase 2 has two primary objectives: \r\n1) Data analysis examining two criteria; the authorship of research articles in the identified top 20 journals and a content analysis of the titles in order to investigate what kinds of research are published in these identified journal.\r\n\r\n2) Refinement of the survey tool (used in Phase 1) based on feedback from participants in the pilot study. ","principal_investigator":"Jaclyn McLean","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3028-0325","data_contact":"306.966.7462; jaclyn.mclean@usask.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":6309,"title":"My DMP MSc ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-09-13 23:08:08 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-13 23:09:08 UTC","slug":"my-dmp-msc","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Ainsley Fraser","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6310,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-09-13 23:08:16 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-13 23:08:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2071","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Michael Livingston","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6311,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-09-13 23:08:23 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-13 23:08:23 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2072","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Emily May","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6313,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-09-13 23:09:22 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-13 23:09:22 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2074","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Lise van der Merwe","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name"