:null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Dawn Davidson","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6391,"title":"Collaborative water services between First Nations and municipalities in Ontario","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-09-25 19:36:24 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-25 19:58:59 UTC","slug":"collaborative-water-services-between-first-nations-and-municipalities-in-ontario","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"435-2018-0060","identifier":"","description":"On many First Nations’ reserves across Canada, lack of safe drinking water is a chronic problem. Researchers at the University of Guelph and Western University have received a SSHRC Insight Grant to study collaborative water arrangements between First Nations and municipalities in Ontario. This five-year $371,300 project is an interdisciplinary effort, involving a mix of quantitative and qualitative methods – including statistical analysis, and in-depth case studies. The central aim of this project is to identify the potential scope for water sharing in the Province, and factors influencing communities to choose to engage, or not engage, in these exchanges. \r\n\r\nThis dataset is one output of the quantitative portion of this research. It documents the extent and nature of water sharing between water systems on Ontario reserves and municipalities, and characterizes the communities containing these water systems. ","principal_investigator":"Brady Deaton","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"bdeaton@uoguelph.ca, 519-824-4120 ext. 52765","funder_name":null},{"id":6392,"title":"FHB Winter 2019","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-09-25 19:43:58 UTC","updated_at":"2018-09-25 19:47:17 UTC","slug":"fhb-winter-2019","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"We screen winter lines for FHB in the filed in the Elora Research Station. Inoculation will be done during June and data collection in July","p