o ORCID","data_contact":"Name, telephone and email","funder_name":null},{"id":6633,"title":"Unconscious Racial Biases Written within Library Acquisition Policies","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-11-05 20:14:16 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-06 21:54:10 UTC","slug":"unconscious-racial-biases-written-within-library-acquisition-policies","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Diversity in public libraries is focused on the consistent integration of people from ethnic minorities into the library community as patrons. However, despite this idea of diversity for public libraries, the fact of the matter is libraries ethnic minorities are both less likely to visit the library or use its services remotely compared to Caucasians. As a result, libraries cannot maintain their duty of being an inclusive environment but instead remain exclusive. Is the lack of diversity in public library resources, as determined by acquisition polices, the reason for the lack of diversity in public library patrons in Ontario, all of which is due to an unconscious racial bias? This study will aim to determine how acquisition policies may be the root cause for the lack of patron diversity in public libraries. ","principal_investigator":"Selina Long","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6634,"title":"Tranche2vie","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-11-05 21:06:38 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-05 22:08:09 UTC","slug":"tranche2vie","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Déterminants psychologiques et contextuels des habitudes de vie chez des adultes traités pour un trouble dépressif majeur : étude par évaluation écologique instantanée.","principal_investigator":"P.Bernard","principal_investigator_identifier":"bernard.paquito@uqam.ca","data_contact":"P.Bernard","funder_name":null},{"id":6635,"title":"Mapping & Visualizing Victorian Literary Sociability","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-11-