IS data management according to best practices.  GIS data is used in spatial analysis and to create maps in response to the information needs of parliamentarians, analysts and parliamentary committees.\r\n\r\nA central repository ensures that:\r\n\r\nThere is one location for data with one person or team responsible for maintaining it (GIS librarian or GIS librarians).\r\n\r\nOrganized, documented data repository is efficient.\r\n\r\nProvides for easier on-boarding of new analysts if location of data is clear.\r\n\r\nAll members of the GIS team should understand what is in the data repository.\r\n\r\nClear documentation in order to facilitate knowledge transfer to new GIS librarian(s).\r\n","principal_investigator":"Aelvoet, Els; Zahab, Mélanie","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Alton, Michele","funder_name":null},{"id":6656,"title":"Women's Equality Profile","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-11-09 16:43:41 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-09 16:49:08 UTC","slug":"women-s-equality-profile","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The New Brunswick Women's Equality Profile is a compendium of statistical information about New Brunswick women. It contains various statistics covering different aspects of women's lives - population, education and training, health, income and poverty, family responsibilities, labour force, positions of influence, justice and violence - all in one place. \r\nThe Equality Profile is a tool to track women's equality. As we release each edition every second year, we will be able to observe trends over time regarding a variety of aspects pertaining to women in New Brunswick.","principal_investigator":"Kylie Bergfalk","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6657,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-11-09 19:02:09 UTC","updated_at":"2018-11-09 19:02:09 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2246","organisation_id":