scription":"Muti-phase study including\r\n1) Qualitative inquiry of 12-20 parents residing in the region of Thunder Bay, Ontario\r\n2) Parent Collaborator Group meetings occurring approximately 2x/month for 3 months for 1 hr. \r\n3) Survey and interview with PCG members upon project completion.","principal_investigator":"Alison Thompson","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0003-0605-6534","data_contact":"Dr Shannon D Scott, 780-492-1037, ss14@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":6663,"title":"Sample Plan for Social Survey Research","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-11-12 18:18:35 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-10 14:34:36 UTC","slug":"sample-plan-for-social-survey-research","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Sample data management plan","principal_investigator":"Sherri Klassen","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6665,"title":"L'impact du drainage agricole souterrain sur la morphologie des petits cours d'eau.","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2018-11-13 19:02:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-01-14 15:10:51 UTC","slug":"l-impact-du-drainage-agricole-souterrain-sur-la-morphologie-des-petits-cours-d-eau","organisation_id":42,"grant_number":"1234567","identifier":"test","description":"Comparaison entre des bassins-versants avec et sans drainage agricole afin d'évaluer si le drainage souterrain affecte la morphologie des cours d'eau et peut provoquer une érosion accélérée de ces derniers.\r\nDonnées de débit de cours d'eau et d'hydrogrammes de crue, de même que la taille des bassins versants, largeur, profondeur et longueur des cours d'eau. \r\nÉtude exploratoire comportant beaucoup de limitations dû au peu de contrôle sur l'environnement de chaque bassin versant","principal_investigator":"Catherine Leduc","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID 0000-0001-7377-8874","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6666,"title":"Trade, Competitiveness and Blockchain","dmptemplate_id":45,"c