 Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-01-25 16:49:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-25 16:55:41 UTC","slug":"my-plan-uvic-dmp-template--14","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Trans-Atlantic Platform – “Social Innovation”","principal_investigator":"Oliver Schmidtke","principal_investigator_identifier":"Oliver Schmidtke","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6967,"title":"Laboratory Leadership Transition Project","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-01-25 19:28:59 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-25 20:56:29 UTC","slug":"laboratory-leadership-transition-project","organisation_id":40,"grant_number":"","identifier":"RRU MALH-2017 ST","description":"Investigating Change Readiness of Laboratory Leaders in preparation for transitioning to a new provincial governance structure. This qualitative study will include individual interviews and focus group methods. Data collected will not include any personally identifiable information. However, organizational information will be evident.","principal_investigator":"Sheryl Thiessen","principal_investigator_identifier":"sheryl.thiessen@phsa.ca","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6969,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-01-26 18:37:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-26 18:37:48 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--326","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Antoine Boudreau LeBlanc","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6970,"title":"DMP for community-driven research on why H. pylori bacteria cause a disproportionate disease burden in northern Indigenous Canadians","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2019-01-26 20:09:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-05-07 12:57:32 UTC","slug":"dmp-for-community-driven-research-on-why-h-pylori-bacteria-cause-a-disproportionate-disease-burden-in-northern-indigenous-canadians","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"409739","identifier":"","description":"Northern Indigenous communities view H. pylori infection as a health research priority because of its link to stomach cancer, which occurs more frequently in northern Canada than on average across the nation. Compared to southern Canadians, this infection is diagnosed more often in northern Indigenous Canadians, in whom it also causes more severe disease and is more difficult to cure. This proposal was developed in partnership with Northwest Territories (NT) and Yukon (YT) communities that seek research aimed at explaining why this common infection causes a disproportionate health burden in their region. The Canadian North Helicobacter pylori (CANHelp) Working Group conducts community-driven research on H. pylori infection, with projects in 4 NT and 5 YT communities. We propose to conduct a genomic analysis of H. pylori bacteria cultured from stomach biopsies of 274 community project participants. Genomic studies examine an organism’s genome (its full set of genes).\r\n\r\nWe will describe features of genomes of the H. pylori strains that infect residents of\r\nparticipating communities and investigate whether these genomic features determine how H. pylori infection impacts stomach health among participants. Our proposed research aims to: describe genomic features of H. pylori strains and how they are distributed across NT and YT communities; examine the relatedness of H. pylori strains within household, families, and communities; and estimate associations of genomic features with disease severity. \r\n\r\nThe CANHelp Working Group has a unique collection of H. pylori isolated from northern Indigenous communities, along with clinical outcome data. It is one of few population-based collections of H. pylori in the world. Thus, the proposed research has the potential to advance knowledge of H. pylori genomics in human populations while furthering community-driven biomedical research that addresses priorities of Indigenous Canadian communities.","principal_investigator":"Janis Geary","principal_investigator_identifier":"Karen Goodman","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6971,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-01-26 20:12:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-26 20:12:42 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2424","organisation_id":38,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Janis Geary","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6972,"title":"My plan (University of Manitoba )","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2019-01-26 20:17:33 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-26 20:17:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-manitoba--26","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Janis Geary","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6973,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-01-27 15:51:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-27 16:00:30 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2425","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This case study intends to explore teacher perspectives on community engagement efforts within international schools. The case study will interview teachers at the International School of Dakar in Dakar, Senegal. It will address the following research questions:\r\n 1. How do international school teachers in Dakar, Senegal conceptualize the engagement between the international school community and the broader host nation community?\r\n2. How do teachers define meaningful and reciprocal engagement between international school students and host nation school students?\r\n3. What barriers do international school teachers in Dakar, Senegal see to meaningful and reciprocal engagement between international school students and host nation school students?\r\n4. What solutions do teachers propose to establish such meaningful engagement?\r\n5. As a teacher, how do I improve my practice in relation to community engagement efforts?\r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Dr. Frances Helyar","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6974,"title":"OAFIA Test (Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance Template)","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-01-28 14:26:56 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-28 14:34:53 UTC","slug":"oafia-test-ontario-agri-food-innovation-alliance-template","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"654321","identifier":"123456","description":"This projects tests the DMP Assistant Tool","principal_investigator":"My name","principal_investigator_identifier":"78910","data_contact":"lib.research@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":6976,"title":"My plan (Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance Template)","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-01-28 14:44:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-28 14:44:43 UTC","slug":"my-plan-ontario-agri-food-innovation-alliance-template--2","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"libresc","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6977,"title":"Manon Picard","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-01-28 23:40:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-27 16:49:19 UTC","slug":"manon-picard","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Manon Picard","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":6978,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-01-29 00:31:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-01-29 00:31:48 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2427","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":6979,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-