suffrage movement and the many civic groups and organizations that were the primary political outlet for women of the time.\r\n\r\nThis project will create a digital archive of Knightley's collected works to open up these works to new scholars and digital humanities practitioners, and also allow for new distant reading analyses and the creation of new digital scholarly editions of the works that the researchers hope will provide new insights into the relationship between Knightley and other authors of the time.","principal_investigator":"Kristen Allford","principal_investigator_identifier":"??","data_contact":"5555555555, kristenallford@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":7232,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-22 17:48:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 17:48:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2561","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Melissa Cuthill","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7233,"title":"Using Zebrafish as a Model System...","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-03-22 17:48:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 17:51:33 UTC","slug":"using-zebrafish-as-a-model-system","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"12345","description":"Using Zebrafish as a Model System for Studying Motor Axon Guidance & Motoneuron Disease: A Teaching Case for Data Management","principal_investigator":"Matt Kaufhold","principal_investigator_identifier":"abcde","data_contact":"NA","funder_name":null},{"id":7234,"title":"Regeneration of Functional Heart Tissue in Rats","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-03-22 17:49:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 17:55:54 UTC","slug":"regeneration-of-functional-heart-tissue-in-rats--3","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Lucas Damer","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7235,"title":"[Sample] Zebrafish as a Model System for STudying Motor Axon Guidance & Motoneuron Disease","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-03-22 17:50:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 17:59:44 UTC","slug":"sample-zebrafish-as-a-model-system-for-studying-motor-axon-guidance-motoneuron-disease","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Purpose: To research and develop drugs for motorneuron diseases, focusing on Spinal Muscular Atrophy (SMA) and Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS) \r\n\r\nGrants: Multiple NIH grants\r\nResearch support funding: private companies, organizations, families affected","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7236,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-03-22 17:56:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 17:56:03 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--467","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Paula Arasaki","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7237,"title":"Grassland Bird Conservation","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-03-22 17:59:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 18:02:06 UTC","slug":"grassland-bird-conservation","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Research on grassland bird habitat quality. \r\nTo create a tool that could potentially be used to assess the suitability of habitat management sites, and inform  decisions on which sites to attempt to improve, and what parts of the sites would benefit most from management.","principal_investigator":"PhD Students","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7238,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-03-22 18:01:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 18:11:11 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--469","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Findings on grassland bird habitat quality. ","principal_investigator":"Anna Lin","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7239,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-22 19:35:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 19:35:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2562","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Wael Ahmed","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7240,"title":"My plan (Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance Template)","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-03-22 19:37:23 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-22 19:41:35 UTC","slug":"my-plan-ontario-agri-food-innovation-alliance-template--19","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"LAAIR2018-5337","identifier":"","description":"Traditional agriculture uses 70% of the global fresh water supply as compared to hydroponics that only use 10% resolving the world-wide shortage demand for fresh water. However, these systems require large amounts of energy to operate. The challenges associated with high production cost, slim profit margins and the high cost of energy make it imperative to adopt such sustainable and economically viable technologies to maintain profitability. Reducing the total energy use and improving productivity is critical for the sector to expand. In this project, a smart pump that is able to circulate water as well as nutrients in vertical farms using 50-70% less energy will be developed. These smart pumps are operated only by air with no moving parts, no lubrication required, no noise or vibration involved. The detailed design of this smart pumping system, optimization of manufacturing processes and product durability tests will be completed for this technology. These smart pumps will be capable of monitoring and adjusting their operating parameters to adapt to system demand and allow the farm to operate efficiently and improve productivity and profitability as well as troubleshoot potential system problems. A fully functioning pumping system will be tested in real world operational facility operated by Back40 Growers in Burlington as a show case for potential commercialization to the vertical framing industry. ","principal_investigator":"Wael Ahmed","principal_investigator_identifier":"orcid.org/0000-0002-6841-9102","data_contact":"ahmedw@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7241,"title":"Green Data Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-23 19:43:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-23 19:52:17 UTC","slug":"green-data-management-plan","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Viji","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Vijaya Lakshmi","funder_name":null},{"id":7242,"title":"Oral Portfolio","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-23 20:31:59 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-23 20:32:48 UTC","slug":"oral-portfolio","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Wendy Fraser","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7243,"title":"Data Plan: Dr. Green","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-24 23:21:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-04-02 16:27:51 UTC","slug":"data-plan-dr-green","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This project will investigate interdisciplinary primary care teamwork in hospital environments.","principal_investigator":"Dr. Green","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7244,"title":"My plan (UVic DMP Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-03-24 23:26:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-24 23:31:51 UTC","slug":"my-plan-uvic-dmp-template--21","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"In a time of Indigenous Resurgence, my PhD research focuses on the health and well being of Canadian Indigenous Peoples in connection to their interrelationships with culturally important plants. My work is conducted within the context of the Type 2 Diabetes crisis taking place in Indigenous communities across Canada with the prevalence of Type 2 Diabetes being three to five times higher than the general population and diagnosis happening at younger ages. Type 2 Diabetes is a colonial disease. It did not exist pre-contact and is a product of the rapid shift from traditional diet to one rich in processed grains, sugar and unhealthy fats. I will work with two Indigenous Communities in Canada through my doctoral work; Skwxwú7mesh (Squamish) First Nations in British Columbia and Tr’ondëk Hwëch’in First Nations in the Yukon. Drawing on trends and methods from ethnobotany and Indigenous Studies I will answer the following question: 1. How can ethnobotanical research honour, and be guided by, Indigenous Worldview? What methods are the most meaningful and effective for advancing in this direction based on my work with Skwxwú7mesh and Tr’ondëk Hwëch’in First Nations communities? 2. What contributions can community-based research focusing on specific cultural keystone plant species, which have historic and present-day significance as food or medicine, make in addressing the T2D crisis? 3. How can culturally important plants help connect a person’s sense of health (physical, spiritual and emotional) to place? What does this connection between plants, people’s health and place mean to the participants themselves?  These questions emerge from overarching themes and priorities that both partnering communities have expressed in initial discussions and consultation. The results of this study will inform the Skwxwú7mesh (Squamish) and Tr’ondëk Hwëch’in First Nations practices on culturally rooted approaches to health through rebuilding Indigenous plant relationships. The results of this work will provide a framework for other Indigenous communities interested in reconnecting with their traditional plant practices and addressing Type 2 Diabetes in a culturally relevant way. Data is being collected in order to gain insight into how best to approach cultural knowledge renewal in connection to plants from an Indigenous perspective and rooted in an Indigenous worldview.","principal_investigator":"Leigh Joseph","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7245,"title":"Thuthuka","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-25 10:59:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-25 11:01:47 UTC","slug":"thuthuka","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"Thuthuka DMP","description":"Comparative study where genomic data will be generated and compared to transcriptomic data as well as enzymatic assay data and HPLC data will be compared","principal_investigator":"Trudy Jansen","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3434-543X","data_contact":"trudy@sun.ac.za","funder_name":null},{"id":7246,"title":"Integrated pest management Stemphylium leaf blight (Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance Template)","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-03-25 13:40:40 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-25 13:42:52 UTC","slug":"integrated-pest-management-stemphylium-leaf-blight-ontario-agri-food-innovation-alliance-template","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"110-012800-000000-030292","identifier":"UofG2016-2543","description":"","principal_investigator":"Mary Ruth  McDonald","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Mary Ruth McDonald","funder_name":null},{"id":7247,"title":" Management of clubroot on canola and brassica vegetables (Ontario Agri-Food Innovation Alliance Template)","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-03-25 13:43:15 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-25 13:45:40 UTC","slug":"management-of-clubroot-on-canola-and-brassica-vegetables-ontario-agri-food-innovation-alliance-template","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"110-012800-000000-030339","identifier":"UofG2017-2896","description":"","principal_investigator":"Mary Ruth  McDonald","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Mary Ruth McDonald","funder_name":null},{"id":7248,"title":"DMP Plan for RDM Faculty Survey, Dalhousie University","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-25 14:51:41 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-25 14:53:30 UTC","slug":"dmp-plan-for-rdm-faculty-survey-dalhousie-university","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"n/a","identifier":"n/a","description":"The purpose of this study is to survey all ranks of faculty, postdoctoral fellows and graduate students at Dalhousie University to understand their research data management (RDM) and research data sharing practices.\r\n\r\nInformation gathered through the survey will help the Dalhousie University Libraries develop services and educational programs to facilitate data management activities for Dalhousie researchers, and contribute to our understanding of how physical and applied researchers at Dalhousie understand and practice research data management. It will also assist in the development of an institutional strategy for research data management at Dalhousie University.","principal_investigator":"Sarah Stevenson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Erin MacPherson","funder_name":null},{"id":7251,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-25 19:27:06 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-25 19:27:06 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2569","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Stephen Beauregard","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7252,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-03-25 20:56:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-03-25 20:56:07 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2570","organisation_id":24,"gran