 of literary hashtags (e.g., #writing, #twitlit, #poetry, etc.) as a means of identifying this new form of literature. After metadata related to these literary tweets are collected, the users' locations are used to map where the amateur writing community is tweeting their stories. This data is visualized using ArcGIS. \"Mapping Twitter Literature\" primarily focuses upon the use of Anglophone hashtags and looks at Twitter literature produced from 2006 (when Twitter was launched) through the present. The driving research questions are: How can we characterize the kind of writing being produced and disseminated on Twitter? Where is the Twitter writing community? How do these texts circulate, and what does the network of Twitter writers look like? ","principal_investigator":"Christian Howard","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-3835-8003","data_contact":"E: cfh.howard@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":7582,"title":"My Learning Portfolio","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:09:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:25:05 UTC","slug":"my-learning-portfolio","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":" ","description":"","principal_investigator":"Mark Wilson","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID 0000-0002-7037-2200","data_contact":"01 510 629 0115, mark.wilson@wisr.edu, markcorbetttwilson@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":7583,"title":"My plan (UVic DMP Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:10:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:10:37 UTC","slug":"my-plan-uvic-dmp-template--32","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Rachelle Ann Tan","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7584,"title":"Denison Arab American Oral History Project","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:11:23 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:29:47 UTC","slug":"denison-arab-american-oral-history-project","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"Arab/American Oral History Denison","description":"In person home interviews with Arab American Immigrants in Columbus, Ohio. The goal is to filled and preserve the personal feelings of multi generational families living in the United States. To be clear, the goal is not to record responses about general big events, but is to capture the small personal stories that our subjects are willing to share. Not only are we collecting the stories, we are capturing the people behind them. How they talk, their hand gestures, etc. We are collecting the full experience for preservation and use by future researchers.","principal_investigator":"Hannah  Bennett","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"207-598-8699 bennet_h1@denison.edu","funder_name":null},{"id":7585,"title":"MyNDIR (My Norse Digital Image Repository))","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:12:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:17:43 UTC","slug":"myndir-my-norse-digital-image-repository","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Trish Baer","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6952-8976","data_contact":"778-678-1426 trish.uvic@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":7586,"title":"Colonial Despatches of BC and Vancouver Island","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:13:15 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:17:31 UTC","slug":"colonial-despatches-of-bc-and-vancouver-island","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"coldesp","description":"This digital archive contains the original correspondence between the British Colonial Office and the colonies of Vancouver Island and British Columbia. This project aims to digitize and publish online a complete archive of the correspondence covering the period from 1846 leading to the founding of Vancouver Island in 1849, the founding of British Columbia in 1858, the annexation of Vancouver Island by British Columbia in 1866, and up to the incorporation of B.C. into the Canadian Federation in 1871. It consists of page-images, XML-encoded transcriptions, editorial annotation and ancillary research data.\r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Martin Holmes","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-3944-1116","data_contact":"Martin Holmes","funder_name":null},{"id":7587,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:15:33 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:15:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2763","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Joe Bauer","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7588,"title":"SF Origins (Portage Template plan)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:17:00 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:19:46 UTC","slug":"sf-origins-portage-template-plan","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Creating an interactive web-edition of Science Fiction texts in the public domain to track the heritage of SF rhetorical devices in the works of marginalized authors of the 20th Century.","principal_investigator":"Phillip Howells","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"phowells2@unl.edu, 724-709-1925","funder_name":null},{"id":7589,"title":"Linked Early Modern Drama Online (LEMDO)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-06-11 18:18:38 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 18:19:11 UTC","slug":"linked-early-modern-drama-online-lemdo","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Janelle Jenstad","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7590,"title":"Market validation and cost analysis of scale up methods for production of industrial enzymes used for starch modification (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-06-11 19:23:34 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-11 20:07:36 UTC","slug":"market-validation-and-cost-analysis-of-scale-up-methods-for-production-of-industrial-enzymes-used-for-starch-modification-alliance-food-from-thought","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030401","identifier":"","description":"The proposed project is a cost analysis and feasibility study examining available options for scale up of an enzyme technology developed by the PI with a leading biopolymer manufacturer (Ecosynthetix Inc.). [1] The technology involves the modification and improvement of an existing commercial starch based polymer using glycogen branching enzymes and [2] improves the performance and handling properties of this commercial product, including other starch-based polymers and also removes the reliance on expensive foreign imported starches by removing amylose and consequent etrogradation. [3] The technology is proven at lab and pilot scale and there is also a market demand for these enzymes, the gap to be addressed is producing enzymes on a scale sufficient to meet the demand of the industrial process. [4] Our work plan aims to address this by conducting a cost analysis for the best means of producing the enzymes on an industrial scale, with the desired outcome [5] of developing a feasible scheme for enzyme production which will fit into the industrial process at Ecosynthetix Inc. [6] On completion of the project the team will need to produce enzyme, or source an enzyme manufacturer to produce enzyme at the required scale for full scale product manufacture.","principal_investigator":"Ian Tetlow","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"itetlow@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7591,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-12 12:27:56 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-12 12:27:56 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2765","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Asem Bala","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7593,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-12 14:37:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-12 14:37:49 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2766","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Molly Contini","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7594,"title":"Impact de la participation sportive chez les adolescents","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-12 15:14:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-16 18:04:59 UTC","slug":"impact-de-la-participation-sportive-chez-les-adolescents","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"862-2018-0002","identifier":"CRSH","description":"Ce projet vise à évaluer l’impact de la participation sportive sur la santé et le bien-être des jeunes. L’activité physique fait partie des saines habitudes de vie à adopter. Lorsque pratiquée dans un contexte sportif, elle peut avoir encore plus de bénéfices pour les jeunes. Toutefois, les connaissances sur les effets de la participation sportive chez les adolescents sont plutôt rares, notamment chez les jeunes qui ont vécus des événements de vie adverse (p.ex., violence, abus). On ne comprend pas encore tout à fait quels sont les aspects-clés de la participation sportive qui favorisent le bien-être durant l’adolescence. Au total, 2000 adolescents seront sollicités dans les écoles secondaires sélectionnées dans les régions du Saguenay−Lac-Saint-Jean, de Québec et de Montréal. Ils complèteront un questionnaire à 4 reprises (2 fois par année).","principal_investigator":"Jacinthe Dion","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0003-2701-6283","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7595,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-12 15:36:57 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-12 15:36:57 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2767","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_inve