litative designed study that is examining this issue in Grey, Bruce, Huron and Perth Counties. Interviews will be conducted with 20 key informants in each of the counties to establish an understanding of the issue from the perspective of those who provide related health and food services to the rural elderly. This will be followed by interviews with 20 rural elderly individuals living in each of the counties to understand their relationship to food insecurity/security, the challenges they experience and any consequences they may suffer from. ","principal_investigator":"Al Lauzon","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7616,"title":"PTSD and Chronic Pain","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-17 23:14:52 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-17 23:16:14 UTC","slug":"ptsd-and-chronic-pain","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"larah.maunder@queensu.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":"Tim Salomons","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7617,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-18 13:29:41 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-18 13:29:41 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--387","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Anne Busin","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7618,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-18 18:45:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-18 18:45:20 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2779","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7619,"title":"Process-based crop modelling for managing climate change impacts on agroecosystems","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-06-18 20:19:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 18:32:05 UTC","slug":"process-based-crop-modelling-for-managing-climate-change-impacts-on-agroecosystems","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030322","identifier":"UofG2017-2830 ","description":"Current and future climate change impacts on soybean, corn and potato production in Ontario will be assessed with the Decision Support System for Agrotechnology Transfer, DSSAT, cropping system model.  The DSSAT simulations will require crop management, soil and climate data.   Measured climate data will be utilised for historic yield simulations, while climate data derived from general circulation models, GCMs, will be utilised for future yield simulations.","principal_investigator":"Professor Jon Warland (supervisor), Kemp Simon (PhD student)","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Professor Jon Warland","funder_name":null},{"id":7620,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-19 12:28:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-19 12:28:46 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2780","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Etienne Rousseau","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7621,"title":"Farmer-Led Research: Evaluating a KTT Best Practice","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-06-19 15:31:21 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-19 15:33:23 UTC","slug":"farmer-led-research-evaluating-a-ktt-best-practice","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"KTT(RF)2019-10354","identifier":"","description":"In Ontario, despite efforts to drive adoption of environmental best management practices (BMPs), rates of key\r\npractices (e.g. cover cropping, minimized tillage and pesticide application, biodiversity conservation) remain\r\nlower than desired. Literature demonstrates that farmer-led research is a useful mechanism for knowledge\r\ngeneration and transfer to increase adoption of environmentally sustainable practices. This proposed project will\r\nexamine farmer-led research as a knowledge translation and transfer best practice through three key activities:\r\n1) an evaluation of the Ecological Farmers Association of Ontario’s Farmer-led Research program; 2) a\r\nliterature review that synthesizes information about farmer-led research in other contexts, highlighting best\r\npractices and assessing their potential relevance for Ontario; and 3) key informant interviews with\r\ninternationally-recognized leaders in farmer-led research, for example the Practical Farmers of Iowa. The project\r\nwill allow us to identify pathways to success as well as constraints with respect to farmer-led research as a KTT\r\npractice. Results of the research will be used to develop a strategy for expanding the scope of farmer-led\r\nresearch in Ontario as a KTT mechanism for driving environmental BMP adoption.","principal_investigator":"Erin Nelson","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7448-9588","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7623,"title":"Improving the Effectiveness of Advisory Services for Facilitating Information Sharing, Accessibility","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-06-19 17:05:17 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-23 16:29:34 UTC","slug":"improving-the-effectiveness-of-advisory-services-for-facilitating-information-sharing-accessibility","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Ataharul Chowdhury","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"chowdhua@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7624,"title":"BMRC-IRMU","dmptemplate_id":47,"created_at":"2019-06-19 19:35:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-19 19:36:44 UTC","slug":"bmrc-irmu","organisation_id":45,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Valerie Preston","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7625,"title":"My plan (York University)","dmptemplate_id":47,"created_at":"2019-06-19 21:56:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-19 21:56:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-york-university--14","organisation_id":45,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"khushboo khushi.phull@gmail.com","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7626,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-19 22:29:02 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-19 22:29:02 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2781","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Anita Chiu","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7627,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-06-20 10:25:22 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-20 10:30:34 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--17","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2018-3099 ","identifier":"030463","description":"The largest cost of raising chickens is feed, therefore maintaining chickens in an environment that supports proper nutrition is essential for productivity and profitability. Widespread adoption of the ideal protein concept, along with the use of digestible amino acid (AA) values for feed ingredients and commercial availability of crystalline AA, has enabled nutritionists to formulate cost-effective and optimal diets for poultry. However, nutrient absorption and gut adaptation to luminal inflammatory stress is challenging production efficiency as a consequence of the restriction on the use of antibiotic growth promoters (AGP) and anti-coccidial drugs. The metabolic changes induced by inflammation are homeostatic in nature and thus nutrients that would have been utilized for growth and skeletal muscle accretion are diverted to support host defense systems. The proposed research will systematically examine AA requirements for poultry raised in antibiotic free feeding regimens when submitted to enteric immunological stress. Essential amino acids that may become limiting either for intestinal function or whole-body growth will be determined to aid in developing poultry diets to “condition” the gut for better nutrient utilization and program metabolism to improve production efficiency and reduce nitrogen excretion. ","principal_investigator":"Elijah Kiarie","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-9752-8546","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7628,"title":"My plan (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2019-06-20 12:02:11 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-20 12:56:29 UTC","slug":"my-plan-memorial-university-of-newfoundland--7","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This dataset contains the results of a survey distributed at the Memorial University of Newfoundland to ascertain current RDM practices of researchers. The dataset is contained in OpenDocument Spreadsheet (.ods) files.","principal_investigator":"Alison Farrell","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"alisonr@mun.ca ","funder_name":null},{"id":7629,"title":"Knowledge Workforce","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-20 13:45:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-20 13:55:59 UTC","slug":"knowledge-workforce","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Data management plan for the Workforce and In-migration Strategy ","principal_investigator":"Lakshay Raheja ","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Dajana Turkovic","funder_name":null},{"id":7630,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-20 14:43:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-20 14:45:21 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--388","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"Résidente en médecine nucléaire","description":"","principal_investigator":"Marie-Eve Marcotte","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://