,"slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--389","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Marie-Eve Emond Beaulieu","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7644,"title":" Pre- and post-weaning nutrition strategies to improve growth performance, gut health, and robustness of pigs after weaning.","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-06-25 15:57:23 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 16:01:05 UTC","slug":"pre-and-post-weaning-nutrition-strategies-to-improve-growth-performance-gut-health-and-robustness-of-pigs-after-weaning","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030466","identifier":"UofG2018-3132","description":"","principal_investigator":"Lee-Anne Huber","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7645,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-25 16:12:22 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 16:12:22 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2792","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7646,"title":"My plan (University of Saskatchewan)","dmptemplate_id":21,"created_at":"2019-06-25 16:14:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 16:14:03 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-saskatchewan--4","organisation_id":17,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7648,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2019-06-25 16:16:14 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 16:16:14 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--747","organisation_id":2,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7649,"title":"Fate of heavy metals in lagoon and wetland wastewater treatment systems and quantification of relative impacts to downstream aquatic systems","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-25 17:21:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-02 13:06:44 UTC","slug":"fate-of-heavy-metals-in-lagoon-and-wetland-wastewater-treatment-systems-and-quantification-of-relative-impacts-to-downstream-aquatic-systems","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This study aims to assess the effectiveness of current community wastewater treatment systems in retaining heavy metals, and the potential loading of heavy metals from these sources to aquatic environments. Many communities use sewage lagoons and downgradient wetlands to provide treatment for municipal wastewater (sewage). Many SDFs also accept other waste streams such as leachate from SWDFs and some SDFs accept waste from composting and soil treatment facilities. Heavy metals are contaminants of concern within these SDFs. It is currently unknown whether the SDFs in NWT are “hot spots” for heavy metals, and if they are having an impact on aquatic systems. Territorial decision-makers have identified the need for research to inform their management of these potential heavy metal sources. In recognition of this research gap, this study has been proposed to improve our understanding of the environmental fate of heavy metals within SDFs and the receiving environment. This information will lead to improved management and regulation of wastewater in NWT and protection of aquatic and human health.  The study will include: (i) a desktop review of existing data; and (ii) a field investigation on two sites, selected based on the outcomes of the desktop review. The field investigation will include detailed monitoring of heavy metals within the water and sediment of lagoon and wetland treatment systems, and the aquatic environment they discharge to. Communities will be engaged during the study duration with employment of two residents to help with the fieldwork campaign and data dissemination. Plain language summaries, interim and final reports, and a Story Map will be produced, translated and presented in-person to the communities and project stakeholders. The results will give insight into the potential for SDFs to either attenuate or act as a source of heavy metals. These results will enable identification of potential cumulative impacts from heavy metals associated with SDFs and SWDFs to NWT receiving environments. \r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Rob Jamieson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"P: 902-494-6791, jamiesrc@dal.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7650,"title":"Novanet Indigenous Subject Headings Working Group","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-25 17:21:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 17:22:31 UTC","slug":"novanet-indigenous-subject-headings-working-group","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Amy Lorencz","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7651,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-06-25 20:17:30 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 20:17:30 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--493","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jennifer Bui","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7652,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-25 20:38:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-25 20:38:43 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2795","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"brian.hansen@ahs.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7653,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-26 18:06:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-26 18:06:04 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--390","organisation_id":29,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Marie-Eve Emond Beaulieu","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7654,"title":"Transition of Care","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2019-06-26 18:11:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-26 18:12:50 UTC","slug":"transition-of-care","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Nicole Pittman","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7655,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-26 20:29:05 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-26 20:29:05 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2796","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"RAMSES ILARRAZA","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7657,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-27 14:07:34 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-27 14:07:34 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2797","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Kevin Manuel","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7658,"title":"Global Competence for ALL","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-27 14:43:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-27 14:43:52 UTC","slug":"global-competence-for-all","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Linyuan Guo-Brennan","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7659,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-06-27 18:05:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-31 17:06:11 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--19","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030442","identifier":"UofG2018-3083","description":"Ontario biomass growers are keen to understand the impacts of land-use change on soil organic carbon (SOC) sequestration, nutrient-use efficiency (nitrogen [N] and phosphorus [P]) and greenhouse gas emissions reduction as influenced by biomass crops (switchgrass and Miscanthus). Biomass growers have a shared goal in developing sustainable and profitable best management strategies to further enhance environmental sustainability of their industry in order to ensure continuous and uninterrupted supply of feedstock to bioeconomy and industrial uses.\r\nPrevious OMAFRA funded research (# 301-82) has established a GIS database and maps with SOC data linked to 19 biomass grower fields in Ontario. This baseline data set enables future monitoring of rates of soil C sequestration. The influence of bio-fertilizer on biomass crop productivity also has been studied at local scale during the previous project. However, field scale influence of bio-fertilizer application on biomass productivity, soil phosphorus, greenhouse gas emissions reduction and soil health aspects needs to studied. This is important in order to firmly conclude biomass crops’ contribution to ecosystem services including soil health and\r\nSOC sequestration. Collectively, results derived from this study will directly contribute to the OMAFRA-UofG Bioeconomy-Industrial use priorities, and Environmental Sustainability priorities.\r\n\r\nIn support of above described rationale, data (numeric) from this research will be collected to address the following objectives:\r\n1. To quantify SOC sequestration “rates” by using 2016 baseline data.\r\n2. To quantitatively assess soil total N and P associated with above land-use systems.\r\n3. To quantify SOC and N in different soil aggregate-size fractions.\r\n4. To quantify greenhouse gas emissions as influenced by the applied fertilizer treatments.\r\n5. To quantify C (CO2) released from different fractions through, incubation studies.\r\n6. To assess SOC stability and sustainability in 3 land-use systems based on above data.\r\n7. To quantitatively assess biomass yields influenced by the use of different biofertilizers supplied by supporting industry partners and rank them based on their yield response and cost-effectiveness.\r\n8. To develop soil health indicators for biomass crops by quantitatively assessing fungal communities (microfaunal), earthworm densities (macro-faunal), SOC, Haney soil health and Solvita test.\r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Naresh Thevathasan","principal_investigator_identifier":"908010380","data_contact":"Amir Bazrgar, 519-824-4120 Ext. 53488. abazrgar@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7660,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-06-28 18:28:32 UTC","updated_at":"2019-06-28 18:34:13 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2799","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"CIMP210","identifier":"","description":"NWT CIMP210 - Data Management Plan\r\n\r\nDevelopment of a Biological Monitoring Program to Detect Change in Stream Health Along the Dempster-Inuvik-Tuktoyaktuk-Corridor\r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Joseph Culp","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"jordan.musetta-lambert@canada.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7661,"title":"ICLR Doberstein","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-02 16:39:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-02 16:39:47 UTC","slug":"iclr-doberstein","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Brent Doberstein","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7662,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-02 17:17:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-02 17:17:43 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage-