"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jennifer Spinney","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7668,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-04 18:55:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-04 18:55:25 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--393","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7669,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-07-05 02:08:40 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-05 02:11:23 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--20","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030360","identifier":"","description":"Validation of a dairy cow illness detection model using behaviour and production data from precision technologies","principal_investigator":"Trevor DeVries","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-9364-2456","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7670,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-05 17:23:50 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-05 17:23:50 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2804","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Carol Perry","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7671,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-05 19:39:52 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-05 19:39:52 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2805","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Chris Rennick","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7672,"title":"Pathogen surveillance for late blight management decisions in field tomatoes","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-07-05 19:57:41 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-05 20:02:16 UTC","slug":"pathogen-surveillance-for-late-blight-management-decisions-in-field-tomatoes","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2018-3084","identifier":"UofG2018-3084","description":"Late blight (Phytophthora infestans) is a destructive disease of field tomatoes in Ontario. High-risk conditions for\r\nlate blight require modifications to fungicide programs to manage risk. However, over the past 10 years the date\r\nof first appearance of late blight has varied from late June to late August. Thus, better identification of high-risk\r\nperiods would improve judicious use of fungicides. One approach to assessing disease risk is to monitor for\r\npathogen inoculum. The research will evaluate the efficacy of the Spornado passive trap, Rotorod active trap,\r\nand SporeCam for identification of P. infestans inoculum in one growing region to help conceptualize a\r\nmonitoring network. Establishment of a spore trap network will allow for comparison of the timing and frequency\r\nof P. infestans detection among traps and unprotected sentinel plots. To assess the value of spore trap data in\r\ndecision-making, field trials will compare fungicide program adjustments based on near real-time trap results\r\nwith the BliteCast decision support system and current industry strategies for identification of high-risk periods\r\nusing susceptible and resistant tomato cultivars. The project will contribute to the development of best practices\r\nfor establishment of surveillance networks in Ontario and explore the application of network data for\r\nmanagement decisions.","principal_investigator":"Cheryl Trueman","principal_investigator_identifier":"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7919-0713","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7673,"title":"Data Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":33,"created_at":"2019-07-05 20:52:01 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-05 20:59:26 UTC","slug":"data-management-plan--4","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The nature of this research project is to analyze the 2nd and 3rd metacarophalangeal joints for inflammation and how it influences the development / progression of bone erosions. Specifically, we will be collecting data to better differentiate between true inflammation and normal levels of inflammation (acquired with ultrasound). \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe collected data will be securely stored within a One Drive Business account, after the data has been stripped of any identifying information and encrypted. The information is being store in this manner to allow for researchers and collaborators to access the data and perform their own analysis.","principal_investigator":"Dr. Sarah Manske","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7674,"title":"Greenhouse targeted detection LAAIR Market Research","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-07-08 13:37:21 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-08 14:07:07 UTC","slug":"greenhouse-targeted-detection-laair-market-research","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"LAAIR2019-5378","identifier":"LAAIR2019-5378","description":"Market validation data management plan for survey of greenhouse operators to assess the application for point of need molecular protocols to screen for pest, pathogen, and invasive species. ","principal_investigator":"Robert Hanner","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Robert Young","funder_name":null},{"id":7675,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-07-08 16:18:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-08 16:30:59 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--23","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030417","identifier":"LAAIR2019-5387","description":"This project aims to produce a soy-based fermented cheese that is analogous to a fresh cheese product, but is more environmentally friendly, tastier, and healthier than other dairy and non-dairy cheeses. Veganism was a top searched trend in 2017, and interest increased over 250% over the past 4 years. As a further indication of market demand, Plant-Based Foods of Canada was a new industry organization established in September 2018 that functions as a division of Foods & Consumer Products of Canada and supports the regulatory and market interests of plant-based food companies. Finally, we saw strong demand for our product in surveys and focus groups conducted with over 400 members of our target population.\r\n\r\nPresently there are no locally-produced soy-based premium cheese blocks or spreads available on the market, with all the alternatives being tree nut-based. Our research showed that fewer people have tried premium plant-based cheeses than other lower-tier brands, primarily due to cost. Sensory tests also showed that consumers liked our product very much and wanted to purchase it. Our MVP clearly differentiates itself by being a soy-based cheese that has vastly improved sensory qualities yet is competitively priced within the segment. \r\n\r\nHaving done initial market validation studies and testing at pilot scale, we intend to 1) conduct further testing with pilot scale equipment to identify methods of automating and scaling our processes, 2) finalize 3 SKUs for our industry partner, and 3) complete process testing at industrial scale. The desired outcome is to establish a scalable, cost effective process to produce 3 SKUs of soy-based cheese without compromising on sensory quality and nutritional content. Upon completion, three of the team members will found a company to commercialize our MVP.","principal_investigator":"Arthur Hill","principal_investigator_identifier":"arhill@uoguelph.ca","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7676,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-07-08 18:56:11 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-21 15:56:23 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--24","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UG # 30369","identifier":"","description":"The project explores farm to school food programs in Ontario.  While there has been considerable attention to the (children's) health related dimension of Farm to School food programs (F2S) there has been less attention given in Ontario to date to the role of local food production in supplying these programs, and the degree to which public institutions, in this case schools, might grow to represent potentially valuable markets for farmers. The research will seek to document perspectives, experiences and, importantly, expectations, needs and obstacles from various actor groups in the farm to school value chain.  This includes farmer/producers, school food purchasers and various intermediary actors that serve to connect and facilitate.    It is hoped the research can expand both an understanding of the factors and actions that can improve and expand farm to school food ventures, and provide a preliminary indication of the potential  economic impact of F2S initiatives for farmers.  ","principal_investigator":"John Smithers","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"John Smithers; jsmither@uoguelph.ca;  ph: 519 824 4120 x56722","funder_name":null},{"id":7677,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-09 12:12:40 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-09 12:12:40 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--394","organisation_id":29,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Stephane Talbot","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7678,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2019-07-09 15:54:27 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-09 15:54:27 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--749","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Chad Krayenhoff","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7679,"title":"Language in Lyrics","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-09 18:01:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-09 18:05:25 UTC","slug":"language-in-lyrics","organisation_id":36,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Heather Sparling","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2313-9075","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7680,"title":"DFO ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-09 18:01:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-09 18:05:20 UTC","slug":"dfo","organisation_id":36,"grant_number":"","identifier":"CBU","description":"","principal_investigator":"Jasmine Hoover","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3563-6952","data_contact":"Jasmine Hoover ","funder_name":null},{"id":7681,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-09 18:25:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-09 18:25:37 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2808","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"David Feinberg","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7683,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-10 18:25:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-10 18:25:39 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2809","organisation_id":9,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Maryse Kiese","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7684,"title":"Improving management of cercospora leaf spot in Ontario sugar beets","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-07-10 18:56:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-10 19:02:39 UTC","slug":"improving-management-of-cercospora-leaf-spot-in-ontario-sugar-beets","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2018-3168","identifier":"UofG2018-3168","description":"Cercospora leaf spot (CLS, Cercospora beticola) is an economically important disease of sugar beet in Ontario. There is increasing concern about CLS because of fungicide resistance, the proposed phase-out of mancozeb, and lack of host resistance. We will investigate methods to improve CLS management using multiple approaches. First, the potential of a canopy deposition aid to improve fungicide coverage and performance will be evaluated. Second, we will screen alternative fungicides (i.e. bicarbonates, phosphites, alternative copper formulations, biologicals, micronutrients) for CLS management. Pending these results, we will evaluate methods to incorporate these tools into fungicide programs, and/or investigate their mode of action (i.e. iron, boron). Finally, since the timing to initiate fungicide applications for CLS is poorly understood, and there is evidence that C. beticola is active much earlier than previously thought, we will use living and Burkard spore traps to examine the possibility that early season inoculum sources are from asexual and/or sexual spores. This will contribute to the development of a model to predict early season infection by C. beticola and improve fungicide application timing. Successful completion of the project will make important contributions to both short and long-term management of CLS in Ontario and worldwide.","principal_investigator":"Cheryl Trueman","principal_investigator_identifier":"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-7919-0713","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7685,"title":"COLC","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-10 19:02:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-10 19:05:53 UTC","slug":"colc","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Carie Hoover","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Diz@colc.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7686,"title":"My plan (University of Manitoba )","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2019-07-10 21:46:23 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-10 21:50:53 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-manitoba--38","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"HS22801(H2019:165)","description":"The proposed study aims to examine the impact of the CBTm Course on prevention of PTSD and related conditions among PSP’s.  It is hypothesized that participating in the CBTm Course will lead to improvements in outcomes compared to the comparison group.  We propose to conduct a 2-arm, pilot randomized-controlled trial to address the following primary objectives:\r\n\r\n1.\tTo examine the impact of the CBTm Course on symptoms of PTSD\r\n2.\tTo examine the impact of the CBTm Course on symptoms of anxiety and depression\r\n3.\tTo examine the impact of the CBTm Course on resilience\r\n\r\nThis pilot RCT will also address the following secondary objectives:\r\n4.\tTo examine the impact of the CBTm Course on physiological and mental health symptoms  \r\n5.\tTo examine the impact of the CBTm Course on perceived levels of stress\r\n6.\tTo examine client satisfaction of the CBTm Course\r\n7.\tTo examine the impact of the CBTm Course on the ability to engage in mindfulness\r\n8.\tTo examine the impact of the CBTm Course on work engagement\r\n","principal_investigator":"Jacquelyne Wong","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"jwong8@hsc.mb.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7687,"title":"SL_FCstacks_Summer 2019","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-07-11 18:15:38 UTC","updated_at":"2019-07-11 18:47:12 UTC","slug":"sl_fcstacks_summer-2019","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Stauffer FC collection\r\nTo obtain a high-level overview of the collection and create actionable pick lists for deaccession of duplicates.","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7688,"title":"My plan (Portage Templat