","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-08-26 22:22:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-30 13:52:05 UTC","slug":"a-temporal-study-of-salmonella-serovars-in-poultry-breeder-flocks-and-hatcheries-in-ontario-from-2009-to-2018-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"FRS Project # 030449","identifier":"UoG2018-3162","description":"The research project will analyze surveillance data of the OMAFRA-supervised Ontario Hatchery and Supply Flock Policy (OHSFP), which provides monitoring and testing of Ontario poultry breeding flocks for Salmonella. The primary goal of the project is to describe long-term trends and seasonal patterns in Salmonella isolations collected from breeder flocks and hatcheries through the OHSFP over the past 10 years (2009 to 2018). A secondary goal is to validate the broiler breeder Salmonella vaccination program, which began midway through this period.","principal_investigator":"Dr. Michele Guerin","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"519-824-4120 ext. 54486; mguerin@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7824,"title":"Demonstration version ","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2019-08-27 19:55:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-27 20:00:16 UTC","slug":"demonstration-version","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This is a demo based on a real-life case of a health research project (contact: Cox; opioids in palliative care)","principal_investigator":"Andrea Szwajcer","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID 0000-0002-7215-9219","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7825,"title":"Test (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2019-08-27 20:52:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-27 20:56:18 UTC","slug":"test-university-of-alberta-template","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This is a language documentation project on Piaroa, a Sáliban language of Venezuela and Colombia. The primary research question concerns the grammar of the language. What are the sounds? How are words and phrases formed? How, when, and by whom is the language used? The data is being collected to create a corpus of naturalistic language data that will allow us to further the description of this language.","principal_investigator":"Jorge Emilio Rosés Labrada","principal_investigator_identifier":"Jorge Emilio Rosés Labrada","data_contact":"jrosesla@ualberta.ca; 780-492-5698","funder_name":null},{"id":7826,"title":"Highly Graphitized Biocarbon from Biomass for Automotive and Smart Material Applications","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-08-28 14:17:28 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 18:04:10 UTC","slug":"highly-graphitized-biocarbon-from-biomass-for-automotive-and-smart-material-applications","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030332","identifier":"UofG2017-2870","description":"- Determination of the most effective source of biomass in the Ontario region for biocarbon production in term of properties, sustainability and cost.\r\n- Manufacturing of highly graphitized biocarbon particles from biomass with the presence of catalyst: process optimization and scale-up.\r\n- Design of biocomposites by the addition of biocarbon particles into biobased and biodegradable polymers: optimization of biocarbon composites preparation methods.\r\n- Evaluation of thermal and electrical conductive properties of optimized composite blends and trail test of the industrial models.\r\n- Synthesis, design and optimization of smart green materials with elevated absorption properties for depollution application. \r\n- Economic/properties balance evaluation of the new series of biocomposites in comparison to commercial grades graphitic filler based composites.\r\n- Economic and social impact of development of these new products in the Ontario and establishment of a regional and international circular economy.","principal_investigator":"Manjusri Misra","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0003-2179-7699","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7827,"title":"High Biomass-filled Affordable and Cost-competitive Green Composites for Compostable Food Packaging Applications","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-08-28 14:22:05 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 17:29:25 UTC","slug":"high-biomass-filled-affordable-and-cost-competitive-green-composites-for-compostable-food-packaging-applications","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030361","identifier":"UofG2017-3008","description":"•\tDeveloping high performance biodegradable materials for substitution of current petro-based products used in food packaging applications; including stiffness – toughness – HDT balance and good barrier properties.\r\n•\tIntroducing biomass filler with weight loadings as high as 50 wt%, guaranteeing the cost competitiveness of these biodegradable packaging products in the market;\r\n•\tPrototyping Compostable Food Containers/Cutlery by the thermoforming process or other applicable polymer processing methods.\r\n•\tConduct various assessments to understand the full life cycle of the designed biodegradable package from manufacturer and consumer perspectives, and the socioeconomic benefits and GHG impact.","principal_investigator":"Amar Mohanty","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-1079-2481","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7828,"title":"Exposing Circular Economy in Advanced Biocarbon Manufacturing from Chicken Feather Wastes for Light-weight Auto-parts Uses","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-08-28 15:49:49 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 17:30:49 UTC","slug":"exposing-circular-economy-in-advanced-biocarbon-manufacturing-from-chicken-feather-wastes-for-light-weight-auto-parts-uses","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030331","identifier":"UofG2017-2869","description":"•\tProduce biocarbon material from chicken feather waste and its biocomposites that can match or exceed the properties of commercially available synthetic composite materials for automotive application.\r\n•\tInvestigate and optimize pyrolysis parameters to maximize yield and increase graphitic structure.\r\n•\tMaximize Ontario sourced biobased content in biocomposites.\r\n•\tMinimize the biocomposite cost to allow for competition with commercial synthetic composites in automotive applications.\r\n•\tCreate materials that are feasible for production at industrial scale.","principal_investigator":"Amar Mohanty","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-1079-2481","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7829,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-08-28 17:43:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 17:44:45 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--48","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"10377","identifier":"","description":"This is a knowledge mobilization initiative promoting sustainable soil\r\nmanagement by bridging gaps between farmers, researchers, and consumers.\r\nInterviews, surveys, and other evaluation formats are being collected to determine\r\neffectiveness of KTT efforts.","principal_investigator":"Kari Dunfield","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Cameron Ogilvie, cogilvie@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7830,"title":"Shannon's Test Plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-08-28 19:05:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 19:26:54 UTC","slug":"shannon-s-test-plan-portage-template","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Shannon McAlorum","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7831,"title":"Bringing Metis Music Home","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-08-28 19:10:27 UTC","updated_at":"2019-08-28 19:16:55 UTC","slug":"bringing-metis-music-home","organisation_id":28,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Monique 