ll,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Zichao Lin","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7965,"title":"CFI-IF Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-16 02:54:06 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-16 02:55:51 UTC","slug":"cfi-if-plan","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Data Management plan for CFI-IF (Ullah)","principal_investigator":"Aman Ullah","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"James doiron","funder_name":null},{"id":7966,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-16 16:46:06 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-16 16:46:06 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2959","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Stefanie Roder","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7967,"title":"Innovative strategies to add value to (Ontario grown) bean-derived food ingredients (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-17 03:56:56 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-17 04:03:55 UTC","slug":"innovative-strategies-to-add-value-to-ontario-grown-bean-derived-food-ingredients-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2018-3161","identifier":"bean project","description":"This research project is a study focusing on processing of bean flour and bean cooking/soaking liquid. The data that will be collected will be chemical, physical and physicochemical characterization of these fractions after processing. Also functionality testing (e.g. suitability for bakery product ingredient, interface stabilization) and sensory trials on developed food products will be gathered (both quantitative and qualitative data). The purpose of the data collection is to evaluate the potential of the bean-derived ingredients as value-added food ingredients.","principal_investigator":"Iris Joye","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-0992-466X","data_contact":"Iris Joye","funder_name":null},{"id":7968,"title":"Targeting tumor hypoxia ","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-09-17 16:28:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-17 18:10:50 UTC","slug":"targeting-tumor-hypoxia","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Shoukat Dedhar","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"schafe@bccrc.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7969,"title":"Drug Depletion Study of Injectable Trimethoprim Sulfadoxine in Lactating Dairy Does","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-18 18:13:05 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-18 18:20:24 UTC","slug":"drug-depletion-study-of-injectable-trimethoprim-sulfadoxine-in-lactating-dairy-does","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG-3260","identifier":"UofG-3260","description":"Data is being collected on the levels of sulphadoxine present in the milk of lactating dairy goats after being injected with trimethoprim sulphadoxine intramuscularly once a day for 5 days. The objective is determine the withdrawal time for this antibiotic in milk.","principal_investigator":"Cath Bauman","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6706-5456","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7971,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-18 19:53:37 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-18 19:53:37 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2960","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7972,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-18 20:09:05 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-25 19:38:35 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--73","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This project will bring about a novel plant-based meatless steak with the fibrous texture typical for animal muscle tissue through the combined use of microstructure engineering and extrusion technology. According to FAO, the livestock sector is one of the major stressors on the planet. Unfortunately, most consumers enjoy the texture of meat and many are disappointed with traditional plant-based protein products such as tofu and seitan. Lately, the development of novel plant-based structured or fibrous products has emerged as the most promising strategy to decrease meat consumption. \r\nThe aim of this project is to create a plant-based fibrous meat analog (p-steak prototype) using Ontario crops. To do so, investigations and product development will be performed at pilot plant scale using an innovative approach involving high moisture twin-screw extrusion and biopolymer chemistry. Compelling feasibility studies and market assessments clearly indicate that now is the right time to bring our p-steak into an industrially relevant environment. Patentable technology will result in multiple customizable Minimum Viable Products (MVPs) that can be tailored to the largest growing customer segment aligned. The p-steak will be a perfect alternative to traditional meat products and enable Canadians to meet the new Canada Food Guide in terms of protein intake. Organoleptic and sensory properties and processing cost will be carefully considered and investigated to achieve commercially viable products. Here, there is an excellent opportunity for Ontario plant producers and processors to add sustainable monetary value to their cereal and pulse crops. After successful completion of this project, we will seek financial support in terms of efficient marketing and industrial growth. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Mario Martinez","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://scholar.google.ca/citations?user=OBFz-I4AAAAJ&hl=en","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7973,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-18 20:27:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-18 20:35:43 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2961","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7975,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-18 21:47:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-18 21:47:04 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2963","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Dhawal Gupta","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7976,"title":"My plan (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2019-09-19 12:14:59 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-19 12:14:59 UTC","slug":"my-plan-memorial-university-of-newfoundland--18","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Kendra Lester","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7977,"title":"Enhancing digestion efficiency, weaning success, and welfare of dairy and veal calves through provision of a novel calf starter","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-19 14:52:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-19 14:55:05 UTC","slug":"enhancing-digestion-efficiency-weaning-success-and-welfare-of-dairy-and-veal-calves-through-provision-of-a-novel-calf-starter","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030470","identifier":"UofG2018-3248","description":"","principal_investigator":"Trevor DeVries","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"ext. 54081, tdevries@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":7978,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-19 14:58:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-19 15:01:24 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2964","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"030420","identifier":"LAAIR2019-5385","description":"PTC+: A novel culture vessel for plant propagation. Market validation for new culture  vessels.","principal_investigator":"Praveen Saxena","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-7203-6868","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7979,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-19 17:47:34 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-19 17:47:34 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2965","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Ian Fleming","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7980,"title":"OMAFRA’s Guidelines on Permitted Uses as a tool to achieve farmland protection, farm diversification and provide economic benefit: Assessing effectiveness and identifying best practices","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-20 13:00:44 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-20 13:05:56 UTC","slug":"omafra-s-guidelines-on-permitted-uses-as-a-tool-to-achieve-farmland-protection-farm-diversification-and-provide-economic-benefit-assessing-effectiveness-and-identifying-best-practices","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2018-3120","identifier":"","description":"A review and analysis of farm diversification strategies and their economic benefit.  This includes a review and evaluation of policy and the identification of best practices","principal_investigator":"Wayne Caldwell","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Wayne Caldwell","funder_name":null},{"id":7981,"title":"International Food Policy Study - Youth","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-20 15:21:35 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-20 15:23:14 UTC","slug":"international-food-policy-study-youth","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"ORE 41477","description":"","principal_investigator":"David Hammond","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Christine White","funder_name":null},{"id":7982,"title":"Neuro700","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-20 16:03:04 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 15:44:35 UTC","slug":"neuro700","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Kiersten Mangold","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7983,"title":"Net Carbon Balance Dynamics of Diverse and Non-diverse Crop Rotations at the Farm Scale","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-20 18:58:10 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-20 19:02:29 UTC","slug":"net-carbon-balance-dynamics-of-diverse-and-non-diverse-crop-rotations-at-the-farm-scale","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2017-2862","identifier":"","description":"This is a field project aimed at determining the net carbon balance of non-diverse rotation (cornsoybean-soybean) and a diverse rotation (corn-soybean-winter wheat with cover crops) over 3 years. Drivers limiting carbon uptake or\r\nenhancing carbon loss, and how these change over the course of a year, or between years, for the two fields\r\nstudied will be identified. Recommendations on how to best manage diverse systems with cover crops so as to ensure long-term carbon gain will be made.","principal_investigator":"Claudia Wagner-Riddle","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-4802-6088","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7984,"title":"Tracing nitrogen losses and transfer from cover crops and cover crop mixtures to the subsequent corn crop","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-20 19:04:45 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-20 19:06:22 UTC","slug":"tracing-nitrogen-losses-and-transfer-from-cover-crops-and-cover-crop-mixtures-to-the-subsequent-corn-crop","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2018-3130","identifier":"","description":"We are using a novel approach of tracing N from above and below\r\nground cover crop residue into the subsequent corn crop. The experiment will involve application of a 15N\r\nlabelled solution to cover crops and cover crop mixtures in fall, include the study of over-winter N dynamics and\r\nprovide estimates of cover crop N loss. Emissions of the greenhouse gas nitrous oxide will be measured and\r\ntraced to the above and below ground cover crop N pools. Practical recommendations for farmers concerned\r\nabout the N availability to cash crops that follow single cover crop or cover crop mixtures will be made. The\r\ngained knowledge will help guide cover crop adoption and improve soil health in Ontario in the long-term.","principal_investigator":"Claudia Wagner-Riddle","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-4802-6088","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7985,"title":"MSc Project - OCN Signaling Pathway","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-20 19:26:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-20 19:27:53 UTC","slug":"msc-project-ocn-signaling-pathway","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Erika Kropf","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7986,"title":"SMP Lab","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2019-09-20 22:59:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-20 23:00:50 UTC","slug":"smp-lab","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Dr. Jean-Sebastien Blouin","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7987,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-22 14:17:29 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-22 14:17:29 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2970","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Mohammad Ali","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7988,"title":"Cracking the Correction Code ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-22 17:56:21 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-22 17:59:09 UTC","slug":"cracking-the-correction-code","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":"6027360","identifier":"CTL ERG 19-20","description":"The Department of French Studies recently introduced reforms for improving the\r\ngrammatical accuracy and quality of student writing. However, despite implementing this common framework, instructors do not know what kinds of feedback will improve learning outcomes. This project explores the effectiveness of different kinds of corrective feedback on student writing in our second-year French language composition course, FREN 231. By doing so, this research project empowers instructors with strategies for developing the writing skills of second language learners.\r\n\r\nThis study will collect samples of student writing, coded analysis of student error ratios, and surveys of student beliefs about error correction.\r\n","principal_investigator":"Michael Reyes","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7502-9295","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7989,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-22 20:17:55 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-22 20:17:55 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2972","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Adile Nexha","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7990,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 13:47:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 13:47:03 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--417","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Arina Soare","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7991,"title":"CAN-BIND Deep Learning","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 14:09:19 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 14:45:48 UTC","slug":"can-bind-deep-learning","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Pedro Ballester","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9928-2527","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7992,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 14:55:57 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 14:55:57 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2974","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Flavia Spiroiu","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7993,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 15:02:06 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 15:02:06 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2975","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7994,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 15:10:39 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 15:10:39 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2976","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jennifer Mepham","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7995,"title":"The use of big data to predict the emergence of foodborne outbreaks ","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-23 15:39:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-23 17:57:04 UTC","slug":"the-use-of-big-data-to-predict-the-emergence-of-foodborne-outbreaks","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"499016","identifier":"","description":"Typically, Canadian infections from foodborne pathogens, Vibrio spp., and Cyclospora, have been small and sporadic, usually associated with travel and importation of herbs, berries, seafood and fresh produce, especially leafy green vegetables such as lettuce. Over the last few years, Canada, particularly the provinces of British Columbia (BC), Alberta, Saskatchewan, Ontario and Quebec have seen a rise in infections from these two pathogens. Why? Is it due to climate change, most notably increases in sea temperatures during the spring and summer months and globalization of food? \r\n\r\nOne of example of this is the Vibrio parahaemolyticus outbreak in 2015, where 82 people became ill after consuming raw oysters caught off the BC coast. One of the causes was warmer seas, which was on average 2ºC above the norm for that time of year (July-September). As a result, the Vancouver Coastal Health Authority banned the sale of raw oysters harvested on Vancouver Island for the first time since 1997 (Public Health Agency of Canada, 2015; BC Centres for Disease Control, 2018a). \r\n\r\nAnother example is the Cyclospora outbreak in the late spring early summer of 2016 that resulted in 87 reported cases from Ontario, Quebec, Alberta and BC. The exact food source was not identified, but believed to be imported produce for reasons of: (a) previous Cyclospora outbreaks have been linked to pre-packaged salad mixes, basil, cilantro, raspberries, blackberries, mesclun lettuce and snow and snap peas, and (b) the parasite is generally not found on produce grown in Canada, United States or Europe (Public Health Agency of Canada, 2016). \r\n\r\nFrom our current on-going research in developing a modeling framework to predict foodborne pathogens in Canada, we determined that a more in-depth evaluation was needed on individual pathogens and especially how they are affected by climate change, globalization of food importation and travel. As such, this research will focus on Vibrio spp., and Cyclospora addressing why Canada has seen an increase in outbreaks associated with these two pathogens. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Jeff Farber","principal_investigator_identifier":"300027564","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":7996,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 17:05:10 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 17:05:10 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2977","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Carly McIntyre-Wood","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7997,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 17:25:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 17:25:20 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2978","organisation_id":47,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Emily Tufts","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7998,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 17:33:41 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 17:33:41 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2979","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Heather Dwyer","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":7999,"title":"Pilot Data from Cannabis Study ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 17:33:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 17:37:54 UTC","slug":"pilot-data-from-cannabis-study","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"00001","description":"This is a blinded RCT pilot study. We will be exploring the preliminary safety and efficacy of adjunct cannabis therapy when compared to standard treatment of anxiety. The data will be collected for analysis.","principal_investigator":"Heather Dwyer","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"dwyerh1@mcmaster.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8000,"title":"Hip v Wrist","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 17:57:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 17:59:21 UTC","slug":"hip-v-wrist","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"PAR","description":"Hip v wrist","principal_investigator":"Becky Breau","principal_investigator_identifier":"Vallis LAB","data_contact":"Becky","funder_name":null},{"id":8001,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-09-23 18:02:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 18:02:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--78","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Becky Breau","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8002,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 18:11:50 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 18:11:50 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2982","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Balpreet Panesar","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8003,"title":"DS Needs Assessment","dmptemplate_id":47,"created_at":"2019-09-23 18:19:57 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 18:53:54 UTC","slug":"ds-needs-assessment","organisation_id":45,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The goal of this study is to create a holistic understanding of digital scholarship practices and needs at York University. In addition to serving the York University Libraries’ goals of supporting and fostering digital scholarship practices, the proposed study contributes to existing research of digital humanities and digital scholarship supports in postsecondary institutions and provides a snapshot of the awareness and use of digital research methods and tools in a large Canadian university with a strong liberal arts focus. The results of this study will inform a programmatic approach to digital scholarship work at York University, contribute to a paucity of literature on models for strengths-based needs assessments in libraries, complement a small but growing list of digital scholarship centre planning initiative case studies in Canadian academic libraries, and contribute to a greater understanding of the landscape of digital scholarship in Canada.\r\n\r\nWorking from an action research framework, and informed by strengths-based approaches, the proposed study will explore the following research questions:\r\n1.\tHow do York University faculty members and graduate students use research, teaching and scholarly communications practices that incorporate digital data, tools, or methods?\r\n2.\tWhat current supports for digital scholarship exist for the benefit of York University students, staff, and faculty, and what is their scope (for example, are these supports accessible to all, or are they tailored for use by a specific department or faculty)? \r\n3.\tWhat is the current state of the “community of practice” established by faculty members and graduate students who employ digital data, tools, and methods as part of their work?\r\n4.\tWhat outcomes for digital scholarship practices would faculty members, graduate students, and library staff like to see?\r\n","principal_investigator":"Kris Joseph","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8004,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 18:39:09 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 18:39:09 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2983","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Taylor Nelles-McGee","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8005,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-09-23 18:45:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-09-23 18:45:24 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--2984","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Tarin Karunagoda","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8006,"title":"My pl