ractices-at-a-low-barrier-women-s-agency","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This project uses interviews, focus groups, and document collection to gather data on Sistering's past and present advocacy activities. Sistering is a multiservice agency in Toronto for at-risk, homeless, and marginalized cis women and trans people. Our research questions are: What are the best practices for advocacy activities in this sector? What is the current instititutional capacity of Sistering to engage in advocacy? and How can Sistering build greater institutional capacity for advocacy? This is a community-based research project, partnering Dr. Heather Smyth (Dept of English, University of Waterloo) and coordinators and staff at Sistering to conduct research that will fulfill a need of a community organization. The results of this research will aid Sistering in creating its Advocacy Plan within the Strategic Plan of the organization.","principal_investigator":"Heather Smyth","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"hsmyth@uwaterloo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8109,"title":"My plan (UVic DMP Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-10-07 22:27:31 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-07 22:27:31 UTC","slug":"my-plan-uvic-dmp-template--45","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Amr Farghali","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8111,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-08 13:11:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-08 13:11:51 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3029","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jill Rumore","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8112,"title":"My plan (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2019-10-08 14:47:36 UTC","