52:18 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-10 14:05:18 UTC","slug":"david-s-plan","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"400218730","description":"This research project focuses on the collection and interpretation of soil fluxes at a deciduous and coniferous site. ","principal_investigator":"Yueqian (David) Ma","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"may118@mcmaster.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8137,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-09 15:53:02 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-09 15:53:52 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3046","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"8767","identifier":"098","description":"Test plan","principal_investigator":"Krysha Dukacz","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID","data_contact":"Fred Guipi","funder_name":null},{"id":8138,"title":"Built Environment Influences on Bicycling Behaviour in Hamilton, Ontario","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-09 21:47:58 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-20 19:20:40 UTC","slug":"built-environment-influences-on-bicycling-behaviour-in-hamilton-ontario","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"I am conducting an explanatory sequential mixed methods study to understand and describe how the built environment influences bicycling behaviour and route choice in Hamilton, Ontario.  Most of the current literature that has looked at the attributes of the built environment that influence bicycling for transport is from European countries with a long tradition of such types of travel, and only recently more evidence from North America and Canada in particular has emerged.  For this reason, there is a need to collect local evidence to understand whether the built environment attributes identified in the literature from other countries are relevant or different here in Canada. In the first phase, I will be doing secondary data analysis of bicycle trips in Hamilton collected through the Transportation Tomorrow Survey.  I will develop a Poisson regression model to estimate bicycle travel.  Based on the model analysis, I will conduct bikeability audits in areas across the city that have under- and over-predicted bicycling shares. In the second and final phase, I will conduct semi-structured interviews with local bicyclists to gather their perspectives about how the built environment influences their route choice.  I will use the results of the bikeability audits to structure the interview. ","principal_investigator":"Elise Desjardins","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8139,"title":"The relationship between iron nutrition status and immunity","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-10-10 13:01:04 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-14 15:04:21 UTC","slug":"the-relationship-between-iron-nutrition-status-and-immunity--2","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030337","identifier":"UofG2017-2887","description":"A field trial to determine if anemia influences pig immune response to vaccination. The data are collected in order to perform statistical analysis and proof or disprove the hypothesis that anemic pigs will not produce a strong antibody response to vaccination.","principal_investigator":"Robert Friendship","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"519 824 4129 ext 54022, rfriends@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8140,"title":"Making new friends: The impact of shyness on unfamiliar children's interactions","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-10 14:17:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 15:43:29 UTC","slug":"making-new-friends-the-impact-of-shyness-on-unfamiliar-children-s-interactions","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The goal of the study is to employ a dyadic framework to examine the relations between shyness and interpersonal rapport among newly acquainted peers. Data to be collected include questionnaire measures of temperament and observational measures of dyadic peer interactions.  ","principal_investigator":"Heather Henderson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8141,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-10 15:00:27 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-10 15:00:27 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3049","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Alison  Curtis","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8146,"title":"My plan (York University)","dmptemplate_id":47,"created_at":"2019-10-10 20:14:43 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-10 20:14:43 UTC","slug":"my-plan-york-university--21","organisation_id":45,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Marcia Salmon","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8147,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-10 23:58:52 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-10 23:58:52 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3050","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sumesh Thakur","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8148,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-11 04:42:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 04:42:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3051","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Marcia Salmon","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8149,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-11 15:09:56 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 15:09:56 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3052","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8150,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-11 15:13:52 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 15:39:07 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3053","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"San Francisco System (SFS) Project\r\n","principal_investigator":"Kimie Hara","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8152,"title":"Exploring novel agricultural frontiers","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-10-11 16:48:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-14 21:25:12 UTC","slug":"exploring-novel-agricultural-frontiers","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"499076","identifier":"499076","description":"This research project aims to explore possible new Canadian “agricultural frontiers,” or land that is not currently cultivated but that may become suitable for agriculture due to climate change and new emerging technology. Developing these frontiers is expected to help humanity maintain global food security alongside population growth. However, such significant land use change may also have negative environmental consequences. This research aims to: (1) identify the extent and location of potential agricultural crop-specific frontiers; and (2) identify potential negative environmental consequences such as soil organic carbon loss, soil erosion and habitat loss due to deforestation and cultivation. These issues will be explored by combining climate model outputs with fine spatial scale soil and infrastructure data and technologies thereby providing a spatially explicit analysis of possible agricultural frontiers on various technologies.","principal_investigator":"Evan Fraser","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5124-488X","data_contact":"Rachel Lee, rachell@uoguelph.ca, 519-824-4120x58961","funder_name":null},{"id":8153,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-11 18:13:13 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 18:13:13 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3054","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sarah Sousa","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8155,"title":"Influencing antibiotic use decision making by dairy veterinarians","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-10-11 18:51:33 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 18:56:50 UTC","slug":"influencing-antibiotic-use-decision-making-by-dairy-veterinarians","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030435","identifier":"KTT(RF)2019-10355","description":"The objectives of this project are to determine: i) the potential impact SR research results have on veterinary decision making in Ontario, ii) the best method to translate and transfer antibiotic efficacy research results to veterinarians measured by changes in antimicrobial use decision-making, iii) the best method to translate and transfer teat sealant efficacy research results to veterinarians measured by changes in teat sealant use decision-making. ","principal_investigator":"David Kelton","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-9606-7602","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8156,"title":"Investigating the dynamics of Johne's Disease in Ontario dairy herds (2013-2018)","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-10-11 19:11:22 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 19:14:24 UTC","slug":"investigating-the-dynamics-of-johne-s-disease-in-ontario-dairy-herds-2013-2018","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030467","identifier":"UofG2018-3140","description":"The overall aim of this project is to evaluate the long-term impact of the OJEMAP on JD prevalence and biosecurity practices on Ontario dairy farms. Objectives: 1. Quantify changes in herd-level prevalence of JD by estimating the current herd-level prevalence and comparing it to the prevalence of JD in 2013. 2. Describe changes in control practices and adoption rates of recommended control strategies by repeating the RAMP process with a subset of herds, including herds that had maintained negative status and those that changed in status over the five-year period (negative to positive / positive to negative). 3. Determine which control practices are most effective by using results from Objectives 1 and 2 to compare JD status change to control strategies that were implemented over the long term. 4. Describe barriers to the long-term adoption of recommended disease control management changes by farmers who failed to adopt recommended changes. ","principal_investigator":"David Kelton","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-9606-7602","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8157,"title":"The relationship between iron nutrition status and immunity","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-11 19:20:57 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 19:27:44 UTC","slug":"the-relationship-between-iron-nutrition-status-and-immunity","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"030337","identifier":"UofG2017-2887 ","description":"A field trial to determine if anemia influences pig immune response to vaccination. The data is collected in order to perform statistical analysis and proof or disprove the hypothesis that anemic pigs will not produce a strong antibody response to vaccination.","principal_investigator":"Robert Friendship","principal_investigator_identifier":" 0000-0003-4630-3878","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8158,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-11 21:13:15 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-11 21:13:15 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3056","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Tracy Prowse","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8159,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-12 00:45:40 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-12 00:45:40 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3057","or