d":8169,"title":"Urban Form Research","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-16 14:35:54 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-16 14:59:39 UTC","slug":"urban-form-research","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"Ferrari_McMaster","description":"This research project seeks to investigate how the urban form, the design of the built environment can control and shape the individual’s travel behavior. There is a lack of empirical work on the subject in developing countries, which has different spatial dynamics that could bring other issues to the debate.","principal_investigator":"Tatiana Ferrari","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0003-1234-1235","data_contact":"tatianak.ferrari@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":8170,"title":"My plan (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2019-10-16 14:55:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-16 14:56:00 UTC","slug":"my-plan-memorial-university-of-newfoundland--26","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Jordan jpatterson13@mun.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8171,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-16 15:34:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-22 13:23:31 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3068","organisation_id":27,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The goal of this project is to research and develop drugs for treating motoneuron diseases through a genetic model of Spinal Muscular Atrophy (SMA) and Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS) in zebrafish.  ","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8172,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-16 15:38:16 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-16 15:38:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3069","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jeff Moon","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8174,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-16 16:59:19 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-16 16:59:19 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--421","organisation_id":44,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Maxime Lévesque","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8175,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-16 19:42:46 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-16 19:42:46 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--422","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Pascal Guillot","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8176,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-16 23:49:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-16 23:49:08 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--423","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8177,"title":"Accessibility in the Library: Teaching and Learning","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-17 12:06:36 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-17 12:08:14 UTC","slug":"accessibility-in-the-library-teaching-and-learning","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Lisa Snider, Maggie Neilson, Vincent Grovestine","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Maggie Neilson (maggiejean.neilson@acadiau.ca)","funder_name":null},{"id":8178,"title":"A comprehensive assessment of slow growing chickens: tackling sustainability issues for chicken strains of tomorrow","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-10-17 14:27:56 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-18 13:59:32 UTC","slug":"a-comprehensive-assessment-of-slow-growing-chickens-tackling-sustainability-issues-for-chicken-strains-of-tomorrow","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"499064","identifier":"","description":"This project focuses on bench marking the welfare and productivity of 16 genotypes of broiler chickens. We hypothesize that the growth rate of broiler chickens will relate to their behaviour, physiology, health, mortality and productivity. Phenotypic traits will be characterized for individual birds within genotypes. This database is being created to share phenotypic data to lead to science-based recommendations on better genetics and management of broilers. Data may also be used for individual or all genotypes for modelling nutrient utilization, and for performing a life cycle assessment to maximize sustainability.  \r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Tina Widowski","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3274-7558","data_contact":"Stephanie Torrey, 519 824 4120 x53660; storrey@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8179,"title":"The Functionality of Outdoor Classrooms in the Simcoe County District School Board","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-17 15:18:51 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-17 15:27:58 UTC","slug":"the-functionality-of-outdoor-classrooms-in-the-simcoe-county-district-school-board","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"- to determine how educators in the Simcoe County District School Board are using outdoor classrooms: for what subjects and/or school priorities and personal development goals; at what grade levels; how the outdoors serves their needs (functionality); how often they use the outdoor classrooms, and more\r\n- after the initial survey data is collected, it will be used to identify educators interested in and worthy of being involved in semi-structured interviews to delve deeper into the functionality of the outdoor classrooms","principal_investigator":"Loretta Sbrocca","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"sbrocc1@uwindsor.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8180,"title":"Human Dimensions of the Digital Agricultural Revolution","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-10-17 19:59:47 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-14 21:25:19 UTC","slug":"human-dimensions-of-the-digital-agricultural-revolution","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"499077","identifier":"499077","description":"The world is on the cusp of a digital agricultural revolution that promises the ability to produce more food with less environmental impact. The overarching research objective of this project is to better understand the human dimensions of the digital agricultural revolution. To meet this core objective, we will collect text records of interviews, surveys, and focus groups to answer the following questions:\r\n\r\n(1) How do members of rural communities, focusing on producers: (a) use digital technologies; (b) perceive benefits and barriers to these technologies; and (c) think policy and research can enable them to realize benefits and reduce barriers?\r\n(2) What would a national data governance framework for the agri-food sector look like? \r\n(3) How can we develop new pedagogical tools to ensure that the post-secondary system in Canada is equipped to train the next generation of agri-food thought leaders? Student experiences of the new Food from Thought graduate cohort program will also be evaluated for insight into question 3.\r\n","principal_investigator":"Evan Fraser","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5124-488X","data_contact":"Rachel Lee, 519-824-4120x58961, rachell@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8181,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-17 22:05:35 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-17 22:05:35 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3072","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8182,"title":"Generational Differences in Travel Behavior","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-18 07:00:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-24 01:35:57 UTC","slug":"generational-differences-in-travel-behavior","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"NA","identifier":"NA","description":"My PhD research will utilize the data which will be collected by Dr. Bruce Newbold (Principal Investigator) under the project \"Automobility in Canada: An Intergenrational Perspective\" sponsored by Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council (SSHRC). The PhD research will explore two questions: \r\n1. How is the travel behavior evolving among generations (particularly among baby boomers and millennials)? 2. What are the factors that influencing each generations travel behavior in terms of trip frequency, trip purpose, mode choice, trip duration and trip length and how do these factors differ between and within generations?\r\n\r\nThe primary data will be collected in two phases.\r\nPhase 1: A questionnaire survey asking socio-economic conditions, travel behavior and preferences towards residential location and transportation options. \r\nPhase 2: Completion of a 7 day travel diary using a GPS device. The dairy will include detail information on travel such as travel duration, trip purpose, trip mode, etc. The GPS device will be used to collect data on the exact activity points (e.g. work, shopping, leisure) which will be used to calculate distances. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Shaila Jamal (Student Investigator)","principal_investigator_identifier":"NA","data_contact":"NA","funder_name":null},{"id":8183,"title":"The number of siblings, education level, psychological state of adult IBD patient","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2019-10-18 12:47:42 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-30 17:13:38 UTC","slug":"the-number-of-siblings-education-level-psychological-state-of-adult-ibd-patient","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The original purpose of the data being collected is to determine predictors of outcomes and to optimize management of various aspects of IBD.\r\nMy specific aim of this secondary use of the original data is to see whether the number of siblings in the family would influence the educational and psychological status of IBD patients.  ","principal_investigator":"Qian Liu","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"qianl@myumanitoba.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":8184,"title":"Plan de gestion des données - Recherche Vanessa Tanguay","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-18 13:33:48 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-18 13:34:47 UTC","slug":"plan-de-gestion-des-donnees-recherche-vanessa-tanguay","organisation_id":13,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Vanessa Tanguay","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8185,"title":"Travel behavior on the Eastern Corridor in Madrid","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-18 15:21:07 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-20 20:25:09 UTC","slug":"travel-behavior-on-the-eastern-corridor-in-madrid","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"BES-2016-077150","identifier":"SPIP2017-02160","description":"The main aim of this Project is to address the problem of recurrent congestion suffered by drivers at the accesses to the city of Madrid, Spain.\r\nMadrid Metropolitan Area is connected to Madrid City Centre through a radial network of six main transportation corridors. All these corridors have free highways (named A1 to A6), rail services, and suburban bus services. Furthermore, four of these corridors have an additional alternative, a toll highway (named R2 to R5) parallel to the existing free highways. Toll sections generally have excess capacity whereas drivers in toll-free sections experience congestion during peak hours.\r\nBased on a case study, this project seeks to determine to what extent it is possible to change the behaviour of passengers in the corridor to reduce the use of the free highway in favour of the other options (toll highway, bus, metro). To this end, a survey was carried out on different transport demand management measures among the dwellers of the Eastern corridor. ","principal_investigator":"Fernando Romero","principal_investigator_identifier":"B-6881-2019","data_contact":"fernando.romero@upm.es","funder_name":null},{"id":8186,"title":"My ANTH demo plan ","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2019-10-18 19:54:14 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-18 19:55:05 UTC","slug":"my-anth-demo-plan","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Demo for 3D project ","principal_investigator":"Kathleen  Matthews","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8187,"title":"Firm level barriers to entry into export markets in the food processing Industry","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-10-20 03:18:12 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-20 03:28:02 UTC","slug":"firm-level-barriers-to-entry-into-export-markets-in-the-food-processing-industry","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"UofG2018-3289","description":"To examine the barriers to entry into export markets, and to assess the importance of firm dynamics for export market survival and growth, we will use data from two administrative databases from Statistics Canada. The primary data set is Trade by Exporter Characteristics (TEC) dataset. The TEC data allow us to examine the value, volume, and destination of exports at the transaction level. We will also use the National Accounts Longitudinal Microdata File in order to examine firm characteristics (i.e., productivity, ownership status, foreign investment). To provide descriptive analysis of the challenges and opportunities that Canadian face on the foreign markets, we will use the 2017 Survey of Innovation and Business Strategy (SIBS 2017) that looks at \"affiliations with foreign businesses, imports and exports of goods or services as well as at challenges and opportunities faced by Canadian enterprises to connect to global markets.\"","principal_investigator":"Getu Hailu","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8188,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-20 12:07:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-20 12:07:08 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3075","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Michaela Rizzolli","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8189,"title":"My plan (NRC Data Management Plan template Draft)","dmptemplate_id":33,"created_at":"2019-10-20 17:41:24 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-20 17:41:24 UTC","slug":"my-plan-nrc-data-management-plan-template-draft--18","organisation_id":39,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8190,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-21 11:19:03 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-21 11:19:03 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--425","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Claude Nozères","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8191,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-21 11:19:35 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-21 11:19:35 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--426","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Claude Nozères","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8192,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-10-21 11:20:25 UTC","updated_at":"2019-10-21 11:20:25 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--427","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":n