:null,"principal_investigator":"Vrati Mehra","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8367,"title":"My plan (York University)","dmptemplate_id":47,"created_at":"2019-11-04 15:37:20 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-04 15:37:20 UTC","slug":"my-plan-york-university--40","organisation_id":45,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Ying Hui Hsieh","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8368,"title":"Investigating the soil microbiome to understand soil health and soil ecosystem services","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2019-11-04 17:11:41 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-15 18:44:44 UTC","slug":"investigating-the-soil-microbiome-to-understand-soil-health-and-soil-ecosystem-services","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Understanding the soil microbiome is essential to the stewardship of ecosystem services provided by soils, such as soil fertility (for food, fibre and fuel production), water quality, resistance to erosion and climate mitigation through reduced feedbacks to climate change. Microbial communities play a central role in virtually every biogeochemical cycle on earth. While soil microbial diversity and activity can be characterized using molecular tools, quantitative linkages to ecosystem function are often difficult. We need a better understanding of microbial activity and ultimately, biogeochemical cycling, in order to predict soil ecosystem responses to changes in climate, vegetation or land management.\r\n\r\nAn array of scientific approaches, including short-term field studies and long-term field experiments will be used to investigate microbial drivers of soil ecosystem services and soil health. Over the next two years, metagenomics and metatranscriptomics (i.e., high throughput sequencing approaches applied to environmental samples) will be used to provide comprehensive and quantitative descriptions of the taxonomic and functional diversity using the total pool of nucleic acids and identify couplings between environmental conditions and the microbial community composition and function. \r\nThe research will:\r\n(1) Assess the impact of sustainable and resilient agricultural practices on the functional diversity of microbes in the plant-soil interface;\r\n(2) Estimate tradeoffs of diversified cropping systems by comparing in situ measurements of microbial activity to greenhouse gas emissions under field conditions.\r\n.\r\nThis research will contribute to our understanding of the ecosystem tradeoffs required to maximize productivity in agroecosystems in order to meet the demands of a global population while minimizing impacts on soil, air, and water quality, recognizing that we are also experiencing unseen climate variability and environmental change.\r\n\r\n","principal_investigator":"Kari Dunfield","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8369,"title":"Ontario's Happy Planet Index","dmptemplate_id":47,"created_at":"2019-11-04 19:41:38 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-04 19:42:54 UTC","slug":"ontario-s-happy-planet-index","organisation_id":45,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Jason Robinson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8370,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-11-04 22:03:40 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-04 22:03:40 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3152","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Vivek Jadon","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8372,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-11-05 16:53:08 UTC","updated_at":"2019-11-05 16:53:08 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--453","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":nul