 and Integration","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2019-12-10 18:23:05 UTC","updated_at":"2019-12-10 18:36:49 UTC","slug":"the-canada-excellence-research-chair-cerc-program-in-migration-and-integration","organisation_id":26,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The Canada Excellence Research Chair (CERC) program in Migration and Integration (2019-2026) aims to produce innovative and usable knowledge exploring the links between migration and post-migration processes, forced and voluntary mobility, internal and international migration, the role of countries of origin and transit as well as of non-state stakeholders at local, national and international level, in both migration management and migrant integration. We shall pay special attention to Canadian realities but will also engage in comparative research with and among other countries in different world regions.  The program is supported by a $10 million Tri-Agency grant from the Social Sciences and Humanities Research Council (SSHRC), the Natural Sciences and Engineering Research Council (NSERC) and the Canadian Institutes of Health Research (CIHR). The program is housed at Ryerson University and affiliated with the Department of Sociology. \r\n\r\nThe CERC research agenda is structured along seven broad Research Streams which however should be considered as closely inter-related and flexible: \r\n\r\n1. The Governance of Migration in a Globalizing World \r\n2. ‘Southern’ perspectives on Migration and Migrant Integration \r\n3. Cities, Migration, Asylum \r\n4. Rethinking Settlement and Integration in a Comparative Perspective \r\n5. Temporary Migration: A Critical Assessment \r\n6. Managing Labour Migration in the 21st century \r\n7. (Political) Narratives on Migration \r\nand an interdisciplinary Data and Methods Lab.\r\n","principal_investigator":"Anna Triandafyllidou","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Anna Triandafyllidou","funder_name":null},{"id":8609,"title":"My plan (Portage