10 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--483","organisation_id":42,"grant_number":"892-2019-2013","identifier":"Subventions d'engagement partenarial individuelles","description":"Objectif principal du projet est, en partenariat avec l'OOAQ, de réaliser l'évaluation des impacts à court\r\nterme et du retour sur l'investissement d'un programme de mentorat visant à soutenir la pratique\r\nprofessionnelle de nouveaux membres à l'OOAQ.","principal_investigator":"Marie-Eve  Caty","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8709,"title":"Répartition géographique du du t/d non affriqué devant voyelle haute dans l'est du Canada en 2021","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-01-23 14:45:41 UTC","updated_at":"2021-02-19 18:25:57 UTC","slug":"repartition-geographique-du-du-t-d-non-affrique-devant-voyelle-haute-dans-l-est-du-canada-en-2021","organisation_id":29,"grant_number":"s.a.","identifier":"","description":"ce projet de recherche vise à cartographier la prononciation non affriquée des consonnes alvéo-dentales devant voyelle haute au Québec en 2021. La collecte de données se fera au moyen d'une courte entrevue enregistrée portant sur un sujet linguistique relevant davantage de l'opinion afin d'inciter les participants à s'exprimer naturellement.","principal_investigator":"Mireille Léger-Rousseau","principal_investigator_identifier":"ORCID","data_contact":"chercheur@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":8710,"title":"Guiding the accurate assessment of general practitioners’ unperceived learning needs","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-01-23 14:45:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-01-27 00:49:31 UTC","slug":"guiding-the-accurate-assessment-of-general-practitioners-unperceived-learning-needs","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This study will investigate a novel approach to designing assessments along the continuum of professional development/ continuing medical education. \r\n\r\nRQ: Can an operational analysis of resesarch resources guide an effective needs assessment strategy?\r\n\r\nData is being collected from subject matter experts (SMEs) to be analyzed using the the analytic heirchary process (AHP). The AHP is a tool that can incorporate multiple quantitative and qualitative criteria in a meaningful and rational way. It is a well established process in operations research that begins with a problem being decomposed into a hierarchy of criteria. \r\n\r\nThe problem that this research aims to address is the lack of resource management reporting with needs assessment evaluation strategies in the field of continued professional development/ medical education (CPD/CME). \r\n\r\nCriteria under analysis will be cost, time, population, and research personnel. These four factors were chosen as they are the main components of a traditional project proposal and thereby are established independent variables that must be defined in a formal protocol.  \r\n\r\nThe AHP produces a logical hierarchy that decision makers can use to systematically assess a group of alternatives. Founded in evidence from previous literature reviews on the subject, there are four alternative methods that a CPD/CME researcher might use to employ a needs assessment: (1) a knowledge assessment (2) a competence assessment (3) a performance evaluation and (4) an environmental scan. \r\n\r\nThe AHP analysis works by making pair-wise comparisons for each of the chosen criteria. This comparison may use concrete data from the alternatives or human judgments as a way to input subjacent information. In this study, subject matter experts (SMEs) in the field of CPD/CME will be recruited to develop the pair-wise comparison matrices. \r\n\r\n to quantify the dependence of needs assessment strategies on different research resources.","principal_investigator":"Meghan Lofft/ Heather Armson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8711,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","d