g environment which permits the mashing up of traditional archival research with existing open data resources. It re-envisages how historical scholars might think about data and historical phenomena, and the balance between automated and traditional manual archival labour.","principal_investigator":"Matthew Milner","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8854,"title":"19th C NL Women's Imaginative Lit","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2020-02-21 13:25:39 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 14:07:09 UTC","slug":"19th-c-nl-women-s-imaginative-lit","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"My PhD dissertation project (English Literature). I will be critically reading and analyzing texts from the 19th century (up until WW1) and using journal articles and books (secondary texts) to aid in my analysis. ","principal_investigator":"Heather C. O'Brien","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8855,"title":"My plan (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2020-02-21 13:26:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 13:26:20 UTC","slug":"my-plan-memorial-university-of-newfoundland--47","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Vesna Kerezi","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8856,"title":"OFI Module I Informing Governance Responses in a Changing Ocean","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2020-02-21 13:35:07 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 13:42:17 UTC","slug":"ofi-module-i-informing-governance-responses-in-a-changing-ocean","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Ocean Frontier Institute's 'Informing Governance Responses in a Changing Ocean' is a collaborative research initiative that examines the consequences of social, ecological, economic and institutional changes for the future of fisheries, coastal communities and the economy of Newfoundland and Labrador, Canada. It also explores alternative options for governments and other governing actors to respond to these changes in order to help achieve a sustainable future.\r\n\r\nThe first phase of the project hosted a Taking Stock Dialogue, bringing together stakeholders from research, government, industry and the community to appraise changes that occurred (e.g. regulatory, industry, resources) leading up to and since the groundfish  moratoria, critically assess current fisheries, and identify where research is required to fill knowledge gaps.\r\n\r\nThe research program includes five projects critical to informing current and future governance:\r\n\r\n1) Access to Resources & Markets\r\n2) Recruitment, Training & Retention\r\n3) Perceptions, Values & Knowledge\r\n4) Marine Health & Safety\r\n5) Vulnerability & Viability\r\n\r\nThe final phase of the project will use the research results as a basis to develop and host a Getting it Right Dialogue, where stakeholders will be invited to discuss options for Newfoundland and Labrador's fisheries and to develop short- and long-term governance responses.","principal_investigator":"Ratana Chuenpagdee","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Mirella de Oliveira Leis","funder_name":null},{"id":8857,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-02-21 13:36:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 13:36:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3400","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sharon Hewitt","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8858,"title":"My plan (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2020-02-21 13:37:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 13:37:53 UTC","slug":"my-plan-memorial-university-of-newfoundland--49","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"krishna roy","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8859,"title":"My plan (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2020-02-21 13:50:29 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 13:50:29 UTC","slug":"my-plan-memorial-university-of-newfoundland--50","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sanaz Nabavian","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8860,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-02-21 16:09:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 16:09:13 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--504","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Stéphanie Dudonné","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":8862,"title":"CONOC Data Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-02-21 17:34:27 UTC","updated_at":"2020-03-31 16:20:21 UTC","slug":"conoc-data-management-plan","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Eric Oliver","principal_investigator_identifier":"Breanna Bishop","data_contact":"Breanna Bishop","funder_name":null},{"id":8863,"title":"SURGE workshop plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-02-21 17:35:47 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 17:36:56 UTC","slug":"surge-workshop-plan","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Erin MacPherson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8864,"title":"Comp1_Tang","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-02-21 17:35:48 UTC","updated_at":"2020-03-02 14:50:00 UTC","slug":"comp1_tang","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Full Title: \"Knowledge of Vaping, Perceived Harms, and its Association with Nicotine and Cannabis Use\"\r\n\r\nVaping has become a common form of young adult consumption of tobacco, nicotine, and cannabis. Despite the danger posed by the increased prevalence of vaping in young adults, research on the benefits and harms of vaping is underdeveloped. The purpose of the proposed study is to evaluate the role of cognitive risk factors in predicting increased vaping behavior and greater cannabis/tobacco use disorder severity, using the Theory of Planned Behavior as a guiding framework. Dalhousie university students (N = 183) will be recruited online via the Department of Psychology Research Participation system (SONA) and campus advertisement to complete an online survey on Survey Monkey. Using hierarchical multiple regression, the proposed analysis will evaluate the incremental utility of attitudes, social norms, and impulsivity in explaining frequency of vaping and cannabis/tobacco use disorder. The results of this project will provide the first empirical data on factual knowledge about vaping in young adults, which may facilitate increased vaping behavior given that inaccurate beliefs about the harms of vaping act as permissive information for continued use by providing a self-assessment of one’s own cannabis/nicotine use habits as safe or even beneficial.\r\n","principal_investigator":"Karen Tang","principal_investigator_identifier":"http://orcid.org/0000-0001-8981-1077","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8865,"title":"Surge Workshop plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-02-21 17:35:48 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 17:37:08 UTC","slug":"surge-workshop-plan--2","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Pallavi","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8866,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-02-21 17:35:51 UTC","updated_at":"2020-02-21 17:35:51 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3406","organisation_id":15,"grant_