 at the university and shared collection development, consistent with the library’s Information Resources Strategy. ","principal_investigator":"Racquel Devison","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Heather McMllen","funder_name":null},{"id":8998,"title":"FES stroke","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-04-03 14:31:18 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-03 14:31:54 UTC","slug":"fes-stroke","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Sarah Bailey","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":8999,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-04-03 16:19:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-03 16:19:52 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3484","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Patrick LeClair","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9000,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-04-05 01:29:17 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-05 01:29:17 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3485","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Aleks Spasevski","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9001,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-04-05 18:30:34 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-05 18:30:34 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3486","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9002,"title":"My plan (UVic DMP Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2020-04-07 18:18:42 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-07 18:18:42 UTC","slug":"my-plan-uvic-dmp-template--77","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Ralph Evins","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9004,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-04-08 07:26:55 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-08 07:26:55 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3488","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jonathan Jacobs","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9005,"title":"Clinicians’ Moral Experience and Moral Distinctions in Philosophical Bioethics","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-04-08 13:58:34 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-08 14:05:35 UTC","slug":"clinicians-moral-experience-and-moral-distinctions-in-philosophical-bioethics","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"With the recent introduction of legislation allowing for doctor-assisted death, age-old philosophical debates surrounding death and dying are assuming a new and urgent importance for doctors and patients. As end of life approaches, decision-making around issues of treatment, non-treatment, and palliative care become fraught with both emotion and confusion. What is needed is a clearer framework for such decision-making, one that draws from the insights of philosophers and bioethicists, but also from the experiences of clinicians. This project’s broad research goal is to take initial steps towards developing such a framework, one which allows the moral awareness of clinicians in end-of-life care to inform the philosophical-bioethical understanding of the distinction between killing and allowing to die, and which locates ways in which, conversely, bioethical debate can help inform clinical practice in end-of-life care. The four specific objectives of this project are\r\n1. to use a literature review and conceptual analysis to clearly delineate the main contested issues in bioethical debates surrounding the distinction between killing and allowing to die;\r\n2. to assess the subjective moral experience of internal medicine physicians involved in practices leading to patient death (withdrawing treatment and administering Medical Assistance in Dying);\r\n3. to revisit and refine existing conceptual debates (Obj 1) in light of the moral experience of internal medicine physicians (Obj 2);\r\n4. to develop, based on the results of Obj 3, a set of guidelines for ethical reflection for use in the instruction of internal medicine physicians in residency.","principal_investigator":"Andrew Stumpf","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Zack MacDonald, zack.macdonald@uwaterloo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9006,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-04-08 14:48:35 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-08 14:48:35 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3490","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Michelle Anagnostou","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9007,"title":"OFI Module E - Colleen McBride","dmptemplate_id":54,"created_at":"2020-04-08 14:54:02 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-29 17:11:22 UTC","slug":"ofi-module-e-colleen-mcbride","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"0000-0001-7742-9882","description":"","principal_investigator":"Colleen McBride, cemcbride@mun.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Sara Jenkins, sara.jenkins@mun.ca, 709-743-6339","funder_name":null},{"id":9008,"title":"OFI Module E - Maryam Beheshti Foroutani","dmptemplate_id":54,"created_at":"2020-04-08 14:58:47 UTC","updated_at":"2020-04-23 12:52:17 UTC","slug":"ofi-module-e-maryam-beheshti-foroutani","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Maryam Beheshti Foroutani, mbf613@mun.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6743-2711","data_contact":