nd-after-covid-19","organisation_id":48,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The purpose of the study is to explore Canadian adults’ everyday practices before and during the COVID-19 pandemic as well as future expectations once things return to normal. In particular, the study aims to understand the racialization effect of COVID-19 on people’s daily encounters and the types of microaggressions happening during the pandemic. Questions will examine participant’s everyday practices such as where we choose to eat, where we shop and people’s perception and reactions to each other in everyday encounters such as the workplace, public transit, grocery stores, hospitals, and other public spaces. In an ethnically diverse country like Canada, understanding the impact of microaggressions that result from an event like COVID-19 should be addressed since it will impact our social well-being and inclusiveness as a community both in the short and long term. \r\n\r\nResearch questions:\r\n1. What type of microaggressions were\r\nhappening prior to COVID-19?\r\n2. What types of microaggressions are\r\nhappening during COVID-19?\r\n3. Who engages in and who has\r\nexperienced microaggressions?\r\n4. What are the implications of these\r\nmicroaggressions post COVID-19?","principal_investigator":"Dr. Karla Dhungana Sainju and Dr. Olga Marques","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9101,"title":"CONCOR-KIDS","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-01 14:59:44 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-01 15:17:47 UTC","slug":"concor-kids","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Bryan","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9102,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-01 19:10:08 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-01 19:10:08 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3537","organisation_id":38,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Sharissa Hantke","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9103,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-01 19:40:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-01 19:40:30 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3538","organisation_id":11,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"lina harper","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9104,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-01 21:01:14 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-01 21:01:14 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3539","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9105,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-05-01 21:03:46 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-01 21:03:46 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--564","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9106,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-04 13:44:38 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-04 13:44:38 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--524","organisation_id":29,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Ély Charette-Dussault","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9107,"title":"Investigation and Analysis Associated with Reducing GHG Emissions on CAF Bases","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-04 15:10:16 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-04 15:11:48 UTC","slug":"investigation-and-analysis-associated-with-reducing-ghg-emissions-on-caf-bases","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The Department of National Defence (DND) is the largest emitter of greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions within the Canadian Federal Government,  compromising 49% of emissions. The Greening Government Strategy aims to reduce total emissions by 40% by the year 2030, and 80% by the year 2050. This research proposes the use of a four (4) step mixed-methods methodology to investigate GHG emissions at Canadian Armed Forces (CAF) Bases in an effort to reduce Canada’s total GHG emissions. Specifically this work will: \r\n1.\tQuantify GHG emissions using a comprehensive GHG accounting framework and accurate data collection methods; \r\n2.\tDelineate factors influencing GHG emissions through open-ended interviews;\r\n3.\tIntegrate qualitative and quantitative data to analyze all GHG sources at CAF bases; and,\r\n4.\tUse analysis to inform a framework of solutions that will reduce GHG emissions. \r\nUsing this methodology, optimization strategies will be specific, applicable, and achievable. This research will prioritize the unique range and activities of CAF bases including challenging climatic and geographic factors. The objective of this research is to provide a framework and tools for reducing GHGs at bases across Canada. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Elizabeth Arif","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"11eiha@queensu.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9108,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-04 19:08:42 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-04 19:08:42 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3541","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Deepa Upadhyaya","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9109,"title":"My plan (UVic DMP Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2020-05-05 15:23:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-05 15:23:30 UTC","slu