":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9115,"title":"Zulu Kingdom Archaeological Project","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2020-05-07 01:55:12 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-07 02:01:14 UTC","slug":"zulu-kingdom-archaeological-project","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"435-2020-0663","identifier":"52205","description":"Archaeological research project combining archaeology, history, archaeological science, and genetic research to develop a better understanding of the political economy of the Zulu Kingdom.","principal_investigator":"Kent Fowler","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-8181-7885","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9116,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-07 05:33:19 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-07 05:34:14 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3545","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Remote Delivery","principal_investigator":"Ellen Wang","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9117,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-07 13:58:11 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-07 13:58:11 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--527","organisation_id":44,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Florent Parent","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9118,"title":"Portraiture","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-07 15:44:05 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-07 15:47:01 UTC","slug":"portraiture","organisation_id":29,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Olivier Arvisais","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9119,"title":"My plan (Dalhousie University Generic Plan)","dmptemplate_id":56,"created_at":"2020-05-07 16:00:23 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-07 16:00:23 UTC","slug":"my-plan-dalhousie-university-generic-plan--9","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"James Barker","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9120,"title":"Bio-optical proxies of phytoplankton abundance, physiological status, and community composition. ","dmptemplate_id":56,"created_at":"2020-05-07 17:01:55 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 14:56:53 UTC","slug":"bio-optical-proxies-of-phytoplankton-abundance-physiological-status-and-community-composition","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"Discovery Grants Program","description":"As written in Grant proposal - Phytoplankton are single-celled marine and freshwater plants that can be cultivated as sources of\r\nvaluable natural products. These include lipids (essential nutrients like omega-6 fatty acids but also\r\ntriacylgylerides, the precursors of biodiesel), proteins that can be used in feedstocks, antioxidants\r\n(carotenoids and flavonoids), and potential pharmaceuticals. Mass culture of phytoplankton has also been\r\ntested as a means of treating wastewaters that are high in nutrients to remediate eutrophication in\r\nwatersheds and coastal waters. Coastal eutrophication is responsible for hypoxia and an increased\r\nincidence of harmful algal blooms worldwide. Both are environmentally and economically costly.\r\nMany phytoplankton that produce high-value compounds can be grown mixotrophically, a mixed\r\nnutritional mode in which the cells are both autotrophic (photosynthetic) and heterotrophic (utilizing\r\nlabile organic compounds). Mixotrophy can greatly increase growth rates are cell yields but is poorly\r\nunderstood. Consequently, screening for optimal conditions proceeds by trial and error.\r\nThis project will develop a conceptual framework for predicting mixotrophic growth and cell\r\ncomposition as a function of light intensity, temperature, and nutrient availability by extending a widelyused\r\nmodel, the Dynamic Balance model. This would define growth optima for the species used to\r\nextend the model, maximizing yield of three high-value compounds. It would also provide a means to\r\nfocus optimization of conditions for strains producing other valuable compounds in the future.\r\nBacterial contamination of mixotrophic culture is more-or-less inevitable and the bacteria can outcompete\r\nthe phytoplankton for the organic substrates and can cause mass mortality. Suppression of\r\nbacterial growth without inhibiting growth of the phytoplankton is therefore essential for economicallyfeasible\r\ncultivation. This project will test use of a proven technology, ultraviolet-C radiation, as a\r\ndifferential stressor that could inhibit bacterial growth without affecting the phytoplankton.\r\nLast, many valuable products are up-regulated under conditions of stress. Successful cultivation\r\nassessing when the culture has reached the optimum condition for harvesting. Bio-optical techniques are\r\nideal for this as they are sensitive to changes in cell composition and function, are non-destructive, and\r\ncan be used in real time. This project will develop and ground-truth bio-optical signatures that would\r\nassess readiness for harvest of cells producing high-value compounds.\r\nThe enhanced production and more efficient screening of strains will facilitate next-generation\r\ncultivation of phytoplankton as cell factories for targeted natural products and as means of remediating\r\ncontaminated wastewaters. This would translate to a novel form of aquaculture and to clearer coastal and\r\ninland waters in Canada and worldwide.","principal_investigator":"Dr. Hugh MacIntyre","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Cat London ","funder_name":null},{"id":9121,"title":"Herbicides and cover crops for improved corn establishment _ Alliance – Tier I ","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-05-07 21:37:44 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-17 20:49:51 UTC","slug":"herbicides-and-cover-crops-for-improved-corn-establishment-_-alliance-tier-i","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"UG-T1-2020-100098","description":"One challenge with cover crops is to maximise their growth without\r\nreducing the yield of the main crops. For example, delaying termination of a\r\nrye cover crop and planting green maximizes biomass production but may\r\naffect corn establishment. Subsequent variable results have been attributed\r\nto causes such as rye allelopathy, N capture or increased root diseases.\r\nAnother factor that has not been considered is the possibility that corn\r\nplants emerging in the presence of a green rye cover crop may be impacted\r\nbecause of altered light being reflected by the green tissues.\r\nAnother approach to cover crops that warrants examinations is the variable\r\nestablishment of various species when interseeded into corn which may be\r\ndue to the use of residual herbicides in PRE- or early POST-emergence.\r\nKnowing which corn herbicides have enough residual to impact cover crops\r\nand determining species sensitivity to specific products would allow for\r\noptimisation of interseeding.","principal_investigator":"François Tardif","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0003-3023-1937","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9122,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-07 23:00:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-07 23:00:52 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3546","organisation_id":38,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Kevin Read","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9123,"title":"Women’s Advanced Risk Assessment in Manitoba (WARM) Hearts – Examining biomarkers of frailty and cardiovascular health in middle aged and older women","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2020-05-08 16:57:22 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-08 18:23:36 UTC","slug":"women-s-advanced-risk-assessment-in-manitoba-warm-hearts-examining-biomarkers-of-frailty-and-cardiovascular-health-in-middle-aged-and-older-women","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"WARM Hearts is a prospective cohort study following 1000 Manitoban women over the age of 55 without history of cardiac illness for a 5 year period after screening. The primary objective of this study is to test the ability of novel cardiovascular disease prognostic tools to identify women at risk for future cardiovascular disease. The secondary objective of this study is to identify novel cardiovascular disease biomarkers that may indicate a person is at increased risk for cardiovascular disease.","principal_investigator":"Todd Duhamel","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"James Ducas, Study Coordinator Faculty of Kinesiology and Recreation Management University of Manitoba","funder_name":null},{"id":9124,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-08 17:07:31 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-08 17:07:31 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3547","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Julia Kimball","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9125,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-08 18:22:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-08 18:22:26 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--529","organisation_id":44,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Patrick Bittner Lamy","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9126,"title":"Narratives of Indigenous Peoples and Resource Development","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-05-08 18:39:27 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-08 18:46:47 UTC","slug":"narratives-of-indigenous-peoples-and-resource-development","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"A database of the varying First Nations, Inuit, and Metis perspectives of nonrenewable resource extraction as depicted by their own media. I am using interpretive research methods under the training of my supervisor to apply discourse, narrative, and image analysis. Using 7 different Indigenous owned and reported information sources with texts that are published between 2010 and 2020 to establish a recent historical context of the Indigenous assertions. The expected outcomes are a comparison and contrast between the perspectives of First Nations, Inuit, and Metis peoples to defy and contradict the narrative of Indigenous peoples in Canadian popular media. This research extends into Anthropology, Sociology, Political Science, and Native Studies to combine concepts that critically analyze how the stereotypes suppress and homogenize Indigenous perspectives in the mainstream media. By learning about these issues we can incorporate Indigenous ways of knowing to possibly improve the transition to renewable energy sources in Canada and make Indigenous stereotypes illegitimate. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Meagan McLay","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9127,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-11 13:25:17 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-11 13:25:17 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3548","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Lita O'Halloran","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9128,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-12 02:43:08 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-12 02:43:08 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3549","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Erin Clary","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9129,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-12 18:14:54 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-12 18:14:54 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3550","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9130,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-12 18:18:08 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-12 18:18:08 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3551","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Erin Clary","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9131,"title":"Reproducibility in astrophysics","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-12 18:18:12 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 16:14:21 UTC","slug":"reproducibility-in-astrophysics","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This is a case study of computational reproducibility in HPC - a use case in relativistic astrophysics and gravitational physics\". The goal of this project is, with the use of an open, community-driven software platform of core computational tools, to develop and implement practices in managing and curating both dataset and scientific software for re-use.","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"Qian Zhang","data_contact":"zhangqian06@gmail.com","funder_name":null},{"id":9132,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-12 21:42:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-12 21:42:26 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3553","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9133,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-05-13 14:35:46 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 14:35:46 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--130","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Rebecca Moore","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9134,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-05-13 15:31:39 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 15:31:39 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--834","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9136,"title":"Narumi Taniguchi","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-13 18:26:37 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 20:12:39 UTC","slug":"narumi-taniguchi","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"N/A","identifier":"N/A","description":"","principal_investigator":"Narumi Taniguchi","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Narumi Taniguchi","funder_name":null},{"id":9137,"title":"Aspiration Pneumonia Data collection","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-05-13 19:12:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 19:13:27 UTC","slug":"aspiration-pneumonia-data-collection","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Tom McLaughlin","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"katie.hynes@alumni.ubc.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9138,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-05-13 20:24:45 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 20:24:45 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--566","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Adriane Peak","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9139,"title":"Survey on Systematic Reviews in the Social Sciences & Humanities","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2020-05-13 20:56:11 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 21:01:23 UTC","slug":"survey-on-systematic-reviews-in-the-social-sciences-humanities","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"We will survey HSS librarians to determine a) if they are being asked to support systematic reviews b) whether they feel confident doing so, and c) if this activity is supported/encouraged by their library administration.","principal_investigator":"Me-Linh Le, Janice Winkler, Christine Neilson","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9140,"title":"Aman Hussain ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-13 21:10:40 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 21:11:03 UTC","slug":"aman-hussain","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Aman Hussain ","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Aman Hussain ","funder_name":null},{"id":9141,"title":"BioProducts Institute Generic","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-05-13 21:19:41 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-13 21:22:35 UTC","slug":"bioproducts-institute-generic","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"BioProducts Institute administrative data related to the operation of the institute","principal_investigator":"Barb Conway","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9142,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-05-14 15:24:36 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-14 15:28:23 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--131","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"UofG2017-2930","description":"The Healthy Menu Choices Act introduced regulation requiring the posting of calorie information in food chains with more than twenty outlets in Ontario. The objective is to encourage informed and, ideally, healthier choices for food that is ready for consumption. The results of previous research have been equivocal with respect to the effectiveness of presenting calorie information on menus. Our approach (using eye-tracking technology and individual participants) allows us to evaluate not only the overall impact of menu labeling but also the differences between individuals, the impact of specific different presentations of information, and the process through which individuals are making the decision. We will also evaluate a number of “nudges” to improve the response to the health information on menus.\r\nA second (unstated) objective of the regulation is to perhaps nudge restaurant companies to make changes to menu items to improve the overall quality of the menu from a health perspective. The second element of our proposed study will provide insight into changes in menus that have arisen due to the labeling requirements. This study provides an opportunity to develop a better understanding of both the effectiveness of the current policy and potential approaches to improving the outcomes.\r\n","principal_investigator":"Mike von Massow","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Mike von Massow","funder_name":null},{"id":9143,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-14 18:31:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-14 18:31:30 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3557","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Daisy Zhang","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9144,"title":"Plant response to herbivory","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-14 19:10:24 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-15 18:59:48 UTC","slug":"plant-response-to-herbivory","organisation_id":12,"grant_number":"NSF XX-XX-XX","identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3771-2450","description":"We are studying the mechanisms and ecological consequences of plants’ induced responses to herbivore damage. Specifically, we are looking at the impact on pollinators of herbivore-induced changes in volatile organic compounds emitted by plants. Using a single species of\r\nplant growing in the field, we are trying to find a correlation between between herbivory and fruit set or herbivory and pollination. This will be accomplished by performing experiments in the field, such as adding herbivores, or adding a plant hormone, or removing visual cues from the plant.","principal_investigator":"Danielle Dennie","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3771-2450","data_contact":"danielle.dennie@concordia.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9145,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-05-14 21:02:46 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-14 21:02:46 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--568","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Serena Small","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9146,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-15 15:33:11 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-15 15:33:11 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--530","organisation_id":9,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Amal Boultif","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9147,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-15 15:33:12 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-15 16:38:14 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--531","organisation_id":9,"grant_number":"13-2020","identifier":"Fonds de démarrage facultaire ","description":"Cette recherche documentaire vise, dans un premier temps, à réaliser un état des lieux, des usages de la littératie médiatique et multimodale en contexte numérique LMM@ (Lacelle, Boutin et Lebrun, 2017), dans les pratiques des enseignant.e.s de français langue première ou seconde, en contexte minoritaire ou majoritaire. Nous désirons faire un état des lieux des pratiques effectives dans les cours de français, en relevant les études qui traitent des pratiques et d’approches de la LMM@. L’objectif de ce premier volet de la recension serait d’identifier ces pratiques, et de distinguer celles qu’on pourrait considérer comme exemplaires et innovantes en enseignement du français. Les aspects qui nous intéressent en enseignement apprentissages du français sont la lecture et la compréhension des textes, l’écriture et le fonctionnement de la langue, mais aussi les usages transversaux, dans des contextes interdisciplinaires : français, univers social, arts.\r\n\r\nDans un second temps, cette recherche documentaire s’intéresse au transfert des savoirs savants (Malo et Develay) en savoirs de pratique relatifs à la LMM@ chez les enseignant.e.s en formation dans les programmes en éducation.\r\n\r\nCe second volet de la recension s’intéresse donc aux aspects de la LMM@ qui sont enseignés dans les programmes de baccalauréat en éducation, aussi bien dans les universités francophones en Ontario que dans les autres provinces canadiennes. Nous voulons donc documenter les usages intégrés de la LMM@ aux cours de premier cycle universitaire spécifiquement les programmes de formation à l’enseignement, et à la pédagogie, par les professeur. e. s et chargé. e. s de cours et dans les prescriptions des programmes, mais aussi dans les syllabus ou descriptifs des contenus ou attentes des cours du baccalauréat en éducation.","principal_investigator":"Amal Boultif","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Béatrice Crettenand Pécorini","funder_name":null},{"id":9148,"title":"Heat storage and improved thermal management to reduce energy use and improve growing conditions in Ontario commercial-scale greenhouses ","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-05-15 20:22:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-19 19:19:01 UTC","slug":"heat-storage-and-improved-thermal-management-to-reduce-energy-use-and-improve-growing-conditions-in-ontario-commercial-scale-greenhouses","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UG-T1-2020-10010","identifier":"","description":"Improved greenhouse temperature and moisture control could reduce fuel costs and GHG emissions, and extend production seasons. Growers need Ontario-and crop-specific guidance to determine which of the many possible technologies and practices to implement. Dehumidification, thermal storage, including earth-air heat exchange, and adapting ground-source heat pump technologies, may be appropriate for use in Ontario greenhouses. Some of these methods have not been extensively studied in Ontario-like climates. This project will use existing experimental data (GERT dehumidification project) and facilities (Harrow Research Station) to understand energy and moisture conditions. Parametric and computer modeling of greenhouse interior heat and mass transfer forced by exterior weather conditions, with experimental validation, will be used to quantify costs, growing condition improvements and environmental impacts of implementing energy saving technologies that could be realistically used in Ontario commercial\r\ngreenhouses.","principal_investigator":"Syeda Tasnim, David Lubitz","principal_investigator_identifier":"David Lubitz","data_contact":"David Lubitz","funder_name":null},{"id":9149,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-18 23:00:50 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-18 23:00:50 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3559","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Nigel Barnim","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9150,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-19 16:26:14 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-19 16:26:14 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3560","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Semone Myrie","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9151,"title":"My plan (University of Manitoba )","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2020-05-19 16:26:21 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-19 18:46:12 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-manitoba--60","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Aaron Kilmury","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9152,"title":"RRIWT2DERWHCS","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-19 18:58:54 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-19 19:56:43 UTC","slug":"rriwt2derwhcs","organisation_id":26,"grant_number":"","identifier":"REB 146","description":"The research has been designed using Clandinin and Connelly's (2000) Narrative Inquiry approach. The process for conducting this research consists of focusing on studying two participants, gathering information through the collection of stories and artwork. The purpose of the research is to understand and acquire knowledge about how rural residing Indigenous women living with type 2 diabetes experience receiving Westernized healthcare services. The aim of the research is to inform personal and professional knowledge development.","principal_investigator":"Chantelle  Walker","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"c4walker@ryerson.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9153,"title":"SAGE Study","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2020-05-19 19:29:19 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-28 14:55:31 UTC","slug":"sage-study","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Study of Asthma Genes and the Environment – SAGE Study.\r\nSAGE (the Study of Asthma, Genes, and the Environment), is a longitudinal study.The study started in 2002. Researchers sent letters to the parents of all children born in 1995 and still living in Manitoba. 13980 families were invited to participate via a survey. 3681 families completed and returned the survey. 11% had asthma, 5% had hay fever or food allergy. The rest (84%) did not have any allergic diseases. All families of children with asthma were invited to participate in the longitudinal study. Children without asthma were randomly selected and invited to participate in the study.\r\nIn all, 723 children agreed to participate. 246 with asthma and 477 without asthma.","principal_investigator":"Allan Becker, Elinor Simons","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Henry Huang","funder_name":null},{"id":9154,"title":"Treatment of MS ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-19 20:19:23 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-19 20:26:32 UTC","slug":"treatment-of-ms","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Data collected are to be used to help assist create a mnemonic for the pharmacological interventions used in multiple sclerosis. ","principal_investigator":"Ashley Wong","principal_investigator_identifier":"Mohammed El Hussein","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9155,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-05-19 20:24:19 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-21 19:44:22 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--569","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"To collect substance information - for point-of-care delivery, and epidemiological and [OTHER] study.","principal_investigator":"Peter M Plett","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9156,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-20 03:46:32 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-20 03:46:32 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template