,"title":"Measuring WELL Design ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-21 17:47:45 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-21 17:55:32 UTC","slug":"measuring-well-design","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Maintaining student and faculty wellbeing is of great concern to post-secondary institutions. While wellness programming offer a solution to those who have time to participate, we ask: how might space design and installations enhance wellbeing in post-secondary learning spaces? Measuring WELL Design aims to simultaneously collect user perceived wellbeing data and IoT sensor data to measure the impact of WELL Design and IEQ on student faculty wellbeing. The data collected through case studies and discrete studies within the project will be used to direct cost-effect space and product design to enhance student and faculty wellbeing  in post-secondary learning spaces. ","principal_investigator":"William (Zack) MacDonald","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9168,"title":"SN 3.6","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-21 20:31:18 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-21 20:33:00 UTC","slug":"sn-3-6","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Gina Muckle/Richard Bélanger","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Natalia Poliakova","funder_name":null},{"id":9169,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-05-21 21:08:42 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-21 21:08:42 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--570","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Jasmine Chipman Koty","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9170,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-21 21:09:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-21 21:09:13 UTC",