ersity). Collaborators, co-applicants and partner organizations are also involved from New Brunswick, BC, Québec and Illinois, while some partner organizations have national mandates. The project also features an international advisory committee, with current representation from the UK and the US. \r\n\r\nThis plan is drafted in compliance with the Tri-Council Policy Statement: Ethical Conduct for Research Involving Humans (TCPS2) and the Tri-Agency Statement on Principles of Digital Data Management and was developed using the Canadian Association of Research Libraries’ Portage Data Management Plan Assistant.","principal_investigator":"Catherine Leviten-Reid","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Jasmine_Hoover@cbu.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9182,"title":"Prevention & Education","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-27 12:55:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-27 13:21:35 UTC","slug":"prevention-education","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The P&E review has been commissioned to help understand what is the right mix of prevention/education interventions to apply and those interventions that are less effective or have unintended consequences, which will inform a range of policy, regulatory and other action by a range of stakeholders.\r\n\r\nThe interviews will add the perspectives of third sector charities to provide context for the systematic review findings.","principal_investigator":"Jess Voll, Margo Hilbrecht","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9183,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-05-27 13:51:21 UTC","updated_at":"2020-05-27 13:51:21 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3576","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Taheera Walji","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9184,"title":"Online Information Liter