hley Cole","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9209,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-01 20:50:29 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-01 20:50:29 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--139","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Dorothee Bienzle","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9210,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-02 15:40:46 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-02 15:40:46 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--534","organisation_id":51,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Laurence Labelle","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9211,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-02 18:44:06 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-02 18:48:21 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--140","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofGT2-27351 ","identifier":"27351","description":"The ABF (feeding programs without or with reduced antibiotics and coccidiostats) trend has created several poultry production challenges, such as increased pressure of enteric diseases, most notably coccidiosis and necrotic enteritis, poor feed utilization and higher production costs. A key element in ABF feeding programs is to maintain gastrointestinal health and function to maximize nutrients digestion and absorption. Antibiotic Growth Promoters are associated with increased nutrient absorption and energy retention resulting in improved performance. Recent scientific research and our data in broilers shows that supporting intestinal health status is key to poultry performance and profitability. The long-term goal of our research program is to unravel factors and processes that regulate intestinal function and health in poultry by integrating maternal, in-ovo and early post-hatch nutrition strategies to support continuous gut development at embryonic through to early post-hatch period to optimize nutrients utilization for enhanced poultry productivity and reduced antibiotic use. The specific overall objective of this program is to study mechanisms mediating adaptive digestive and absorptive responses with respect to dietary strategies and how they relate to growth and development to facilitate design of effective antibiotic free starter diets, particularly in conditions where enteric pathogens may otherwise compromise efficient production.","principal_investigator":"Elijah Kiarie","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-9752-8546","data_contact":"Tel: +1-519-824-4120 Ext. 53746 l ekiarie@uoguelph.ca ","funder_name":null},{"id":9212,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-02 18:58:02 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-02 18:59:46 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--141","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofGT2-2019-27378 ","identifier":"27378 ","description":"There are growing concerns in Canada and around the world on indiscriminate use of antibiotics and the linkage to the emergency of antibiotic resistant human and animal pathogens. Indeed, Canadian Animal Health Institute has acted to phase out use of medically important antibiotics for growth promotion and placed veterinary oversight in antimicrobial use in animal protein production. The actions taken by regulatory bodies, producers and consumers will eliminate or reduce the total use of antibiotics in pig production placing greater emphasis on dietary strategies for promoting and maintaining healthy and functional gastrointestinal tract. The overriding goal of this research is to investigate the potential of bioactive feed ingredients, specifically prebiotics, as an alternative to in-feed antibiotics in pig diets using growth performance, changes in intestinal structure and function and microbiota activity as response criteria. Demonstrating benefit of these feed ingredients will lead to commercial development of feed supplements capable of maintaining a healthy intestinal system with enhanced digestive function in pigs. ","principal_investigator":"Elijah Kiarie","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-9752-8546","data_contact":"Tel: +1-519-824-4120 Ext. 53746 l ekiarie@uoguelph.ca ","funder_name":null},{"id":9213,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-02 19:27:07 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-02 19:27:07 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--535","organisation_id":51,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Arina Soare","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9214,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-03 00:20:18 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-03 00:20:18 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--142","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Ljiljana Tamburic-Ilincic","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9215,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-03 00:47:57 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-03 00:49:14 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--143","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UofG2018-3243","identifier":"","description":"Winter wheat grown in Eastern Canada is grouped in three classes with specific quality characteristics required for different market. Several biotic and abiotic factors are responsible for decreased yield and quality in different environments and growing seasons. Fusarium head blight (FHB) is a serious wheat diseases for Ontario wheat growers. This research project will evaluate and develop new and improved wheat cultivars and germplasm. Data will be collected across Ontario.","principal_investigator":"Ljiljana Tamburic-Ilincic","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Ljiljana Tamburic-Ilincic","funder_name":null},{"id":9216,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-03 15:34:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-03 15:34:58 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--536","organisation_id":44,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Martine Gagnon","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9217,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-06-03 18:32:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-03 18:32:20 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--838","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Ian  Winship","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9218,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-03 18:50:16 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-03 18:50:16 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--144","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Lauren Fletcher lfletc03@uoguelph.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name"