"my-plan-dalhousie-university-generic-plan--13","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9248,"title":"Soil carbon sequestration : What are the major driving forces?","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-06-09 16:44:14 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-18 18:59:59 UTC","slug":"soil-carbon-sequestration-what-are-the-major-driving-forces","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"IT17087; Mitacs Accelerate PDF","identifier":"","description":"There is a growing movement within the agricultural community to use a nature-based approach to soil management, emphasizing its natural ability to sequester atmospheric carbon (CO2). Soil carbon sequestration not only improves soil health and fertility but benefits the climate (reduced GHG emissions) and watersheds (facilitates water infiltration, mitigating floods, and purification). This project, awarded as a Mitacs Accelerate Industrial Postdoctoral Fellowship, is part of a larger study (run by the not-for-profit, Food Water Wellness Foundation) with the objectives to: i) effectively measure and monitor soil carbon sequestration to develop a protocol for a carbon offset programme; and ii) investigate the chemical, biological and physical processes within a soil that influence carbon sequestration and the effect of agricultural management practices on those processes.\r\n\r\nThis project, being shorter in duration (one year), will be focused on the second objectives listed above. Emphasis will be on the soil analysis of approximately 450 soil cores (varying in land use and climatic conditions within Alberta), specifically: pH, soil organic carbon, total nitrogen, and texture. This work will be done in Dr. Monika Gorzelak's lab at Agriculture and Agri-Food Canada in Lethbridge.\r\n\r\nThere is a separate team located in Olds that is responsible for the processing of the cores and gathering: bulk density, soil moisture, root depth, horizon definitions and gravel content. \r\n\r\nAdditionally, the Chinook Applied Research Association Soil Health Lab in Oyen will analyse the soil samples for soil respiration.   \r\n\r\nFinally, Food Water Wellness Foundation will conduct surveys with the landowners to gather data on land use and management practices. \r\n\r\nThis data will be combined and analysed in an effort to understand what variables are responsible for driving soil carbon sequestration.","principal_investigator":"Catherine Hepp","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"chepp@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9250,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-09 17:35:21 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 17:35:21 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--539","organisation_id":44,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Genevieve Laroche","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9251,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-09 17:37:15 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 17:37:15 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--540","organisation_id":44,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Katherine Tanaka","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9252,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-09 18:01:01 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 18:01:01 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3600","organisation_id":55,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"James Doiron","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9254,"title":"READYorNot CHD Trial","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-06-09 18:15:11 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-25 20:43:41 UTC","slug":"readyornot-chd-trial","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Andrew Mackie","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Daniella San Martin-Feeney, ds22@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9255,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-09 18:23:11 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 18:23:11 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3602","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Trevor Avery","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9256,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-06-09 18:29:50 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 18:29:50 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--842","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Ahlam abdulnab@ualberta.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9257,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-09 18:48:00 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-09 18:48:49 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3603","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9261,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-10 14:33:44 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-10 14:33:44 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3604","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Donna Sevenpifer","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9262,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-10 14:38:24 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-10 14:38:24 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3605","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9263,"title":"MA Thesis Data Management Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-10 15:19:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-10 18:00:11 UTC","slug":"ma-thesis-data-management-plan","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Many organizations are implementing gratitude initiatives into the workplace, as there are many benefits to increasing gratitude for employees. However, there are potential dark sides to implementing these interventions that have largely been ignored. The current study aims to investigate the moderating effect individual differences could cause between gratitude interventions and experiencing felt gratitude. In order to investigate this, the research question asks if different gratitude interventions cause changes in felt gratitude dependent on individual factors, including entitlement and trait gratitude?\r\nIt is hypothesized that individuals high in entitlement will experience lower levels of felt gratitude, regardless of the intervention.\r\nThe gratitude interventions of interest include vignette's, a one-time gratitude list, a one-week daily gratitude journal, and a two-week daily gratitude journal. \r\nParticipants will be randomly assigned to one of four conditions, each with their own gratitude intervention.","principal_investigator":"Julia Kearney","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9264,"title":"UG-T1-2020-100223: Increasing lodging resistance in oats for enhanced quality and yield","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-10 17:08:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-10 19:37:45 UTC","slug":"ug-t1-2020-100223-increasing-lodging-resistance-in-oats-for-enhanced-quality-and-yield","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"110-012800-000000-030563","identifier":"","description":"A DMP for UG-T1-2020-100223: Increasing lodging resistance in oats for enhanced quality and yield.\r\n\r\nThis is a field-based research project taking place at the Winchester and New Liskeard Agricultural Research Stations. The study investigates different agronomic management practices in terms of their ability to reduce lodging in milling oats.\r\n\r\nThe DMP is focused on main data-based outputs of the project: important dates (e.g. planting, harvest), in-season measurements (e.g. stand count) and final harvest data (e.g. yield). ","principal_investigator":"Joshua Nasielski","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-9257-0208","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9265,"title":"MA Thesis Data Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-10 21:22:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-10 22:02:59 UTC","slug":"ma-thesis-data-plan","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"We seek to determine whether situational factors can have an impact on the experience of interview anxiety using a randomized experiment. More specifically, we are interested in investigating  whether the interviewer building rapport with the applicant lowers applicant interview anxiety, as well as whether providing interview questions ahead of time reduces applicant interview anxiety. We will also test intolerance of uncertainty as a moderator of this relation between question provision and interview anxiety. To test these relations, students will be invited to apply for a research assistant position at the University of Guelph. After taking part in the interview, they will be invited to participate in the study by filling out a survey which includes an interview anxiety and intolerance of uncertainty scale. Anonymous data will be kept to test whether the 3 experimental conditions show any mean differences on interview anxiety.","principal_investigator":"Jordan Moore","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9267,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-11 15:11:47 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-11 15:12:01 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--541","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9268,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-11 16:52:45 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-11 16:52:45 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3609","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Wayne Johnston","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9269,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-11 16:54:07 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-11 16:54:07 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--149","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Wayne Johnston","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9270,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-11 18:18:25 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-11 18:18:25 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--150","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Rebecca Moore","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9271,"title":"Investigation of alternative control measures for post-weaning E. coli diarrhea in pigs","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-12 13:01:09 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-12 13:08:03 UTC","slug":"investigation-of-alternative-control-measures-for-post-weaning-e-coli-diarrhea-in-pigs","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030536","identifier":"UG-T1-2020-100191","description":"Newly weaned pigs often develop enteric diseases because of the sudden loss of passive protection from\r\nmilk and the rapid change in diet. The most common cause of diarrhea in the first few weeks post-weaning is\r\ncaused by enterotoxigenic E. coli (ETEC). Producers commonly choose to add high levels (>2000 ppm) of\r\nzinc oxide in the first nursery diets to combat ETEC or they might use antibiotics as a means of preventing\r\ndiarrhea. Both of these approaches are drawing criticism because of environmental and public health\r\nconcerns. There are promising new approaches being developed that need to be carefully evaluated in order\r\nthat producers can make a well educated decision regarding ETEC control. Among the most promising\r\napproaches include live oral E. coli vaccines, probiotics and proteobiotics. We propose to conduct controlled\r\nexperimental challenge studies and in-field clinical trials in order to provide data to assess these alternative\r\ntreatment options.The objective of this proposal is:\r\n-to determine if post-weaning E. coli diarrhea can be effectively controlled by means other than antibiotics\r\nand heavy metals, including the use of oral vaccines, probiotics and proteobiotics","principal_investigator":"Robert Friendship","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0003-4630-3878","data_contact":"519 824 4129 ext 54022, rfriends@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9272,"title":"Impact of specialized feeding regime for replacement gilts on lactation performance","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-12 14:03:50 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-12 14:08:19 UTC","slug":"impact-of-specialized-feeding-regime-for-replacement-gilts-on-lactation-performance","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"027350","identifier":"project 27350","description":"Sow milk production is important and it is therefore essential to develop methods to increase milk yield. The main limiting factor for milk production is the number of milk-secreting cells that are present at the beginning of lactation. Rapid mammary development takes place from 90 days of age until puberty. Nutrition, endocrine status and management during this period can have an important impact on mammary development and these factors need to be examined. The objective of this study is to determine the impact of a specialized feeding regime for replacement gilts on their lactation performance. It is common to feed gilts a diet to slow down the growth rate to reduce locomotory problems but no one has examined these feeding programs with regard to their effect on mammary development. \r\nGilts (n=90) will be assigned to one of three feeding programs from 90 days until puberty. Two feeding programs will restrict nutrient intake, either by limit feeding or by using a high fibre diet. Milk yield will be measured indirectly by weighing piglets at birth and at weaning. A representative milk sample will be collected from 10 sows per treatment to determine standard composition. \r\n","principal_investigator":"Robert Friendship","principal_investigator_identifier":" 0000-0003-4630-3878","data_contact":"519 824 4129 ext 54022, rfriends@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9273,"title":"Improving outcomes for Ontario apple producers though precision agriculture and labour efficiency strategies","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-12 20:24:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-16 19:38:06 UTC","slug":"improving-outcomes-for-ontario-apple-producers-though-precision-agriculture-and-labour-efficiency-strategies--2","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UG-T1-2020-100086","identifier":"Agri-Food Innovation Alliance","description":"This project will investigate the advancement of precision crop load management strategies and mechanical pruning in Ontario apple orchards. The overall goal of the project is to reduce the reliance on manual labour, increase orchard fruit quality and efficiency, and decrease the need for manual hand thinning and pruning. \r\nInstitution: University of Guelph\r\n","principal_investigator":"Prof. John Cline","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9274,"title":"Lab Data Files ","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2020-06-12 23:11:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-03 20:15:34 UTC","slug":"lab-data-files","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"BRANCH ","description":"Data management plan for archival data used in the BRANCH lab. Inclusive of various projects and available for all members of the lab.","principal_investigator":"Stuart MacDonald ","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1042-4750","data_contact":"Cynthia McDowell; cynthiamcdowell@uvic.ca; (778) 866-2985","funder_name":null},{"id":9275,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-06-13 21:13:03 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-13 21:13:03 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--571","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Arantxa","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9276,"title":"Amazing Race","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-15 12:06:49 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 12:15:25 UTC","slug":"amazing-race","organisation_id":9,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Teaching data mining using EMR dataset.","principal_investigator":"Jeffrey Puncher","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9277,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-15 12:43:32 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 12:43:32 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3611","organisation_id":12,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9278,"title":"Emergency physician knowledge, training and confidence in managing dental emergencies","dmptemplate_id":56,"created_at":"2020-06-15 13:25:48 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 13:26:45 UTC","slug":"emergency-physician-knowledge-training-and-confidence-in-managing-dental-emergencies","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Erin  Steeves","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9279,"title":"My plan (University of Guelph Agri-Food Funding Template (Alliance/Food from Thought) )","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-15 15:40:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 15:40:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-guelph-agri-food-funding-template-alliance-food-from-thought--154","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Lorna Deeth","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9280,"title":"The Visual Instruction Movement","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-06-15 16:11:44 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 16:12:21 UTC","slug":"the-visual-instruction-movement","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Andrea Korda","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9281,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-15 17:51:37 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-16 20:13:42 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3612","organisation_id":48,"grant_number":"","identifier":"15888","description":"The main focus of this project is to figure out how can privacy policy terms be displayed to make them more understandable to general technology users.\r\nTo answer the main questions we need to (phase I) understand privacy policy requirements and needs by both legal domain experts and the general public. Based on the requirements, phase I, results we will develop a text visualization solution, then we will evaluate (phase II) the developed solution by asking for the users' and experts' feedback.","principal_investigator":"Dr. Christopher Collins","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"christopher.collins@uoit.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9282,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-15 21:38:54 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 21:41:30 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3613","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"This project examines different aspects of prosody in young children and tests the association between these measures and reading measures a year later.","principal_investigator":"Lesly Wade-Woolley","principal_investigator_identifier":"orcid.org/0000-0001-9022-6676","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9283,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-15 23:43:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 23:49:39 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3614","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Evans Monyoncho","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Evans Monyoncho","funder_name":null},{"id":9284,"title":"Engendering Acadian Ideneities","dmptemplate_id":56,"created_at":"2020-06-15 23:54:01 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-15 23:55:58 UTC","slug":"engendering-acadian-ideneities","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"PhD Research Project","principal_investigator":"Katie MacLeod","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9285,"title":"Hakai-MaPP Kelp","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-16 01:22:42 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-17 19:11:49 UTC","slug":"hakai-mapp-kelp","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Margot  Hessing-Lewis","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9287,"title":"Study Summer2020","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-16 02:57:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-16 02:58:46 UTC","slug":"study-summer2020","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"12345","identifier":"ABC","description":"","principal_investigator":"Dr. Stephanie Capobianco","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"123-122-9098","funder_name":null},{"id":9288,"title":"Development of hydrometeorological risk indicators","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-06-16 12:47:08 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-16 19:05:21 UTC","slug":"development-of-hydrometeorological-risk-indicators","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UG-T1-2020-100172","identifier":"","description":"This plan outlines the data management procedures that will be associated with the development of risk indicators for crop fields prone to extreme weather, flooding and hydrologic connectivity in the Canadian portion of the Lake Erie Basin. Publicly available geospatial datasets illustrating historical and projected future climate conditions in Southwestern Ontario will be downloaded from online data repositories. Optical satellite imagery will also be downloaded from online data repositories and used to delineate areas subject to surface-water inundation. All geospatial datasets will be processed to compute risk indicators pertaining to extreme weather, flooding and hydrologic connectivity, under historical conditions as well as future climate change scenarios. The end products of this project will be a suite of maps that enable the visualization of specific risk indicators across the Canadian portion of the Lake Erie Basin.","principal_investigator":"Genevieve Ali","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0001-5144-8188","data_contact":"gali@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9289,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-06-16 15:57:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-06-16 15:57:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3617","organisati