e)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-07-09 14:43:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-09 14:43:13 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3695","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Maggie Neilson","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9415,"title":"Meeting graduate students' needs around the scholarly communication process: an investigation ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-07-09 17:41:20 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-09 17:52:05 UTC","slug":"meeting-graduate-students-needs-around-the-scholarly-communication-process-an-investigation","organisation_id":23,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Many graduate students at the University of Calgary begin to publish scholarly works during the course of their studies.  As they submit manuscripts for publication as authors or co-authors, they must grapple with the threshold concept of scholarly communication, the complex system through which research outputs are made available to the scholarly community and beyond. Mastery of this concept marks a fundamental shift in students’ understandings of their disciplines and their role as scholars; however, the complex and sometimes opaque nature of the publishing process can be a barrier to learning.  As librarians, we are uniquely positioned to offer instruction and consultation on topics relating to the process of scholarly publishing that is sensitive to the existing activities, cultures, and habits of disciplinary communities across campus, and complements existing training offered by other units.  Through this investigation, we will seek information from students and faculty mentors to develop and test a scalable, learner-centered, and evidence-based set of instructional modules on scholarly communications for graduate students.\r\n\r\nWe will be interviewing participants and creating learning modules.\r\n\r\nThis study is funded by a University of Calgary TI Teaching and Learning Grant\r\n","principal_investigator":"Christie Hurrell","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"(403) 210-6103, christie.hurrell@ucalgary.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9416,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-07-09 18:58:50 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-09 18:58:50 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3697","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Denis Lacroix","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9417,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-07-09 23:40:24 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-09 23:40:24 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3698","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Denis Lacroix","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9418,"title":"NSERC Strategic Wildfire","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-07-10 22:16:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-10 22:19:35 UTC","slug":"nserc-strategic-wildfire","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"CanadaWildfire2020","description":"Wildland Fire Research data collected under the NSERC strategic network. Data collected to broadly address:\r\nUnderstanding Fire in a Changing World\r\nManaging Ecosystems\r\nDelivering Innovative Fire Management Solutions.","principal_investigator":"Mike Flannigan","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Brian Wiens","funder_name":null},{"id":9419,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-07-12 06:46:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-07-12 06:46:13 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3699","organisation_id":10,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"McMaster RDM","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9420,"title"