on the digitization of early audio recordings to build relationships within and between communities. ","principal_investigator":"Bimadoshka Pucan","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9583,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-09-14 18:45:18 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-14 18:46:29 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--584","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Bruno Carturan","principal_investigator_identifier":" 0000-0001-6811-1063","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9584,"title":"My plan (University of Manitoba )","dmptemplate_id":35,"created_at":"2020-09-14 19:00:29 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-14 19:00:29 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-manitoba--63","organisation_id":37,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Juliette Cooper","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9585,"title":"COVID-19, Precarity, and the Counternarratives of PSWs: Photovoice and Change","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-09-14 19:35:06 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-14 19:39:27 UTC","slug":"covid-19-precarity-and-the-counternarratives-of-psws-photovoice-and-change","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"UW/SSHRC Explore","identifier":"","description":"The purpose of this project is to examine the experiences of PSWs (Personal Support Worker) to explore the impact that COVID-19 has had on their labour and personal conditions of precarity. The one aspect of precarity that we will focus on is invisibility: when labour and labour conditions are unseen. We will use a community-based and critical arts-based approach to inquiry. The PSWs who participate in the project will each be meaningfully involved in the creation of a photovoice that will serve to exhibit their personal narrative, raise critical consciousness, and create engagement with a larger community, thus facilitating agency and the potential for positive structural change. We will ask, in our community-based research:\r\n\r\n1. What has been the impact of COVID-19?\r\n2. How do PSWs feel precarious?\r\n3. How is the labour of  PSWs unseen?\r\n3. How is the invisibility of their labour and experience connected to their sense of precarity ?\r\n4. What are the systems and structures that impact PSWs in their work in LTC facilities?\r\n","principal_investigator":"Trish Van Katwyk","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"pvankatw@uwaterloo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9586,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-09-14 21:57:16 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-14 21:57:16 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-modele-portage--555","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Marie-Lyne Larrivee","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9587,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-09-16 15:28:24 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-16 15:28:24 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3771","organisation_id":33,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Grant Gibson","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9588,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-09-16 17:29:34 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-16 17:29:34 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3772","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Tanya Brown","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9589,"title":"Mechanisms of long-term consequences of transition cow biology on production and reproduction traits","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-09-16 18:19:40 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-18 14:18:55 UTC","slug":"mechanisms-of-long-term-consequences-of-transition-cow-biology-on-production-and-reproduction-traits","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"The transition period is one of the most challenging times a dairy cow will face in her life due to the immense physiological changes she will undergo while moving from a nonlactating pregnant state to a nonpregnant lactating state. These many changes leave her vulnerable to physiological imbalances and health disorders which can have negative effects on her performance for months. This research project aims to better characterize how the quality of the transition period will impact the productive and reproductive performance in the subsequent lactation and whether interventions through precision management can be developed and applied on a tailored basis to mitigate negative ramifications on health and performance.","principal_investigator":"Eduardo de Souza Ribeiro ","principal_investigator_identifier":"orcid.org/0000-0002-4201-7383","data_contact":"eribeiro@uoguelph.ca; (519) 824-4120 Ext. 56516 ","funder_name":null},{"id":9590,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-09-17 17:18:15 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-17 17:18:15 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--3773","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Elizabeth Kreiter","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9591,"title":"My plan (Dalhousie University Generic Plan)","dmptemplate_id":56,"created_at":"2020-09-17 18:12:29 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-17 18:12:29 UTC","slug":"my-plan-dalhousie-university-generic-plan--28","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Erin MacPherson","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9592,"title":"My plan (Portage Template