ns may appear frivolous – which is part of the goal – but ignorance of the mundane may be what prevents the ecological community from being as diverse as the rest of society. Fashion may be a key to understanding our general failure in outreach (why do people not care more about conservation?) and unlocking venues of real change (how will we make ecologists centrepieces in future blockbuster movies?). The lagging of ecology fashion in the context of pop culture may also be affecting how we pursue conservation science – have our professional opinions on scientific interests and conservation actions been misled by our appearance of objectivity and relative anonymity?","principal_investigator":"Dr. Anne Pasek","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Dr. Alexandra Davis","funder_name":null},{"id":9640,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-09-30 17:18:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-30 17:18:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--593","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Helena Neudorf","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9641,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-09-30 17:19:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-30 17:19:13 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--594","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Elizabeth emojaeva@alumni.ubc.ca","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9642,"title":"Many Ways Plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-09-30 17:22:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-09-30 17:23:25 UTC","slug":"many-ways-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template","organisation_id":7