entifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9702,"title":"Food Insecurity and Rural Seniors Living Independently: An Exploratory Study in Huron, Perth, Bruce and Grey Counties","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-10-15 11:46:49 UTC","updated_at":"2020-10-15 12:06:35 UTC","slug":"food-insecurity-and-rural-seniors-living-independently-an-exploratory-study-in-huron-perth-bruce-and-grey-counties","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"030334","identifier":"802171240","description":"This research project proposes to examine the issue of food security/insecurity for rural seniors living independently, a population and context that has largely been ignored. It will take place in Grey, Bruce, Perth and Huron Counties. This study is exploratory and will look to engage multiple perspectives by engaging seniors, primary care providers, public health professionals, home care workers, service providers, and municipal planners/staff through interviews. By obtaining multiple perspectives, a holistic understanding of rural senior food insecurity can be obtained, a badly needed perspective according to existing research literature. Interview data will be analyzed through a constant comparison methodology and triangulation will be conducted by comparing the emergent themes within and among the various stakeholders. Distribution of reports as outlined in the KTT strategy will be disseminated through our two partners - Gateway Rural Health and Canadian Rural Revitalization Foundation (CRRF), In addition, and with the assistance of CRRF, presentations will be made at their annual national conference. Four Webinars will be conducted for audiences identified in the letter of intent in addition to the various stakeholder groups with a focus on the 4 counties with the assistance of Gateway Rural Health.","principal_investigator":"Al Lauzon","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"allauzon@uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9703,"title":"My plan (Portage Temp