estigator":"Sarah Spivey-Faulkner","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Sarah Spivey-Faulkner","funder_name":null},{"id":9898,"title":"Co-operative Management and Traditional Knowledge in Alberta","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-11-05 21:38:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-05 21:43:56 UTC","slug":"co-operative-management-and-traditional-knowledge-in-alberta","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"RES0048018","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Brenda Parlee","principal_investigator_identifier":"1112508","data_contact":"Tracy Howlett, thowlett@ualberta.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9899,"title":"Regional Variety Trials - Bon Accord","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-11-05 21:39:21 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-06 20:31:11 UTC","slug":"regional-variety-trials-bon-accord","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"819417","description":"Variety Evaluation of Cereal Crops\r\n\r\nData is for compilation with other provincial testing sites used to develop the annual seed guide seed.ab.ca","principal_investigator":"Sheri Strydhorst","principal_investigator_identifier":"0000-0002-3883-4911","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9900,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-11-05 21:41:22 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-05 21:41:22 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--872","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Yina  Liu","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9901,"title":"Phylogenetic Ecology of Aquatic Macroinvertebrate Communities that live in Bromeliads","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2020-11-05 21:52:53 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-10 19:22:24 UTC","slug":"phylogenetic-ecology-of-aquatic-macroinvertebrate-communities-that-live-in-bromeliads","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"","identifier":"PEBI","description":"This project aims to use phylogenetic information to infer the ecological processes involved in shaping communities. We will approach this issue from different temporal and spatial scales to understand the short and long-term impacts of ecological events and processes on the assembly of a particular community. From a local scale, we will recover current ecological processes determining species coexistence. Since biotic interactions are particularly important at this scale, and predation has been poorly studied in the field of community phylogenetics, we will focus on characterizing the effects of predation on the phylogenetic structure of prey communities. Expanding the spatial scale, we will assess the effects of different abiotic variables on the phylogenetic structure and diversity of regional species pools. Finally, from an evolutionary perspective, we will focus on a representative clade of the community (Chironomidae family) to evaluate how the evolutionary history of its host (bromeliads) has affected its diversification and distribution. The integration of the different approaches will help unravel how ecological and evolutionary processes interact at different scales to shape current species biodiversity. The database will be used for research done at each of these scales.","principal_investigator":"Nadia Paez","principal_investigator_identifier":"https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0854-3993","data_contact":"email: nadia@zoology.ubc.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":9902,"title":"My plan (UVic DMP Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2020-11-06 04:22:58 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-06 04:22:58 UTC","slug":"my-plan-uvic-dmp-template--110","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Meghan Zee","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":9903,"title":"My plan (OFI Module E (Ecosystem Indicators))","dmptemplate_id":54,"created_at":"2020-11-06 15:17:05 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-06 15:17:05 UTC