32,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"khedidja seridi","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9909,"title":"SRP DMP","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-11-08 02:54:43 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-08 02:55:35 UTC","slug":"srp-dmp","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Of the public health interventions used to prevent the spread of COVID-19 in Canada, lockdowns have become the focus of scrutiny and debate amongst experts. Numerous Canadian MDs, including infectious disease experts and former public health officers, have publicly opposed lockdowns. By conducting semi-structured qualitative interviews with those experts, I aim to investigate: 1) how much they trust public health authorities, 2) their expertise and how it may or may not relate to pandemic management, and 3) their personal views on what it means to be healthy. Understanding how personal values and beliefs may influence professional views on lockdown is important as it may help to improve the quality of scientific discussions by adding a dimension beyond simply considering the available (and rapidly evolving) evidence.","principal_investigator":"Dinesh Moro","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":9910,"title":"Comédie Française Registers Project","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2020-11-09 05:08:43 UTC","updated_at":"2020-11-11 05:24:48 UTC","slug":"comedie-francaise-registers-project","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Sara Harvey","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"admin@cfregisters.org","funder_name":null},{"id":9912,"title":"Dexamethasone Depletion in Cattle","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-11-09 16:00:39 UTC","updated_at":"2021-01-26 16:20:31 UTC","slug":"dexamethasone-depletion-in-cattle","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"UG-T1-2020-100033","iden