,"updated_at":"2020-12-11 20:57:38 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4031","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Keith Glen Newton","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10111,"title":"Field School Data Plan","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-11 22:02:45 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-11 22:07:50 UTC","slug":"field-school-data-plan","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Katie  Dierks","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10112,"title":"Alternative Theories of Relationships and LGBTQ+ Representation in Stranger Things Canon/Fanon. ","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-12 03:18:19 UTC","updated_at":"2021-01-20 02:20:32 UTC","slug":"alternative-theories-of-relationships-and-lgbtq-representation-in-stranger-things-canon-fanon","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":"N/A","identifier":"ORE#42775","description":"My project will consist of this linear Stranger Things (2016) fanfiction, a related, non-linear, Stranger Things (2016) interactive fiction game, and a 30-to-35-page critical analysis paper respectively. I intend to use the first 2 parts of my project to examine a variety of fanfiction sites, along with the interactive fiction platform Twine, to see if there are any trends in fans’ commentary on alternative theories of LGBTQ2+ representation in the Stranger Things (2016) canon/fanon when the same narrative is presented to them in a linear versus a “choose your own adventure” style format. Deviating from the expectations of heterosexuality and/or the straight-gay/lesbian binary previously established within the Stranger Things (2016) canon/fanon, my narrative centers, instead, on male asexuality and/or bisexuality as seen through the respective characterizations of Will Byers and Steve Harrington. Rather than focusing on their more popular, and/or commonly discussed heterosexual, gay, lesbian, slash/femslash counterparts, my account aims to promote the idea of asexuality and/or bisexuality as sexualities and/or sexual orientations which are just as valid LGBTQ2+-related identities.  \r\n\r\nReader responses and/or audience reactions are crucial to my project. Due to the sensitive nature of the topic of this research study - a.k.a. people's attitudes towards sexuality and/or sexual orientation - participation in the study itself will limited to people 18 years or older, who are capable of providing ongoing, and informed consent. Also, as “there is a reasonable expectation for privacy” among members of these sites, (“TCPS 2 CORE - Publicly Available Information”), this investigation will be guided by the ethical standards set forth in the TCPS 2 CORE. Thus, those interested in providing me with commentary for the purposes of my project will need to meet a few more requirements before they will/can be included in my undertaking. Please refer to the information about this study provided in my user profile on this fan/interactive fiction site for more details. Thank you. ","principal_investigator":"KC Collins/Apoorva Sanagavarapu","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Apoorva Sanagavarapu, Telephone 519-954-7809, email asanagav@uwaterloo.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":10113,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-12 13:47:33 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-12 13:47:33 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4034","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Michael Sacke","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10114,"title":"My plan","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-12-13 04:53:13 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-13 04:53:42 UTC","slug":"my-plan--3","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Yiru Zhou","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10115,"title":"My plan (University of Alberta Template)","dmptemplate_id":1,"created_at":"2020-12-13 11:52:35 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-13 11:53:11 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-alberta-template--880","organisation_id":1,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"sd","principal_investigator":"Glen W Armstrong","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10116,"title":"My plan (Dalhousie University Generic Plan)","dmptemplate_id":56,"created_at":"2020-12-14 00:23:38 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-14 00:25:27 UTC","slug":"my-plan-dalhousie-university-generic-plan--47","organisation_id":15,"grant_number":"2020-5338 ","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Catrina Brow","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Kaitrin Doll ","funder_name":null},{"id":10117,"title":"Developing Ontario lager yeasts","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-12-14 01:16:24 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-14 01:22:47 UTC","slug":"developing-ontario-lager-yeasts","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"","identifier":"UG-GLPD-2021-101214","description":"Lager beer accounts for >90% of beer consumed in Ontario. Its production requires significant financial investment to support cold fermentations (<12°C), which historically favoured large producers over craft beer producers. However, craft breweries are increasingly investing in lager production to compete for a stake of the lager market share. Surprisingly, very little diversity exists in the yeasts tasked with its production. Lager yeasts are hybrids of two yeast parents of which one, Saccharomyces eubayanus, is scarce. We have recently isolated such a parent strain from Ontario, which, when bred with other parent strains will not only expanding the diversity of lager-producing strains, but also provide an Ontario regional characteristic to such strains. The advantages not only expands on genetic diversity in lager production, but provides an advantage for marketing lagers with an increased locally produced brand.","principal_investigator":"George van der Merwe","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10118,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-14 15:32:10 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-14 15:32:10 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4035","organisation_id":null,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Anne Busin","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10119,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-14 15:33:08 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-14 15:33:08 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4036","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Anne Busin","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10120,"title":"Test","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-14 22:23:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-14 22:23:52 UTC","slug":"test--26","organisation_id":12,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Natalie Kouri-Towe","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10121,"title":"Retention of BIPOC academic librarians in Canada and the United States","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-14 23:09:26 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-14 23:30:19 UTC","slug":"retention-of-bipoc-academic-librarians-in-canada-and-the-united-states","organisation_id":38,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Maha Kumaran","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10122,"title":"My plan (UVic DMP Template)","dmptemplate_id":44,"created_at":"2020-12-14 23:54:52 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-14 23:55:24 UTC","slug":"my-plan-uvic-dmp-template--119","organisation_id":21,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"","principal_investigator":"Dylan Hillis","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10123,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-15 12:16:03 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-15 12:16:03 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4039","organisation_id":12,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Stacey Cann","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10124,"title":"Development of evidence-based feeding strategies for lactating sows using novel and evolving feeding technologies.","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-12-15 14:15:08 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-15 14:21:50 UTC","slug":"development-of-evidence-based-feeding-strategies-for-lactating-sows-using-novel-and-evolving-feeding-technologies","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"N/A","identifier":"UG-T1-2020-100112","description":"Computerized feeding technologies are becoming more common and are being implemented by Ontario pork producers. These technologies reduce the labour required to deliver feed to pigs, facilitate data collection, and provide the opportunity to closely match estimated (daily) nutrient requirements by blending diets that have differing nutrient densities. For sows, this is a very powerful tool, as nutrient requirements change considerably throughout the reproductive cycle. This research program will explore the use of computerized feeding technologies to generate and apply precision feeding programs for lactating sows, explore the effects of precision feeding on sow productivity, and will develop evidence-based recommendations for feeding sows during the pre-farrowing (transition) and lactation periods. The potential benefits of using precision feeding technologies for lactating sows include optimizing sow performance (e.g., litter growth rates, lifetime productivity), reducing feed costs and environmental impact (minimize nutrient oversupply), and providing solutions to labour shortages on pig farms. We will use ~400 sows and their offspring over six studies. ","principal_investigator":"Lee-Anne Huber","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10125,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-15 14:23:44 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-15 14:23:44 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4040","organisation_id":20,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Myrto Grigoroglou","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10126,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-15 18:50:50 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-15 18:50:50 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4041","organisation_id":25,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Matthew Koristka","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10127,"title":"Kelda Newport (Memorial University of Newfoundland)","dmptemplate_id":20,"created_at":"2020-12-16 15:09:11 UTC","updated_at":"2021-01-06 13:25:23 UTC","slug":"kelda-newport-memorial-university-of-newfoundland","organisation_id":16,"grant_number":"","identifier":"","description":"Public Awareness of deprescribing ","principal_investigator":"Kelda Newport ","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"Kelda Newport","funder_name":null},{"id":10128,"title":"My plan (PortaFamily, residents, and nurses experiences of visiting restrictions in long-term care during COVID-19 pandemicge Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-16 17:07:30 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-16 17:12:06 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portafamily-residents-and-nurses-experiences-of-visiting-restrictions-in-long-term-care-during-covid-19-pandemicge-template","organisation_id":8,"