:"Nature: interpretive description methodology to do qualitative research around the experiences of prenatal education in a group setting with various health professionals involved compared to traditional one-on-one appointments with a physician. \r\n\r\nQuestions: do prenatals have better nutrition during pregnancy from having a dietitian involved in prenatal education?  Is there better uptake of education sessions with a physician involved in prenatal classes? Do prenatals prefer online, in-person or a mixture?  \r\n\r\nCollecting data to influence the way prenatal classes are offered in northern SK, specifically La Ronge with potential rollout to other communities. Especially those who use the standardized prenatal education program materials. ","principal_investigator":"Audrey Boyer","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10133,"title":"Maintaining Immunity+ Colostrum Bioactivity using a Unique Cold Plasma Method","dmptemplate_id":45,"created_at":"2020-12-18 21:29:37 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-18 21:37:09 UTC","slug":"maintaining-immunity-colostrum-bioactivity-using-a-unique-cold-plasma-method","organisation_id":22,"grant_number":"Food from Thought - Commercialization Grant","identifier":"Food from Thought - Commercialization Grant","description":"The goal of this project is to produce a shelf stable designer colostrum from HIRTM/Immunity+ cows using high voltage cold plasma (HVCP) technology, developed by Professor Keener. HVCP applies high voltage to generate a partially ionized gas which does not rely on heat. This technology can be used to extend the colostrum shelf-life, without compromising its bioactivity.","principal_investigator":"Bonnie Mallard","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"bmallard@ovc.uoguelph.ca","funder_name":null},{"id":10134,"title":"Mon plan (Modèle Portage)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2020-12-21 00:54:54 UTC","updated_at":"2020-12-21 00:54:54 UTC","slug":"mon-plan-mode