trol deficits, different gut microbiota profiles,\r\naltered tryptophan (TRP) metabolism and gut dysmotility compared to non-\r\nFP birds. We intend to elucidate the importance of microbial influence on\r\nTRP metabolism and its link to FP. An experiment is to be performed to\r\ninvestigate the effect of providing birds with probiotics, and determine their\r\neffect on behaviour and physiology as a potential strategy to\r\nprevent/reduce FP in laying hens. Furthermore, we will perform behavioural\r\ntesting to investigate birds’ motivation for accessing these probiotics in an\r\nattempt to regulate their gut microbiota profile and FP behaviour.","principal_investigator":"Alexandra Harlander","principal_investigator_identifier":"","data_contact":"","funder_name":null},{"id":10143,"title":"My plan (University of British Columbia Generic Template)","dmptemplate_id":11,"created_at":"2021-01-06 00:03:18 UTC","updated_at":"2021-01-06 00:05:04 UTC","slug":"my-plan-university-of-british-columbia-generic-template--643","organisation_id":7,"grant_number":"n/a","identifier":"H19-03428-A001","description":"The project was a retrospective chart review of patients diagnosed with and treated for cesarean scar ectopic pregnancies at Vancouver General Hospital from 2010 to 2019. 11 patients were identified and treatment outcomes were recorded. An algorithm was created for future use that will be evaluated with a prospective study.","principal_investigator":"Natasha Simula","principal_investigator_identifier":"Nicole Todd","data_contact":"Natasha Simula","funder_name":null},{"id":10144,"title":"My plan (Portage Template)","dmptemplate_id":12,"created_at":"2021-01-06 13:31:48 UTC","updated_at":"2021-01-06 13:31:48 UTC","slug":"my-plan-portage-template--4049","organisation_id":8,"grant_number":null,"identifier":null,"description":null,"principal_investigator":"Victoria Holla","principal_investigator_identifier":null,"data_contact":null,"funder_name":null},{"id":10145,"title":"My plan (